name: A Doubt
examine: A Doubt is a monster fought during the Dream Mentor quest in the Dream World. Many Doubts are summoned during the first battle by The Inadequacy. They represent Cyrisus, the protagonist, and his little nagging doubts about combat. Though they can be fought and killed easily, they disappear once the player defeats The Inadequacy.

name: Aberrant spectre
examine: Aberrant spectres are Slayer monsters that require level 60 Slayer to kill. To avoid stat drain during combat with one, equip a nose peg or slayer helmet. They frequently drop large numbers of grimy herbs and herb seeds. Because of this, bringing a herb sack and seed box when killing them is recommended.

name: Abhorrent spectre
examine: The Abhorrent spectre is a superior variant of the normal aberrant spectre. It has a 1/200 chance of spawning upon killing an aberrant spectre if the player has unlocked Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Abomination
examine: The Abomination is a monster fought during A Taste of Hope after it invades the Myreque Hideout. It is the result of a sinister experiment performed on Serafina's brother in order to allegedly save his life after he was cut by a poisoned blade.

name: Abyssal demon
examine: Abyssal demons are one of the strongest types of demons, requiring level 85 Slayer to be damaged. Alongside their boss variant, they are the only creatures in the game to drop the abyssal whip and abyssal dagger.

name: Abyssal guardian
examine: An Abyssal guardian is a monster that dwells in the Abyss, and also in the Abyssal Area (fairy ring code ALR). Abyssal guardians have fairly high Strength for their combat level, though they have low Attack and Defence levels. Abyssal guardians initiate attack with melee, but use magic if attacked first or the player is attacking them from a distance. Their magic attacks are stronger than their melee attacks, but less accurate. However, as they have a very fast reaction time while aggressive, players usually see the magic attack only after they become un-aggressive.

name: Abyssal leech
examine: An abyssal leech is a monster that dwells in the Abyss, and also in the Abyssal Area. They are the easiest abyssal monsters to kill because they have low defence, low strength, and low hitpoints. However, they have a very high attack level and attack speed, attacking every second tick, making them more dangerous than their combat level may suggest.

name: Abyssal portal
examine: The abyssal portal is a portal that leads deep into the Abyss, and was created by Xeric. While admiring the other world, Vespula flew through the portal and attacked Xeric's crew, who fled the scene. Vespula now controls the area and tends to her offspring while protecting the portal.

name: Abyssal Sire
examine: The Abyssal Sire is an abyssal demon slayer boss that requires level 85 Slayer to kill. To access the boss, the player must have visited the Abyss at least once, either through the Mage of Zamorak or the fairy ring network.[1] As with all other slayer bosses, the Sire can only be fought when assigned abyssal demons or itself as an assignment. Although it resides in a multi-combat area, it is a solo-only boss.

name: Abyssal walker
examine: The Abyssal walker is one of many monsters which can be found in the Abyss, and also in the Abyssal Area (fairy ring code: ALR). They are difficult to hunt as they seem to have a high defence, hitpoints, and strength, although they have low accuracy. It should also be noted that they are difficult to poison, although they are not immune to it. Abyssal walkers killed in the Abyss yield much lower experience. These monsters are aggressive, but will stop being aggressive after a while as well as the Abyssal guardian and the Abyssal leech.

name: Acidic Bloodveld
examine: The Acidic Bloodveld is a monster encountered while fighting Vanstrom Klause during Sins of the Father. During the fight, Vanstrom will occasionally say "My pets will feast on your corpse!", which summons the bloodveld. The bloodveld should be killed from a distance using a ranged or magic attack, or else it will explode for 40+ damage. When the bloodveld is killed, a pool of acid appears on the ground. Stepping on the pool of acid will deal additional damage.

name: Adamant dragon
examine: Adamant dragons are metal dragons first encountered during Dragon Slayer II, in which the player must fight against one during Zorgoth's assault. After completion of the quest, they can be found in the western chamber of the Lithkren Vault.

name: Afflicted
examine: The Afflicted are villagers of Mort'ton who were cursed by Lord Lowerniel Vergidiyad Drakan's evil gust of wind. They speak nonsense to the player if talked to.

name: Agrith Naar
examine: Agrith-Naar is a level 100 Greater demon who is the main antagonist of the Shadow of the Storm quest. He is summoned and then destroyed using Silverlight, which results in the blade transforming into Darklight as a result of absorbing his blood.

name: Agrith-Na-Na
examine: Agrith Na-Na is a banana-based Agrith-Naar, from the Shadow of the Storm quest, fought in the final battle of the Recipe for Disaster quest. He attacks with Magic and melee and has good defensive stats. He can be fought in the Nightmare Zone after the quest is complete.

name: Ahrim the Blighted
examine: Ahrim the Blighted is the oldest of the Barrows brothers and uses the Magic corner of the combat triangle. His crypt is found in the centre of the Barrows. He wears robes, which make him vulnerable to Ranged as well as Melee attacks. Ahrim can easily damage the player with his magical attacks, as they are very accurate even on dragonhide armour. Aside from this, Ahrim can also use Confuse, Weaken and Curse on the player, lowering their Attack, Strength and Defence stats respectively. Ahrim's set effect is Blighted Aura, which gives him a 20% chance to lower the player's Strength stat by 5 for each successful hit.

name: Air elemental
examine: Air elementals are encountered during the Elemental Workshop I quest. As with all elementals, if players cast spells of the elemental's element, the spell will heal instead of damaging the elemental. It should be noted that players do not actually have to kill any air elementals to complete Elemental Workshop I.

name: Air wizard
examine: The air wizard is a monster that is located in the meadow north-east of Rimmington and south of Falador. The wizard can be seen wearing white robes, a white cape, and wielding a staff of air.

name: Al Kharid warrior
examine: Al Kharid warriors are guards of Al Kharid found in the palace. When one warrior is attacked, the others will attempt to attack you as well. It is an excellent place to train for medium-level players because Al Kharid warriors have high Hitpoints but a low combat level, making this a great place to train Attack, Strength and Defence up to level 25-30. The warriors are fairly well known for their great low-level herb drop rate.

name: Albino bat
examine: Albino bats are animals found in the Mos Le'Harmless Cave. They are aggressive and may be a nuisance to players fighting cave horrors; however, they are fairly easy to kill due to their low hitpoints, so players with full Guthan's armour may choose to use them as a means of healing.

name: Alchemical Hydra
examine: The Alchemical Hydra is a boss found in the lower level of the Karuulm Slayer Dungeon in Mount Karuulm, requiring level 95 Slayer to kill. The Alchemical Hydra was the creation of a Dragonkin named Karuulm. While Karuulm saw promise in his creation, he nevertheless saw it as a failure because he could not replicate its traits, and abandoned it along with his other creations: the Wyrms, Drakes, and Hydras.

name: Alexis
examine: Alexis is one of the citizens of Canifis. If you are not wielding wolfbane when you attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is more friendly if you are wearing a ring of charos.

name: Alomone
examine: Alomone is the leader of the Cult of Hazeel south of Ardougne. Players could choose to side with Hazeel during the Hazeel Cult quest. If the player chooses not to side with him, Alomone must be killed later on in the quest. When he is killed he will drop a Carnillean armour, but this is only during the Hazeel Cult quest. The drop trick can be used to obtain more than one by getting it as a drop and then quickly killing him again to obtain another. Interestingly, unlike the other Hazeel Cultists, Alomone doesn't drop bones. He is the only one in the hideout not wielding a staff. An interesting note is that when he attacks, even though he appears unarmed, instead of the normal 'hit noise' a dagger sound is made.

name: Alrik
examine: Alrik is a subject of Miscellania currently located in the Miscellania market.

name: Ammonite Crab
examine: Ammonite Crabs can be found on the most coastal areas and the most northern beaches of Fossil Island, as well as in the northern Wyvern Cave.

name: Ancient Guardian
examine: The Ancient Guardian is a quest monster that is encountered at the end of Below Ice Mountain.

name: Ancient Wizard
examine: Ancient Wizards appear when doing master clue scrolls when the player digs for a clue directed by the strange device or coordinates, in multicombat areas. Each wizard uses a different attack style and can hit fairly high, requiring players to be prepared for a three-on-one fight.

name: Ancient Wyvern
examine: Ancient Wyverns are Slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 82 in order to be harmed. They reside in the Wyvern Cave on Fossil Island and are the strongest species of Wyvern in Old School RuneScape. Like with other Wyverns, an elemental, mind, dragonfire or ancient wyvern shield provides significant protection against their icy breath. These monsters require completion of the Bone Voyage quest to be assigned as a Slayer task.

name: Ancient Zygomite
examine: Ancient Zygomites are stronger variants of mutated zygomites that require level 57 Slayer to harm. They are found exclusively on Fossil Island in the Mushroom Forest. Ancient zygomites cannot be killed unless a fungicide spray has been used to deliver the final blow. They first appear as non-attackable Ancient Fungi, which players must pick in order to provoke them out of the ground.

name: Angry barbarian spirit
examine: An Angry barbarian spirit is found in the Ancient Cavern, along with many other high-levelled monsters, including Mithril dragons. They are quite high hitting (with a maximum hit of 18) but have low accuracy.

name: Angry bear
examine: Angry bear is a monster that first appears during A Soul's Bane.

name: Angry giant rat
examine: Angry giant rat is a monster that first appears during A Soul's Bane.

name: Angry goblin
examine: Angry goblin is a monster that first appears during A Soul's Bane.

name: Angry unicorn
examine: Angry unicorn is a monster that first appears during A Soul's Bane.

name: Animated Adamant Armour
examine: Animated adamant armour is found at the Warriors' Guild. It is the second most powerful variant of animated armour. To summon one, players must use an adamant platebody, adamant platelegs, and an adamant full helm on the magical animator. Defeating this armour is one of the fastest methods of obtaining tokens. If you are a high level, farming the rune version might be a faster option.

name: Animated Black Armour
examine: Animated black armour is a foe that is encountered at the Warriors' Guild. To summon one, players must use a black platebody, black platelegs, and a black full helm on the magical animator. The black animated armour is commonly used to farm tokens by lower levelled players, as it's one of the weakest variations of animated armour. If you are a high level with access to decent equipment, fighting rune would be a quicker alternative to earn tokens.

name: Animated Bronze Armour
examine: Animated bronze armour is a player-created foe, encountered at the Warriors' Guild. To summon one, players must use a bronze platebody, bronze platelegs, and a bronze full helm on the magical animator. The bronze animated armour isn't commonly used for two main reasons: pieces will occasionally be lost, and higher variants yield better tokens per hour.

name: Animated Iron Armour
examine: Animated iron armour is a player-created foe that is encountered at the Warriors' Guild. To summon one, players must place an iron platebody, iron platelegs, and an iron full helm on the magical animator. Like the steel and bronze animated armour, iron isn't commonly used for two main reasons: platelegs will occasionally be lost, and higher variants yield better tokens per hour.

name: Animated Mithril Armour
examine: Animated mithril armour is a player-created foe encountered at the Warriors' Guild. To summon one, players must use a mithril platebody, mithril platelegs, and a mithril full helm on the magical animator. This mithril version is commonly used to farm tokens, due to the fact that it is relatively easy to defeat with lower stats. If you are a high level with access to decent equipment, fighting rune would be a quicker alternative to earn tokens.

name: Animated Rune Armour
examine: Animated rune armour is found at the Warriors' Guild and is the most powerful animated armour in the Animated Armour activity. In order to summon it, you must place a rune full helm, a rune platebody and rune platelegs on the magical animator. This is one of the quickest ways to earn tokens overall, and depending on the player's accuracy, defeating Animated Rune is the fastest way to obtain them.

name: Animated spade
examine: The Animated spade is a monster that can be found just outside Tarn's Lair. As their name suggests, they are spades that appear to move on their own. The spades are apparently controlled by the spirits trapped in the Abandoned Mine. Often, unprepared players who have little or no knowledge of the lair may try to pick it up just to mistakenly attack it and get attacked back. The spades stand tall and upright, slightly off the ground.

name: Animated Steel Armour
examine: Animated steel armour is a player-created foe, encountered at the Warriors' Guild. To summon one, players must use a steel platebody, steel platelegs, and a steel full helm on the magical animator. The steel animated armour isn't commonly used for two reasons: helms will occasionally be lost, and higher variants yield better tokens per hour.

name: Animated steel armour (Tarn's Lair)
examine: Animated steel armour is a set of armour enchanted by Tarn Razorlor when players do battle with him in his lair. He will enchant scrap armour in the area to come alive and attack players, but are more of an inconvenience rather than a threat. They do not need to be killed to complete the fight.

name: Anja
examine: Anja is found upstairs in the house north of the Hetty's house in Rimmington, along with her husband Hengel. A player can ask her for "free stuff", but after a very long dialogue, she will only give the player 1-3 coins. She can also be pickpocketed for 3 and 8 Thieving experience.

name: Ankou
examine: Ankou are skeletal, ghostly monsters. Ankou in the fourth level of the Stronghold of Security can drop the left skull half, one of four parts of the Skull sceptre.

name: Apparition
examine: Apparitions are the manifestations of some of the Menaphite Pantheon; specifically Het, Apmeken, Scabaras, and Crondis. They are fought during Icthlarin's Little Helper, depending on which canopic jar is taken during the quest.

name: Archer (Ardougne)
examine: Archers are found in Ardougne, atop Ardougne Castle. They are not aggressive to players, but when attacked, will defend themselves with Ranged attacks that are fairly accurate and can hit up to 5.

name: Archer (Burthorpe)
examine: Archers are level 42 guards for Burthorpe Castle in Burthorpe, and are members of the Imperial Guard.

name: Arianwyn
examine: Arianwyn Cadarn (pronounced ah-ree-ann-win cah-darn) is the leader of the rebel elves' settlement of Lletya. He is first encountered by players in Ardougne at the end of the quest Regicide, after which he can be interacted with in the building at the very east end of Lletya. Players must have started Mourning's End Part I to enter Lletya and encounter Arianwyn. Arianwyn is heavily featured in the quests Mourning's End Part I and Part II.

name: Armadylean guard
examine: Armadylean guards appear when doing elite clue scroll coordinates. They call out "No warning! Begone!" upon appearing.

name: Armoured Foe
examine: The Armoured Foe was a version of Callisto that could be found roaming the Wilderness during the Wilderness Wars event. Teams who killed it would receive an upgrade to their weapons and armour, thereby gaining an advantage over the other teams.

name: Arrg
examine: Arrg is a quest monster that must be defeated during Troll Romance. All mountain trolls are named after the first thing they ate or tried to eat. Arrg, however, makes an exception. With some trolls, the name of what they first ate is unknown. This is the case with Arrg, so he was named after the sound made by the first thing he ate. This is the same case with Ug and Aga.

name: Arzinian Avatar of Magic
examine: The Arzinian Avatar of Magic is an avatar of the Arzinian Being of Bordanzan that may be fought in the Between a Rock... quest. It only appears if a player's highest combat stat is melee; if it is magic or ranged, the avatar of ranging or strength will appear instead, respectively. However, this is not guaranteed as there is an element of randomness programed into the encounter.[1]

name: Arzinian Avatar of Ranging
examine: The Arzinian Avatar of Ranging is an avatar of the Arzinian Being of Bordanzan that may be fought in the Between a Rock... quest. It only appears if a player's highest combat stat is magic, if it is melee or ranged, the avatar of magic or strength will appear instead, respectively. However, this is not guaranteed as there is an element of randomness programed into the encounter.[1]

name: Arzinian Avatar of Strength
examine: The Arzinian Avatar of Strength is an avatar of the Arzinian Being of Bordanzan that may be fought in the Between a Rock... quest. It only appears if a player's highest combat stat is ranged, if it is melee or magic, the avatar of magic or ranging will appear instead, respectively. However, this is not guaranteed as there is an element of randomness programed into the encounter.[1]

name: Assassin (A Kingdom Divided)
examine: The assassin is an enemy players encounter during A Kingdom Divided.

name: Asyn Shade
examine: Asyn Shades are found in the Shade Catacombs beneath Mort'ton, and are fought in the Shades of Mort'ton minigame.

name: Asyn shadow (Temple Trekking)
examine: Asyn shadows can be encountered in Temple Trekking, while travelling along the medium path through Mort'ton.

name: Avatar of Creation
examine: The Avatar of Creation is one of the two avatars in the Soul Wars minigame, being the counterpart of the Avatar of Destruction.

name: Avatar of Destruction
examine: The Avatar of Destruction is one of the two avatars in the Soul Wars minigame, being the counterpart of the Avatar of Creation.

name: Aviansie
examine: Aviansies (sometimes referred to as aviantese[1] in plural form) are avian monsters found in the southern section of the main chamber of the God Wars Dungeon. Like other creatures within the dungeon, they can be found fighting for their god Armadyl, engaging in combat against the followers of Zamorak.

name: Awakened Altar
examine: The awakened altars can spawn on the north, east, south and west wall of Skotizo's lair during the fight against Skotizo. These altars increase Skotizo's Defence and reduce the amount of damage he takes while activated. If you're wielding Arclight, each altar reduces damage by 15% up to a maximum of 60%. Otherwise, with other weapons, it's 25% up to a maximum of 100%.[1] They have 100 Hitpoints each. Hitting the awakened altars with an Arclight will instantly disable them in one hit, regardless of the player's stats and gear.

name: Baby black dragon
examine: Baby black dragons are the young of adult black dragons and are the strongest baby dragons in Old School RuneScape. Unlike their adult form, they are too young to breathe flames, so no anti-dragon shield or other protection from dragonbreath is needed to fight them. Baby black dragons have combat stats comparable to those of an adult green dragon.

name: Baby blue dragon
examine: Baby blue dragons are the young of adult blue dragons found in Taverley Dungeon, the Isle of Souls Dungeon, and in the basement of the Myths' Guild. Unlike their adult forms, they do not breathe fire.

name: Baby blue dragon (20th Anniversary event)
examine: Baby blue dragons were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. They had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 29 August 2006.

name: Baby dragon (unused)
examine: The Baby dragon was an unused monster that was added in the RuneScape 2 Beta. It did not have any colour, and just used the generic grey baby dragon model with no recolouring. It is unknown what purpose, if any, the monster was intended to serve, yet it remained in the game files for many years and was graphically updated in 2006. Therefore, it was never present in Old School RuneScape, and was deleted entirely from the cache on 10 September 2015.

name: Baby green dragon
examine: Baby green dragons are small green dragons that are found in Brimhaven Dungeon, east of the fire giants upstairs. There is also one spawn located in the basement of the Myths' Guild. There is an agility shortcut that allows direct access to them, requiring level 87 in Agility. Unlike their adult forms, they do not breathe fire.

name: Baby red dragon
examine: Baby red dragons are located in the Brimhaven Dungeon, Forthos Dungeon and in the basement of the Myths' Guild. They have the same combat level as the baby blue dragons that inhabit the Taverley Dungeon.

name: Baby red dragon (Construction)
examine: A baby red dragon can be built in the Guard space of the Oubliette and Dungeon in a player-owned house. It requires 82 Construction to build and when built, it gives 387 experience.

name: Baby Roc
examine: The Baby Roc is a monster encountered during the My Arm's Big Adventure quest. It is level 75 and is relatively easy compared to the Giant Roc that must be fought afterwards. Unlike the Giant Roc, it cannot stun players and only uses Melee.

name: Baby tanglefoot
examine: Baby tanglefeet are located in the shady grove, which is located close to the Cosmic Altar in Zanaris. They are a weaker version of the Tanglefoot monster, which is fought during the A Fairy Tale Part I quest.

name: Balfrug Kreeyath
examine: Balfrug Kreeyath is a three-faced black demon who destroyed the desert city of Ullek during the God Wars. He is one of K'ril Tsutsaroth's bodyguards, along with Zakl'n Gritch and Tstanon Karlak. He attacks with Magic by launching huge fireballs at the player and has a maximum hit of 16.

name: Bandit
examine: Bandits are enemies that inhabit the Bandit Camp (Wilderness). The bandits are guarded by Guard Bandits. These bandits are aggressive, so players should take caution when approaching the camp. The camp's champions, however, such as Donny the lad, are not aggressive.

name: Bandit (Bandit Camp)
examine: Bandits are attackable NPCs, which are found at the Kharidian Desert Bandit Camp. They are descendants of the followers of Zaros who were persecuted by the followers of Saradomin and Zamorak, and bear a grudge toward their followers for this reason. They can be pickpocketed at level 53 Thieving, yielding coins, antipoison, or lockpicks. Each successful pickpocket awards 79.4 Thieving experience.

name: Bandit (Pollnivneach)
examine: Pollnivnian Bandits are located in northern Pollnivneach in between the general store and the rug merchant. They are the fastest Thieving experience at level 45 Thieving. Unbearded Pollnivnian Bandits are also the fastest Thieving experience at 55 Thieving. The best way to distinguish them from one another is by their combat level and beards. Bearded bandits are level 41 combat and wield blackjacks, whereas unbearded bandits are level 56 combat and wield steel scimitars. Level 41 bearded Pollnivnian bandits grant 65 experience and 40 coins per pickpocket. Level 56 unbearded Pollnivnian bandits grant 84.3 experience and 50 coins per pickpocket.

name: Bandit (Shayzien)
examine: Shayzien bandits can be found roaming the Shayzia Ruin.

name: Bandit champion
examine: Ali the bandit champion is a Pollnivnian bandit henchman fought during The Feud quest. He will appear after the player speaks to the leader of the Pollnivnian bandits. When he is killed, he drops bones and a Willow blackjack, or if you already have a Willow blackjack in your inventory, an Adamant scimitar.

name: Bandosian guard
examine: A Bandosian guard can appear while completing the Coordinates portion of an Elite clue. They have the form of an Ork which can be found in the God Wars Dungeon. It is recommended that players use the Protect from Melee prayer as Bandosian guards use only melee attacks. Upon killing the monster dig again in the correct location in order to receive the next clue.

name: Banshee
examine: Banshees are a Slayer monster that require level 15 Slayer to kill. They can be found at the Slayer Tower in Morytania on the ground floor[UK]1st floor[US], on the eastern side. Players must wear earmuffs while fighting them in order to avoid the effects of their screams, which causes the player to take 6 damage and have their stats greatly reduced in Attack, Strength, Defence, Ranged, Magic, Prayer and Agility with every attack received. There is a safespot to the north of the staircase leading to the 1st floor[UK]2nd floor[US], behind the standing torch, between the staircase and wall. As banshee's attacks are magic-based, it is advised to wear ranged armour in order to minimise damage taken while fighting them. As banshees qualify as undead, the effects of the Salve amulets and the Crumble Undead spell will work on them.

name: Barbarian
examine: Barbarians are attackable NPCs found in the Barbarian Village and Outpost. They are commonly fought for training by lower level players due to their low Defence and the many obstacles in the Barbarian Village usable as Safespot. If the player chooses to talk to them, they will taunt the player with quotes such as "Wanna fight?" or "You come to fight, ja?" and immediately attack; players can avoid this by immediately exiting the dialogue instead of clicking to continue.

name: Barbarian (Barbarian Camp)
examine: Barbarians are attackable NPCs found at the Barbarian Camp in the Kourend Woodland. If the player chooses to talk to them, they will taunt the player with quotes such as "Wanna fight?" or "You look funny!" and immediately attack; players can avoid this by immediately exiting the dialogue instead of clicking to continue.

name: Barbarian (historical)
examine: Barbarian is an unused barbarian that was originally found at the Barbarian Village and Barbarian Outpost in the early stages of RuneScape 2. On 20 February 2006 the Barbarian Village was graphically updated, and its inhabitants were replaced by new Barbarians with unique names. While the original Barbarians remained at the Outpost, they too were replaced with the release of Barbarian Assault. As a result, the unused NPCs have never been present in Old School RuneScape.

name: Barbarian Warlord
examine: A Barbarian Warlord can be found in the dungeon by the barbarian camp in the Kourend Woodlands. He is battled during quest A Kingdom Divided when investigating the camp for Lord Hosidius.

name: Barbarian woman (historical)
examine: Barbarian women were attackable NPCs that could previously be found at several locations. Following several updates they were gradually phased out of the game, and replaced by unique characters with mostly the same combat stats and drops.

name: Bark Blamish Snail
examine: The Bark Blamish Snail is one of many snails that roam around the Mort Myre Swamp and the surrounding area.

name: Barrelchest
examine: Barrelchest is a monster that serves as the boss near the end of The Great Brain Robbery. It has two attack styles. If in melee range, it attacks with its anchor and deactivates all prayers and drains prayer points. If the player is outside of melee range, it performs an attack in which it slams its anchor to the ground, triggering an earthquake that can inflict up to 25 damage. However, it will not use its ranged attack if the player is standing behind something (AKA safespotting).

name: Basilisk
examine: A basilisk is a Slayer monster that requires a Slayer level of 40 to kill. Like cockatrice, players must equip a mirror shield or V's shield when fighting these monsters. Players require a Defence level of 20 in order to receive basilisks as a Slayer task, as this is required to wield the shield. To get a basilisk task from Duradel, Nieve, or Konar, players must have also purchased the "Basilocked" slayer reward, costing 80 points. Basilisks have below-average accuracy for their level, but have high Defence. They are weak to crush attacks, so weapons such as the Leaf-bladed battleaxe and the Dragon mace are unusually strong if using melee. The Dragon mace is  generally around the same damage per second as the Dragon scimitar, while the Leaf-bladed battleaxe is approximately 5% greater damager per second than either.

name: Basilisk Knight
examine: Basilisk Knights are a Slayer creature that can be found in the Jormungand's Prison beneath the Island of Stone, requiring level 60 Slayer and completion of The Fremennik Exiles to kill. Like cockatrice and basilisks, players must equip a mirror shield or V's shield when fighting these monsters or they will take heavy damage and their stats will be drained.

name: Basilisk Sentinel
examine: The Basilisk Sentinel is a superior variant of a Basilisk Knight. It has a chance of spawning when a basilisk knight is killed if the player has purchased the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Basilisk Youngling
examine: The basilisk youngling is encountered during The Fremennik Exiles, when searching through the sand pit in north-east Rellekka, north of Freygerd's house. The youngling will hit constant 6s and drain stats when fought without a mirror shield.

name: Bat
examine: Bats are small flying monsters that are most commonly found in numerous dark areas throughout Morytania. They are weak and pose little threat to players.

name: Battle mage
examine: Battle mages are magic-users found in the Wilderness Mage Arena. They appear in the arena itself, and their primary function is to battle the player, thus allowing the player to cast their chosen god spell 100 times on any of the mages in order to be able to use the spell outside of the Arena.

name: Bear Cub
examine: A Bear Cub is a smaller version of the weaker variant of Grizzly bear. They are only found near grizzly bears.

name: Bedabin Nomad Fighter
examine: Bedabin nomad fighters are attackable NPCs that can be found in the Bedabin Camp in the Kharidian Desert. They are friendly and not aggressive, and will even give directions to the Shantay Pass if asked. They appear to be wearing desert clothing and an iron scimitar.

name: Berry
examine: Berry is a troll that guards the prison in the Troll Stronghold, and is featured in the Troll Stronghold quest. He holds the Cell key 2, which is needed to open the cell where Eadgar is held.

name: Berserk barbarian spirit
examine: A berserk barbarian spirit is a monster found in the Ancient Cavern, where one spawns in the south-east corner of the main floor. According to Otto Godblessed, these are the spirits of barbarians that were killed while voyaging down into the Ancient Cavern.

name: Big frog
examine: Big frogs are monsters found in the Lumbridge Swamp, the Lumbridge Caves, the Dorgesh-Kaan South Dungeon and the Lizardman Settlement. They play a minor role in the Rag and Bone Man I quest, as their bones are on his "wish-list".

name: Big Snake
examine: The Big Snake is a large snake encountered in the Freeing King Awowogei subquest of Recipe for Disaster. It uses slow but strong melee attacks and is poisonous.

name: Big Wolf
examine: The Big Wolf is a canine monster found around the White Wolf Mountain. It can prove deadly to low-level players attempting to cross the mountain. There's also one west of the Feldip Hills, but sports a darker colour coat.

name: Billy Goat
examine: A Billy Goat is a larger version of a goat, and is found in most of the same places. There are brown and tan coloured billy goats, but serve no difference in combat.

name: Bird
examine: Birds are avian enemies found on Ape Atoll, Crash Island, inside the Nature Altar, and throughout the Isle of Souls. They attack with melee and can be assigned as Slayer assignments by Turael. Although they are airborne, they use melee.

name: Black bear
examine: Black bears are large monsters that can be found in forests and are the weaker, non-aggressive cousins of the aggressive grizzly bear.

name: Black chinchompa (Hunter)
examine: The black chinchompa is a chinchompa that players can capture with the Hunter skill at level 73 or above and the completion of Eagles' Peak, granting 315 Hunter experience.

name: Black demon
examine: Black demons are large demons that inhabit a few dungeons throughout Gielinor. As demons, they have high combat stats but rather low Defence for their level. They are weak to demonbane weapons; as with most demons, they are also weak to magical attacks.

name: Black demon (20th Anniversary event)
examine: Black demons were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. They had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 29 August 2006.

name: Black demon (The Grand Tree)
examine: A unique Black demon is summoned by Glough during The Grand Tree. This demon can be re-fought in the Nightmare Zone after the quest has been completed. Killing Black demons in Nightmare Zone will count as a kill for a Slayer task.

name: Black dragon
examine: Black dragons are very powerful monsters, and like all other dragons, an anti-dragon shield or equivalent or Antifire potion is recommended in order for the player to protect themselves from their dragonfire. They are also the strongest common chromatic dragon in-game. As with all other common chromatic dragons, their dragonfire attack is melee-range only. Black dragons are the only common chromatic dragons that drop the draconic visage. Notably, the stronger level 247 variant in the Wilderness Slayer Cave drops the draconic visage at a rate of 1 in 5,000, the most common out of any dragon tied with the King Black Dragon and Vorkath.

name: Black dragon (20th Anniversary event)
examine: The Black dragon was an occupant of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. Black dragons had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 29 August 2006.

name: Black golem
examine: The Black golem is encountered during the Spirits of the Elid quest. He guards the southernmost door in the River Elid cave and appears in front of the player, exclaiming "You may not pass!" and must be defeated using the Crush attack style. Other styles work, but deal significantly lower damage.

name: Black Guard
examine: Black Guards are members of the Dwarven Black Guard found throughout areas controlled by the Dwarven Realm. They give Slayer experience if players are assigned to kill dwarves. They wield black warhammers, however the black guard in Keldagrim attack with them much faster than a normal warhammer.

name: Black Guard Berserker
examine: Black Guard Berserkers are located in the western half of Keldagrim, where they guard the headquarters of the Dwarven Black Guard. Here they guard key dwarven figures such as Commander Veldaban and Supreme Commander Bisi.

name: Black Heather
examine: Black Heather is a member of the leading trio of Bandits in the Wilderness Bandit Camp in levels 24-31 of the Wilderness, along with Donny the lad and Speedy Keith. She, like the other two leaders, wields a steel scimitar.

name: Black Knight
examine: Black Knights, also known as the Kinshra, are human warriors found mainly in their fortress and stronghold. They are central to the Black Knights' Fortress quest.

name: Black knight (Port Sarim Jail)
examine: A unique Black knight can be found locked up in the Port Sarim Jail. The Black knight's cell can not be entered, though the player can use Ranged, Magic or long-distance Melee weapons such as Halberds to attack him through the bars.

name: Black Knight (Wanted!)
examine: A unique Black Knight is encountered while following Solus Dellagar during the Wanted! quest. At the penultimate scan location, Solus will summon this Black Knight to attack the player. Upon defeating the Black Knight, Savant will complete the scan of the area, revealing Solus's final location at the Rune essence mine.

name: Black Knight Titan
examine: The Black Knight Titan is encountered during the Holy Grail quest. He is reasonably powerful for his level; but his attacks are inaccurate and very slow. He should be fought with Melee, as he has exceedingly high Ranged and Magic defence. If the player is not holding Excalibur as his hitpoints reach 0, he regenerates back to full hitpoints and players must kill him again. This means either the finishing blow must be dealt using Excalibur, or (if using a delayed attack such as magic or ranged) Excalibur must be switched to before the blow hits him. Since the titan is immobile, players with a fast weapon may employ a hit-and-run technique to kill the titan without being hit. Players can also use a halberd from two squares away to melee him without taking damage.

name: Black unicorn
examine: The black unicorn is a slightly more dangerous version of the unicorn. These creatures are aggressive to all level players when in the Wilderness, but are low-levelled, so they won't affect high levelled players much. They are a very easy way to obtain unicorn horns in decent quantities, as they are present in greater numbers than normal unicorns. They also have a faster spawn rate and tend to walk around quite a bit in their area, and will sometimes run away when their health is low.

name: Black unicorn Foal
examine: A black unicorn foal is a black unicorn's offspring.

name: Blessed giant rat
examine: The blessed giant rat is a type of giant rat on the second floor in the Underground Pass.

name: Blessed spider
examine: A blessed spider is a type of spider found only in the Underground Pass. They are found on the west side of the bridge and in the pit where Kalrag is located. They are believed to be blessed or "converted" to Iban. Like most spiders, blessed spiders attack with melee and are weak to crush.

name: Blood Blamish Snail
examine: The Blood Blamish Snail is a type of snail which live in the north-east part of Mort Myre Swamp. A chisel can be used on the dropped shell to make a blood'n'tar snelm which gains the player 32.5 crafting XP. This is the same for all snelms. They also provide bonus protection against Mort Myre snail attacks.

name: Blood Reaver
examine: Blood Reavers are a type of demon in the service of Zaros found in the Ancient Prison within the God Wars Dungeon. They attack using a spell that resembles Blood Rush and can heal themselves a percentage of damage inflicted.

name: Blood spawn
examine: Blood spawn are monsters that spawn during the The Maiden of Sugadinti encounter in the Theatre of Blood, in which up to eight can spawn. If players successfully avoid the Maiden's blood splat attack, the chances of a blood spawn spawning are halved.

name: Bloodveld
examine: Bloodveld are a type of demon that use their long tongues to attack their victims. Being a Slayer monster, Bloodveld require a Slayer level of 50 to be damaged by players.

name: Bloodworm
examine: Bloodworms are a species of yellowish-reddish, leech-like creatures that lurk in the Barrows tunnels where they live in the darkness and feed on the blood of unwary treasure hunters. Bloodworms are one of the many obstacles between a player and the chest containing rewards where they constantly distract players from completing puzzles. As with all monsters in the crypts, they are aggressive to any player regardless of their Combat level. They are commonly killed alongside two skeletons each run as a quick way to optimise the player's reward potential for the most runes. They may spawn whenever the player opens a door in the tunnels.

name: Blue dragon
examine: Blue dragons are the third strongest of the chromatic dragons, behind red dragons and black dragons. Like all dragons, they can breathe dragonfire, which can inflict up to 50 damage if proper protections aren't used. Dragonfire can be mitigated by equipping an anti-dragon shield or a dragonfire shield – alongside the usage of an antifire potion, which will completely negate dragonfire damage. On top of the strong dragonfire breath, they also attack with an accurate slash attack.

name: Blue dragon (20th Anniversary event)
examine: The Blue dragon was an occupant of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. Blue dragons had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 29 August 2006.

name: Boar
examine: A boar is monster that roams in the woods west of Kourend Castle and the southern island of The Node.

name: Body Golem
examine: The Body Golem is one of the golems found in the Ruins of Camdozaal. It can be found by awakening the rubble lying in the section north-east of the bank chest.

name: Boris
examine: Boris is one of the citizens of Canifis. If players are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when attacking, he will turn into a werewolf. He is more friendly if wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Borrokar
examine: Borrokar is one of Rellekka's many citizens. Borrokar lives in a hut next to the Rellekka mine. He also drops lyres which can be used in The Fremennik Trials, rather than having to make them with 25 Fletching. At level 45 Thieving and after The Fremennik Trials, he can be pickpocketed for 40 coins and 65 Thieving experience.

name: Bouncer
examine: Bouncer is a hellhound that is fought during the Fight Arena quest. He is General Khazard's pet and only friend. It is possible to range or mage him from behind the skeletons that lie scattered around the arena. It is also possible to use a halberd to attack him from one of these safespots.

name: Bouncer (ghost)
examine: Bouncer's ghost is the ghost of General Khazard's deceased pet hellhound named Bouncer, which the player killed during the Fight Arena quest. It is fought at the end of the The General's Shadow miniquest, and resides in a hidden area in the Goblin Cave north of Ardougne until it is slain once more by the player.

name: Brassican Mage
examine: Brassican Mages are followers of Brassica Prime, and the only known followers of the cabbage deity in Old School RuneScape.

name: Brawler
examine: A brawler is a monster from the Pest Control minigame. They are often considered irritating monsters because of their ability to stop players and monsters from walking through them, sometimes preventing players from reaching Spinners or running to the next portal. However, this impassibility also affects other monsters and as such can be used strategically to block monsters from being able to attack the Void Knight.

name: Bree
examine: Bree is the centaur bodyguard of Commander Zilyana, commander of Saradomin's Encampment, along with Growler and Starlight. He uses ranged attacks and has a chance to drop the Saradomin sword.

name: Breoca
examine: Breoca is a citizen of Burthorpe.

name: Brine rat
examine: Brine rats are Slayer monsters that can be found in the Brine Rat Cavern near Rellekka. They are notable for being the only monsters to drop the Brine sabre. A Slayer level of 47 is required to fight them, and a spade is required to access the cavern.

name: Broddi
examine: Broddi is a subject of Miscellania found in the Miscellania market.

name: Bronze dragon
examine: Bronze dragons are metallic dragons found deep within the Brimhaven Dungeon and the Catacombs of Kourend. They are the weakest of the six metallic dragons, but they still should not be underestimated. It is highly recommended to use an anti-dragon shield as otherwise these monsters can deal fatal damage via long-ranged dragonfire. Antifire potions are also recommended, and using both the shield and antifires will negate all dragonfire damage. With just one alone, some damage will be inflicted. It is the only metallic dragon that does not drop the very rare draconic visage. Due to that and their lackluster drops aside from the rare dragon platelegs or skirt, they are not as commonly killed as other dragons.

name: Broodoo victim
examine: Broodoo victims are undead creatures which appear during the Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup minigame. They can be found while cutting light, medium or dense jungle bushes. They use Magic attacks which can drain a player's combat stats. They are highly resistant to conventional attack methods (the player's max hit is reduced to 3), but certain consumables can be used on them to damage them:

name: Bruise Blamish Snail
examine: The Bruise Blamish Snail can be found in the depths of the Mort Myre Swamp. A chisel may be used on the shell it drops to make a snelm. There are two types of these snails:

name: Brutal black dragon
examine: Brutal black dragons are slayer monsters found in the Catacombs of Kourend. Requiring level 77 Slayer in order to be damaged, they are a tougher version of black dragons and as such can be killed as an alternative for a black dragon Slayer task.

name: Brutal blue dragon
examine: Brutal blue dragons are found in the north-west section in the Catacombs of Kourend. They are currently the only monster to drop the blue d'hide body (an item rarely required for medium and hard emote clues).

name: Brutal green dragon
examine: Brutal green dragons are found in the Ancient Cavern, and are a much stronger relative to the green dragons in the Wilderness. Access to the brutal green dragons requires partially completing Barbarian Training. The brutal green dragons use a rudimentary Magic attack and a Melee attack both with a max hit of 18. They are immune to poison. Brutal green dragons can be slain as an alternative for a green dragon Slayer task.

name: Brutal red dragon
examine: Brutal red dragons are found in the north-west section in the Catacombs of Kourend, between the brutal blue and brutal black dragons. They can be killed as part of a red dragon Slayer task.

name: Bryophyta
examine: Bryophyta, the Moss Giantess, is an ancient and mystical moss giant boss who can be found in her lair in the Varrock Sewers. Bryophyta's lair is located just north of where the moss giants reside in the sewers, accessible either through the Varrock Sewers itself or by the agility shortcut from the Edgeville Dungeon. (51 Agility required)

name: Bunny
examine: Bunnies are small rabbits found near the Swaying tree in Rellekka. They can be killed for a Rabbit bone during Rag and Bone Man II.

name: Bush snake
examine: Bush snakes can be found while hacking the jungle around Tai Bwo Wannai Village on Karamja during the Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup minigame. As with all threats encountered during the minigame, killing them awards the player with some favour. It drops snake hide.

name: Callisto
examine: Callisto is an enormous bear empowered by the corruption of the Wilderness that resides south of the Demonic Ruins and is the only monster to drop the tyrannical ring. He attacks using Melee. He can knock players back a few tiles, which renders them unable to move for a few seconds, as well as heal himself slightly. He is also able to perform a deadly shock wave attack that can hit up to 60 and may combine this with a melee attack, which is capable of instantly killing the player if they are within melee range and do not have Protect from Melee active.

name: Camp dweller
examine: Camp dwellers are residents of the Mountain Camp, found in the northeast Fremennik Province near the entrance to Keldagrim.

name: Carnivorous chinchompa
examine: The carnivorous chinchompa is a chinchompa that players can capture with the Hunter skill at level 63 or above after completion of Eagles' Peak, granting 265 Hunter experience each.

name: Catablepon
examine: Catablepon are creatures that appear to be green bulls with reptilian tails. They are found on the third level of the Stronghold of Security. They drop the top of sceptre, one of four parts of the Skull sceptre.

name: Cave abomination
examine: The cave abomination is a superior variant of the cave horror. When on task, it has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock "Bigger and Badder" for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Cave bug
examine: Cave bugs are monsters that require level 7 Slayer to kill. They are found in the Lumbridge Swamp Caves, requiring a light source and a rope to enter, and stronger variants can be located in the Dorgesh-Kaan South Dungeon. They are a good source of low level herbs, which can aid beginning players in training Herblore. Their Hitpoints regenerate about 20 times faster than normal.[1]

name: Cave crawler
examine: Cave crawlers are Slayer monsters that require level 10 Slayer to kill. They can inflict poison, so it is advised that players bring antipoison potions when fighting them. They are the only enemy to drop bronze boots. They also drop a variety of Herblore ingredients, which can be helpful for lower level players looking for an alternative source of herbs over more popular sources, such as Chaos druids. Lower level players should be aware that they have a high hit point regeneration, essentially every “0” damage ticks is a hit point regenerated. This can lead to being completely unable to kill the cave crawler.

name: Cave goblin (monster)
examine: Cave goblins are goblins of the Dorgeshuun who can be found in the Lumbridge Swamp Caves. They are friendly creatures, and are willing to give many adventurers a tinderbox (if the player does not have one) when spoken to after the player assures that they are not there to hurt the cave goblins. Upon being attacked, they will scream "Nooo!", "Don't hurt us!" or "Eeek!" and nearby Cave goblins will try and flee.

name: Cave goblin guard
examine: The cave goblin guards guard the Dorgeshuun Mines. They can be seen patrolling the mines with their boney spears or clubs. They protect the cave goblin miners, and will command, "Stop that!", and begin to attack you if you are spotted assaulting a miner.

name: Cave goblin miner
examine: The cave goblin miners are found outside of Dorgesh-Kaan in the Dorgeshuun Mines. They can be found strutting about the rocks or mining ore. They wield a bone pickaxe that is not obtainable by players, but instead is just used to symbolise the Dorgeshuun's ability to adapt to new use of materials. If you are found attacking one, a cave goblin guard will yell, "Stop that!", and will target you.

name: Cave horror
examine: Cave horrors are a slayer monster found in the Mos Le'Harmless Cave. Killing them requires the completion of Cabin Fever, level 58 Slayer, a witchwood icon, and a light source (unless a fire of eternal light is lit). They are most often killed for their black mask drops along with a decent rate of hard clue scrolls.

name: Cave kraken
examine: Cave kraken are slayer monsters that are found in the Kraken Cove. They can only be attacked if players have them as a Slayer task. To be assigned cave krakens, players require level 87 Slayer and 50 Magic.

name: Cave lizard
examine: Cave lizards are creatures native to the Ourania Cave. They can be seen fighting the Zamorakian guards on the path to the Ourania Altar.

name: Cave slime
examine: Cave slimes are Slayer monsters that require level 17 Slayer to kill. They inflict poison regardless of whether they do damage or not, so it is advised that the player brings a form of anti-poison when fighting them. As they are located in the Lumbridge Swamp Caves, a rope is needed if you have not entered the dungeon before. A light source is also required, but be aware that any exposed light sources (such as a candle) may explode, causing some damage.

name: Ceolburg
examine: Ceolburg is a citizen of Burthorpe who will tell you a little of what is going on in the town.

name: Cerberus
examine: Cerberus is a level 318 hellhound boss that is located in her lair, deep beneath the Taverley Dungeon in the cave entrance in the north-east part of the hellhound area which is found beyond the poisonous spiders. Cerberus requires a Slayer level of 91, along with a task of hellhounds or Cerberus herself. In the event of the hellhound or elite clue scroll task, wild pies may be used to boost the player's Slayer level.

name: Champion of Scabaras
examine: The Champion of Scabaras is fought during the Beneath Cursed Sands quest.

name: Chaos druid
examine: Chaos druids are low-level humans commonly killed for their frequent drops of herbs. Unlike most druids, they worship both Guthix and Zamorak. They attack with their fists and make use of a spell that appears to be a combination of the Confuse and Bind spells, binding their target very briefly if successful.

name: Chaos druid warrior
examine: Chaos druid warriors can be found in Yanille Dungeon, which requires 40 Agility to access. Alternatively, they can be found on the Slepe church's roof.

name: Chaos dwarf
examine: Chaos dwarves are a type of corrupted and dangerous dwarves following Zamorak found in various locations, most notably the Wilderness. It is revealed in Forgettable Tale of a Drunken Dwarf that they are the result of experiments by The Red Axe in their attempt to conquer Keldagrim.

name: Chaos Elemental
examine: The Chaos Elemental is a dark cloud with six tentacles that dwells in the members-only section of the Wilderness, just west of the Rogues' Castle. This area is moderately easy to access from the deep Wilderness teleport lever in Ardougne or Edgeville. A Wilderness Obelisk can randomly teleport players south-east of the Rogues' Castle.

name: Chaos Fanatic
examine:
The Chaos Fanatic is an insane mage that resides west of the Lava Maze. He is surrounded by unattackable miniature chaotic clouds, which serve as scenery. He drops one of three shards required to forge Odium wards and Malediction wards. He has a special attack where he uses a green magical attack that explodes and can deal high damage, similar to the Crazy Archaeologist's explosive book attack. Players must run away from them to avoid damage.
He is also able to disarm players, much like how the Chaos Elemental does. He is also one of the only monsters (including mummies, Vet'ion and the thermonuclear smoke devil) to drop the ancient staff.

name: Chaos Golem
examine: The Chaos Golem is one of the golems found in the Ruins of Camdozaal. It can be found by awakening the Rubble lying in the far south-east section of Camdozaal, south of the body golems.

name: Chaotic death spawn
examine: Chaotic death spawns are monsters that the Nechryarch can summon when it is being attacked. They function similarly to their normal variants.

name: Chasm Crawler
examine: The Chasm Crawler is a superior variant of the cave crawler. It has a chance of spawning once after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Chicken
examine: Chickens are a type of domesticated bird kept as livestock by farmers, and are often found inside pens in the farms of Gielinor.

name: Chicken (Tutorial Island)
examine: Chickens are found on Tutorial Island as part of the Magic training tutorial. The Magic Instructor provides air and mind runes to cast Wind Strike on a chicken to progress in the tutorial.

name: Chinchompa (Hunter)
examine: The chinchompa is a chinchompa that players can capture with the Hunter skill at level 53 or above and the completion of Eagles' Peak, granting 198.4 Hunter experience.

name: Choke devil
examine: The Choke devil is a superior variant of the normal dust devil. It has a chance of spawning once after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Chompy bird
examine: Chompy birds are part of the Chompy bird hunting activity. They can only be killed after completing the Big Chompy Bird Hunting quest. Killing them requires a comp ogre bow or ogre bow with brutal arrows or ogre arrows. They cannot be killed with melee or Magic. Bloated toads must be used as bait to lure them to the area. Bloated toads are made by using ogre bellows filled with swamp gas on nearby toads at the swamp. Chompy birds spawn in a 10 tile radius around the bloated toad (21x21 square). A Chompy bird will leave if it is not killed after one minute.

name: Chronozon
examine: Chronozon is a blood demon that must be defeated towards the end of the Family Crest quest. It is found in the Wilderness area of the Edgeville Dungeon, by the Earth obelisk. Chronozon must be hit with all four elemental blast spells in order to be killed, or otherwise it will return to full health when it is nearly dead. Players should note that Chronozon has to be hit (i.e. do actual damage: if the spell splashes, it will not count). It will not drop the crest part unless the player has completed most of the quest. He can be fought in the Nightmare Zone after the quest is complete.

name: City guard
examine: City guards can be found in the middle of Gu'Tanoth. Four bridges must be crossed to reach them. To cross these bridges, a rock cake from the market and 20 coins must be brought. During the Watchtower Quest, they provide players with a Skavid map.

name: Clivet
examine: Clivet is a member of the Cult of Hazeel, a group dedicated to the revival of the Zamorakian mahjarrat Hazeel.

name: Cockathrice
examine: The cockathrice is a superior variant of the cockatrice. It has a chance of spawning once the Bigger and Badder unlock has been purchased for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master. Like the cockatrice, a mirror shield or V's shield needs to be equipped in order to fight it. It can also be safespotted with Ranged or Magic like the regular cockatrices.

name: Cockatrice
examine: Cockatrice are Slayer monsters that require level 25 Slayer to kill. A mirror shield or V's shield is required to defend against their piercing gaze, or else they will reduce your combat stats every hit, even while safespotting. As 20 Defence is needed to be able to wield a mirror shield, players who do not meet this requirement will not be assigned them as a task. It is worth noting that their strength lies purely in their piercing gaze ability; with a protective shield equipped, do not expect much of a fight. As such, not a lot of resources are necessary to hunt this monster.

name: Colonel Radick
examine: Colonel Radick is located in Yanille near the west gate and has extremely high hitpoints for his combat level. He is probably the Colonel of the Yanille Army. Nevertheless, he doesn't play any role in any quest despite being a unique character. When talking to him, he asks if the player is a friend or a foe. Of course, if the friend option is chosen, he will let you go but if the foe one is chosen, he will attack the player. When asked why Yanille is so heavily defended, he explains that as the southernmost city of Kandarin it must be protected from the Ogres of the Feldip Hills.

name: Colossal Chocco Chicken
examine: The Colossal Chocco Chicken was a boss fought during the 2018 Easter event and the 2019 Easter event. The first time it is fought, it took the colour of the idol that the player picked during the event, and could only be fought solo. After the event, the chicken took on a rainbow-coloured appearance and could be fought by groups of players simultaneously. Unlike most monsters, the Colossal Chocco Chicken did not have a combat level.

name: Colossal Hydra
examine: The Colossal Hydra is a superior variant of the hydra. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Commander Zilyana
examine: Commander Zilyana is the appointed leader of Saradomin's forces in the God Wars Dungeon and one of only two living representatives of the Icyene race in Old School RuneScape, the other being the half-human half-Icyene Safalaan.

name: Confused barbarian
examine: The Confused barbarian is an attackable barbarian NPC that makes his home in the Ancient Cavern, near the Baxtorian Falls. Inside the Ancient Cavern it is located in one of the alcoves near the Brutal green dragons.

name: Confusion beast
examine: Confusion beasts are monsters from A Soul's Bane quest. They are found in the Confusion portion of the quest. Multiple of these beasts will pop up, only one of which being real while the others are merely illusions. You will not be able to damage the ones which are illusions. They may poison you, so it is recommended bring an anti-poison.

name: Corporeal Beast
examine: The Corporeal Beast, often referred to simply as Corp, is a large monster residing in its cave, accessible via a games necklace or through an entrance in level 21 Wilderness east of the Graveyard of Shadows. It has a very large health pool of 2,000 Hitpoints, coupled with high Defence and 50% damage reduction against most weapons; only spears and halberds (on stab attack style) and magic deal full damage. If all players leave the room, its Hitpoints regenerate at a rapid rate.

name: Corrupt Lizardman
examine: The Corrupt Lizardman is a monster fought in a cave at Mount Quidamortem during the Tale of the Righteous quest.

name: Corrupted Bat
examine: Corrupted Bats are low-level monsters found in the Corrupted Gauntlet. Their counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Bat. Up to 3 low-level monsters spawn in a room.

name: Corrupted Bear
examine: The Corrupted Bear is a mini-boss monster found in the Corrupted Gauntlet that attacks with Melee. Their counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Bear. Mini-boss monsters always spawn alone, and only appear at the edges of the Gauntlet map.

name: Corrupted Dark Beast
examine: The Corrupted Dark Beast is a mini-boss monster found in the Corrupted Gauntlet that attacks with Ranged. Their counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Dark Beast. Mini-boss monsters always spawn alone, and only appear at the edges of the Gauntlet map.

name: Corrupted Dragon
examine: The Corrupted Dragon is a mini-boss monster found in the Corrupted Gauntlet that attacks with Magic. Their counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Dragon. Mini-boss monsters always spawn alone, and only appear at the edges of the Gauntlet map.

name: Corrupted Hunllef
examine: The Corrupted Hunllef is the boss monster within The Corrupted Gauntlet. Its counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Hunllef.

name: Corrupted Rat
examine: Corrupted rats are low-level monsters found in the Corrupted Gauntlet. Their counterpart in the Gauntlet is the crystalline rat. Up to 3 low-level monsters spawn in a room.

name: Corrupted Scorpion
examine: Corrupted Scorpions are mid-level monsters found in the Corrupted Gauntlet. Their counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Scorpion. Mid-level monsters always spawn in pairs, if they spawn in a room.

name: Corrupted Spider
examine: Corrupted Spiders are low-level monsters found in the Corrupted Gauntlet. Their counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Spider. Up to 3 low-level monsters spawn in a room.

name: Corrupted Unicorn
examine: Corrupted Unicorns are mid-level monsters found in the Corrupted Gauntlet. Their counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Unicorn. Mid-level monsters always spawn in pairs, if they spawn in a room.

name: Corrupted Wolf
examine: Corrupted Wolves are mid-level monsters found in the Corrupted Gauntlet. Their counterpart in The Gauntlet is the Crystalline Wolf. Mid-level monsters always spawn in pairs, if they spawn in a room.

name: Count Draynor
examine: Count Draynor Drakan[1] lives in a coffin in the basement of Draynor Manor. He was part of House Drakan, being the younger brother of Lowerniel, Ranis and Vanescula Drakan.

name: Cow
examine: Cows are common low level monsters new players train on. They are one of the first NPCs new players see in Lumbridge. Cows can help new players earn money, Cooking experience, and combat experience. The cowhides that they drop can be tanned to make leather or hard leather, or they can be sold for coins to players wanting to raise their Crafting level. While most locations containing cows are crowded, there are some spots usually vacant, like the spot north of the windmill north-west of Lumbridge. Along with cows, you can also find cow calves and dairy cows.

name: Cow (Nightmare Zone)
examine: The cow is a Nightmare Zone "boss" which can randomly appear in practice mode[1], regardless of difficulty, sharing its normal combat stats with a regular cow. Unlike other bosses, it is not associated with a particular quest, and does not have any special mechanics which can endanger the player.

name: Cow calf
examine: Cow calves are low-level monsters commonly found among cows.

name: Crab
examine: Crabs are found only in an undersea crab pen located in a Mogre Camp off of Port Khazard. Crabs can be killed for crab meat, which is an ingredient of fishcake. They will occasionally drop a fresh crab claw or fresh crab shell, which can be crafted into a crab claw glove and crab helmet, respectively. They will also sometimes drop an oyster.

name: Crawling Hand
examine: Crawling Hands are Slayer monsters that require level 5 Slayer to kill. The Crawling hands are the first Slayer monster a player can defeat upon reaching the required level. They are also one of the creatures that will sometimes "die" in a perfect form allowing you to get it stuffed by a taxidermist and mounted in your player-owned house.

name: Crazy archaeologist
examine: Bellock, the crazy archaeologist is an insane individual and demi-boss who resides in the ruins south of The Forgotten Cemetery. He uses Ranged and Melee attacks and can perform a special attack where he throws explosive books that explode in a 3x3 area.

name: Crocodile
examine: Crocodiles are found in the Kharidian Desert south of Pollnivneach on either side of the River Elid. They are often assigned as Slayer tasks by Vannaka. Bring waterskins to avoid dying of thirst.

name: Cruor
examine: Cruor is one of the four mages guarding Nex in the Ancient Prison, within in the God Wars Dungeon. Having mastered blood magic, he enhances Nex's powers over blood. As with all of Nex's mages, he is immobile.

name: Crushing hand
examine: The Crushing hand is a superior variant of the Crawling Hand. It has a chance of spawning once after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Crypt rat
examine: Crypt rats are rats lurking in the Barrows tunnels. Crypt rats are one of the many obstacles between a player and the chest containing rewards where they constantly distract players from completing puzzles. As with all monsters in the crypts, they are aggressive to any player regardless of their Combat level. They may spawn whenever the player opens a door in the tunnels.

name: Crypt spider
examine: Crypt spiders are a stronger variant of spider found in the tunnels of the Barrows. Crypt spiders are one of the many obstacles between a player and the chest containing rewards where they constantly distract players from completing puzzles. As with all monsters in the crypts, they are aggressive to any player regardless of their Combat level.

name: Crystalline Bat
examine: Crystalline Bats are low-level monsters found in The Gauntlet. Their counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Bat. Up to 3 low-level monsters spawn in a room.

name: Crystalline Bear
examine: The Crystalline Bear is a mini-boss monster found in The Gauntlet that attacks with Melee. Its counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Bear. Mini-boss monsters always spawn alone, and only appear at the edges of the Gauntlet map.

name: Crystalline Dark Beast
examine: The Crystalline Dark Beast is a mini-boss monster found in The Gauntlet that attacks with Ranged. Its counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Dark Beast. Mini-boss monsters always spawn alone, and only appear at the edges of the Gauntlet map.

name: Crystalline Dragon
examine: The Crystalline Dragon is a mini-boss monster found in The Gauntlet that attacks with Magic. Its counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Dragon. Mini-boss monsters always spawn alone, and only appear at the edges of the Gauntlet map.

name: Crystalline Hunllef
examine: The Crystalline Hunllef (pronunciation "HIN-hlev") is the boss monster within The Gauntlet. Its counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Hunllef.

name: Crystalline Rat
examine: Crystalline Rats are low-level monsters found in The Gauntlet. Their counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Rat. Up to 3 low-level monsters spawn in a room.

name: Crystalline Scorpion
examine: Crystalline Scorpions are mid-level monsters found in The Gauntlet. Their counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Scorpion. Mid-level monsters always spawn in pairs, if they spawn in a room.

name: Crystalline Spider
examine: Crystalline Spiders are low-level monsters found in The Gauntlet. Their counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Spider. Up to 3 low-level monsters spawn in a room.

name: Crystalline Unicorn
examine: Crystalline Unicorns are mid-level monsters found in The Gauntlet. Their counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Unicorn. Mid-level monsters always spawn in pairs, if they spawn in a room.

name: Crystalline Wolf
examine: Crystalline Wolves are mid-level monsters found in The Gauntlet. Their counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Wolf. Mid-level monsters always spawn in pairs, if they spawn in a room.

name: Cuffs
examine: Cuffs is a thug who can be found loitering north of Falador, along with his associates Narf, Jeff, and Rusty. Since he is level 3 (compared to his friends, who are level 2) it is implied he is the leader/strongest member of the gang.

name: Culinaromancer
examine:
The Culinaromancer is the final boss in the Recipe for Disaster quest. He is, according to legend, an evil mage who draws his power from food.
A hundred years ago, the Culinaromancer was a cook in Lumbridge Castle for the town's duke. He used the exotic and esoteric foodstuffs to which he had access to improve his magical power. In the quest Recipe for Disaster, he was sealed away by Franizzard Van Lumbcook, one of the Lumbridge Castle cook's forefathers, when he threatened to destroy a council that gets together for a feast every ten years. Eliminating the secret council would have been the first step in his plan for world domination.

name: Cyclops
examine: A cyclops (plural cyclopes) is a large one-eyed monster. They are known for dropping many alchable drops, so bringing nature and fire runes is helpful as it allows players to make longer trips and more money without banking or taking up inventory space.

name: Dad
examine: Dad is an abnormally large troll that players must fight during the Troll Stronghold quest. Dad can be re-fought in the Nightmare Zone minigame after the player has completed Troll Stronghold.

name: Dagannoth
examine: Dagannoth are sea-based monsters that live in the Lighthouse basement (close to fairy ring code alp) after players complete Horror from the Deep (type 1 in the table). They can also be found in the southern part of the Catacombs of Kourend, as well as the Jormungand's Prison after completion of The Fremennik Exiles (type 2 in the table).

name: Dagannoth (Construction)
examine: A dagannoth can be built in the Monster space of the Treasure Room in a player-owned house. It requires 90 Construction to build and when built, it gives 2,738 experience.

name: Dagannoth (Horror from the Deep)
examine: A Dagannoth is fought in the Lighthouse basement, before the Dagannoth mother during Horror from the Deep. It only uses melee attacks, and can be safespotted by trapping it behind rocks in the basement.

name: Dagannoth (Waterbirth Island)
examine: Dagannoth are monsters that live in Waterbirth Island Dungeon. There are four types: level 88 and level 90 Dagannoth, level 70 Dagannoth fledgling , and level 42 Dagannoth spawn. This article deals with the level 88 and 90 varieties, which are significantly more dangerous than their lower levelled counterparts.

name: Dagannoth fledgeling
examine: Dagannoth fledgelings are found in the room with the Fremennik Bardur inside the Waterbirth Island dungeon, near the Dagannoth Kings.

name: Dagannoth mother
examine: The Dagannoth mother is fought at the end of the quest Horror from the Deep. She cycles through different colours to explicitly show her weaknesses.

name: Dagannoth Prime
examine: Dagannoth Prime is the Magic-based Dagannoth King found in the depths of the Waterbirth Island Dungeon, along with fellow Dagannoth Kings, Dagannoth Rex and Dagannoth Supreme. Prime is the only monster to drop the Seers ring and Mud battlestaff. His projectile resembles Water Wave. He, along with the other Dagannoth Kings, can also drop the dragon axe.

name: Dagannoth Rex
examine: Dagannoth Rex is the Melee-based Dagannoth King found in the depths of the Waterbirth Island Dungeon, along with fellow Dagannoth Kings, Dagannoth Supreme and Dagannoth Prime. Rex is the only monster to drop the Berserker and Warrior rings, which can become best-in-slot rings for Strength and Slash after being imbued at the Nightmare Zone. He, along with the other Dagannoth Kings, can also drop the rare dragon axe.

name: Dagannoth spawn
examine: Dagannoth spawn are baby dagannoth hatched from eggs found near the walls or water of Waterbirth Dungeon. The eggs will hatch as players walk near, as long as the nearby dagannoth are not yet tolerant towards the player. The eggs respawn after 5 minutes.

name: Dagannoth Supreme
examine: Dagannoth Supreme is the Ranged-based Dagannoth King found in the depths of the Waterbirth Island Dungeon, along with fellow Dagannoth Kings, Dagannoth Rex and Dagannoth Prime. Supreme is the only monster to drop the archers ring and seercull. He, along with the other Dagannoth Kings, can also drop the dragon axe.

name: Damien Leucurte
examine: Damien Leucurte is a vampyre who can be found in the upper floor of the Crombwick Manor in the town of Slepe. He appears to have forcefully taken control of the manor over Lord Crombwick, and is staring intensely at a painting.

name: Damis
examine: Damis is one of the four guardians of the Diamonds of Azzanadra, fought only when doing the Desert Treasure quest. He is the only guardian who exclusively uses melee to attack, however this is made up by him having two forms, with the second form being able to attack at a quick rate as well as draining Prayer rapidly. As with most monsters in the Shadow Dungeon, Damis allows other monsters to pass through him.

name: Dark Ankou
examine: Dark Ankous are randomly and uncommonly summoned during the fight with Skotizo. If the player kills a Dark Ankou, Skotizo may randomly summon another. There is a limit of one Dark Ankou in the room at a time. If a Dark Ankou spawns on the opposite side of Skotizo from the player, or if the player is attacking an altar, it will wander around the room. If the Dark Ankou walks near the player and they are attacking Skotizo, it will become aggressive towards them.

name: Dark beast
examine: Dark beasts are monsters that require 90 Slayer to kill, and are found in the Mourner Tunnels as well as in Iorwerth Dungeon in Prifddinas. Along with their superior variant, they are the only monster in the game to drop the dark bow and the death talisman.

name: Dark energy core
examine: The Dark energy core is a monster that appears from within the Corporeal Beast. This monster heals the Beast, and attacks any players within the vicinity of the Core. It is advised to kill the Dark Core as soon as it is launched towards the player, as it transfers the player's Hitpoints to the Corporeal Beast and in very large clans, can be quite irritating. It can be weakened immensely by poisoning it. Once it has been poisoned, its attacks will be extremely slow, although there must be at least one player around the Dark energy core or else it will start hopping around again and will attack normally. If the Dark energy core was stunned but someone moved away from him and he starts hopping around again, it cannot be stunned again. It will keep dealing damage rapidly until it is killed. If the Corporeal Beast dies, the Dark Core will disappear.

name: Dark warrior
examine: Dark warriors are mainly found in the Dark Warriors' Fortress, a castle in level 12 to 16 Wilderness north-west of Edgeville.

name: Dark wizard
examine: Dark wizards are mages who worship Zamorak and cast Strike spells.

name: Dawn
examine: Dawn, along with Dusk, are the Grotesque Guardians that require level 75 Slayer to kill. She is the boss version of the gargoyle, found on the Slayer Tower's rooftop. In order to access the roof, players must obtain a brittle key from gargoyles while assigned them for a slayer task. Similar to other slayer bosses, such as Cerberus and the Abyssal Sire, the Grotesque Guardians can only be killed while the player is assigned gargoyles as a slayer task.

name: Deadly red spider
examine: Deadly red spiders are an aggressive species of spider. Their eggs can usually be found nearby. The spiders found in Varrock Sewers are a popular training spot for free-to-play, as they reside in a multicombat area and are aggressive to low levels (up to level 68 combat). Bringing a knife or slash weapon is mandatory to access the area.

name: Death spawn
examine: Death spawns may be summoned when players are fighting nechryael or their greater variant; when attacked, they may summon up to two death spawns to help attack the player. While having an extremely low max hit of 2, they are able to hit through protection prayers. Unlike their summoners, death spawns have no Slayer requirement in order to be harmed.

name: Death wing
examine: Death wings are flying monsters that appear in the Legends' Quest. The death wings are located in a remote area, and have no drops, so very few players train on them. Killing a death wing is one of the hard tasks in the Karamja Diary.

name: Deathly mage
examine: Deathly mages are monsters found in the Chambers of Xeric, in the lodestone room. In solo and small groups, players will find two deathly mages alongside two deathly rangers.

name: Deathly ranger
examine: Deathly rangers are monsters found in the Chambers of Xeric, in the lodestone room. In solo and small groups, players will find two deathly rangers alongside two deathly mages.

name: Defiler
examine: Defilers are fast, agile creatures in the Pest Control minigame. They have the appearance of the lower half of a snake, a humanoid top half and a face resembling that of a cat. They can throw flying spikes over long distances, can inflict a large amount of Ranged damage with the missiles, and will actively attack the Void Knight.
