They can even launch their barbs over walls, though if they are in the spaces right in front of one of the three gates, they cannot shoot over it, so keeping them closed will block those directly in front of it. Even though they have no apparent link with imps, they make the same combat sound as imps.

name: Delrith
examine: Delrith is a demon of unknown origin resembling a Lesser demon in appearance. He is summonned by dark wizards from a stone table during the Demon Slayer quest. Delrith was once summoned in ancient times by a cult of monks. Immediately after being summoned he was confronted by Wally, an ancient knight of sorts, and quickly defeated with the powerful weapon known as Silverlight and an incantation. For unknown reasons the cult of Zamorakian Dark wizards at the south entrance of Varrock are performing the ritual to summon Delrith into this world again.

name: Demon (Construction)
examine: A demon can be built in the Monster space of the Treasure Room in a player-owned house. It requires 75 Construction to build and when built, it gives 707 experience.

name: Demon of Balance
examine: The Demon of Balance was a Guthixian demon who had to be defeated in order to obtain a demon's heart for Kolodion's spell during Mage Arena II miniquest. In order to summon it, players had to use an enchanted symbol to locate it, similar to using an enchanted key or strange device.

name: Demon of Darkness
examine: The Demon of Darkness was a Zamorakian demon who had to be defeated in order to obtain a demon's heart for Kolodion's spell during Mage Arena II miniquest. In order to summon it, players had to use an enchanted symbol to locate it, similar to using an enchanted key or strange device.

name: Demon of Light
examine: The Demon of Light was a Saradominist demon who had to be defeated in order to obtain a demon's heart for Kolodion's spell during Mage Arena II miniquest. In order to summon it, players had to use an enchanted symbol to locate it, similar to using an enchanted key or strange device.

name: Demonic gorilla
examine: Demonic gorillas are powerful creatures found in the Crash Site Cavern. Two of them are fought during Monkey Madness II, in the penultimate stage of the fight. After the quest is completed, more demonic gorillas can be found in the caverns alongside their tortured brethren. They are primarily killed for their zenyte shard and ballista component drops.

name: Deranged archaeologist
examine: The deranged archaeologist is a demi-boss located on Fossil Island, at the southern end of the Tar Swamp. An axe is required to chop a swamp vine in order to reach him. Directly before the area is a spine that will occasionally hit passing players for 10 damage and apply poison.

name: Derwen
examine: Derwen is an ancient servant of Guthix, who takes great interest in Justiciar Zachariah and Porazdir, attempting to keep a balance between them.[1] He has to be defeated in order to obtain the ent's roots for Kolodion's spell during Mage Arena II miniquest. In order to summon him, players have to use an enchanted symbol to locate him, similar to using an enchanted key or strange device.

name: Desert Lizard
examine: Desert lizards are Slayer monsters found in the Kharidian Desert, requiring level 22 Slayer to kill. In order to kill a desert lizard, an ice cooler must be used when it has less than 5 Hitpoints. If an ice cooler is used on a desert lizard with 5 or more Hitpoints, the cooler will be consumed but have no effect. Players can buy the "Reptile freezer" perk from a Slayer master for 90 Slayer points, which will automatically ice the desert lizard when it falls below 5 Hitpoints, provided that the player has an ice cooler in their inventory.

name: Desert snake
examine: A Desert snake can be found south of the orange salamander hunting area in the Kharidian Desert near the Smoke Dungeon entrance. A few may also be found near the Menaphite Thug tent in Pollnivneach. They are just like any other snake, and are non-poisonous. Some players may kill these because they do not hit very high but Waterskins will be needed. They have just two drops: bones, and snake spines which are used during Rag and Bone Man II.

name: Desert Wolf
examine: A desert wolf is a type of wolf that is located in the Kharidian Desert. Players who wish to kill desert wolves should bring waterskins or wear the Desert amulet 4 to avoid damage from thirst and possibly death. The desert wolf is relatively easy to defeat, being a low level monster. Players below its level should not mess with it, especially pures. It is quite abundant in the Kharidian Desert, so if you do not wish to fight it, just run away. Better yet, use the Magic carpet service to get away from monsters. They are aggressive to players level 54 Combat and below. Anyone under its level should be extremely careful and make sure they have plenty of waterskins and food. One should note that the desert beyond the Shantay Pass is under the thirst effect. Use caution fighting these in the desert at a low level; higher levels should not have to worry.

name: Dessourt
examine: Dessourt is one of the bosses fought during Recipe for Disaster. He resembles Dessous from Desert Treasure. He is most vulnerable to Magic and fairly weak to Ranged and stab. He is resistant to slash and crush.

name: Dessous
examine: Dessous, the Harvester of Blood, is a vampyre lord who owns some territory north of Castle Drakan. He must be killed during the Desert Treasure quest. The player is told of Dessous by Malak, one of the four guardians of the Diamonds of Azzanadra, who wants him dead in order to claim Dessous's land as his own. In order to achieve this, Malak tells the player that Dessous guards the diamond and if they wish to retrieve it they must eliminate him; it is when the player encounters Malak after the fight that he confesses that he is the real guardian and that Dessous was just an enemy of his, and then gives the diamond to the player as a reward for their troubles. According to Malak, Dessous is ancient but weak for vampyre standards and indeed he describes him as a 'frail and decrepit example of our species.'

name: Deviant spectre
examine: Deviant spectres are stronger variants of aberrant spectres that require level 60 Slayer to kill. They are found exclusively within the Catacombs of Kourend. Directly east of the djr fairy ring there is a mysterious hole for quick access to this creature, which must be accessed from below before being able to be used. The closest bank to this location is the Shayzien bank, which is south-east of the mysterious hole.

name: Dharok the Wretched
examine: Dharok the Wretched is the second oldest of the six Barrows brothers. Dharok's crypt is located in the north-east of the Barrows area. He uses melee equipment, which make him vulnerable to Magic attacks. Dharok's set effect is Wretched Strength, which increases his max hit by 1% for each Hitpoint he is missing.

name: Dire Wolf
examine: Dire Wolves are one of the stronger species of wolf found in Isafdar, near the limestone mine and Lletya. Four can also be found on Mynydd, with one of them being albino.

name: Disciple of Iban
examine: Disciples of Iban support Iban and are located in the Underground Pass. They drop Zamorak robes and, if one does not have one in their bank or inventory and has completed Underground Pass, a broken Iban's staff, which can be repaired by bringing it and 200,000 coins to the Dark Mage in West Ardougne.

name: Don't Know What
examine: Don't Know What is a troll found in the troll town of Weiss, and is Mother's bodyguard. During Making Friends with My Arm, he was the next in line to rule Weiss and marry Snowflake. However, after the events of the quest, he is defeated and now takes over Boulder's role as the gatekeeper.

name: Donny the lad
examine: Donny the lad is one of the three Bandits that lead the Wilderness Bandit Camp. Players cannot talk to Donny, any attempt to will give the player a message that states: "Donny the Lad is not interested in talking". Speedy Keith and Black Heather are the other two leaders of the Wilderness Bandit Camp.

name: Doomion
examine: Doomion is a demon encountered during the Underground Pass quest. When killed, it drops the amulet of doomion, which is needed to obtain Iban's shadow. Protect from Melee should be used during this part of the quest to save hitpoints for coping with its attacks.

name: Double agent
examine: Double agents appear when doing hard or master clue scroll emote clues. They call "I expect you to die!" upon appearing.

name: Drake
examine: Drakes  are wingless dragons found in the middle level of the Karuulm Slayer Dungeon in Mount Karuulm, requiring level 84 Slayer to kill. As they are only found within the volcano, players must wear the boots of stone, boots of brimstone or granite boots to protect themselves from the extreme heat of the dungeon floor. Alternatively, players who have completed the elite Kourend & Kebos Diary can wear any type of footwear, or no footwear, without being rapidly burned.

name: Druid
examine: Druids are level 33 non-player characters found in the druidic village of Taverley, a small settlement in western Asgarnia. They attack with both Melee and Magic (similar in appearance to Entangle). These druids are sometimes fought for the herbs that they carry, although chaos druids are a better source of herbs.

name: Drunken man
examine: The drunken man can be found in the upstairs of the Rising Sun Inn in Falador square. He has a distinct walking animation, resembling the "drunk" stance held by players when equipping Ale of the gods or Crystal chalice. When spoken to, he asks why there are two of the player before describing "giant hairy cabbages" and moving away across the room.

name: Duck
examine: Ducks are small animals which can be found in rivers or lakes. They are a fairly good way to start training the Magic skill with low-Level Curse spells and even Strike spells.

name: Duckling
examine: Ducklings are smaller versions of Ducks found swimming in the pond north-west of Lumbridge, by Farmer Fred's farm. They can only be attacked with ranged or magic attacks.

name: Duke
examine: Duke replaces Kruk as head of the Ninja Monkey Guards of Marim after the events of Monkey Madness II. He can be spoken to post-quest to receive 2 x 50,000 XP rewards in Magic, Ranged, Attack, Defence, Strength, or Hitpoints. He can be found on the east hill above the main gate of Ape Atoll. This hill can be reached by walking up the west hill and climbing up the ladder to access a bridge leading to the east hill.

name: Dungeon rat
examine: Dungeon rats are rare monsters found only in select members' dungeons. They play a key role in the Clock Tower quest in which players poison their food trough so that they attempt to escape by chewing away a railing, which allows the player to grab the white cog.

name: Durial321
examine: Durial321 was a player spoof found in Falador within unrestricted worlds during the World 666 event. He attacked with his abyssal whip and was able to cast Ice Barrage. Upon death, he would always drop a green partyhat awarded to the player who dealt the most damage. In keeping with the idea of him being an actual player, protection prayers could be used to reduce his attacks' damage but did not negate them entirely.

name: Dusk
examine: Dusk, along with Dawn, are the Grotesque Guardians that require level 75 Slayer to kill. It is the boss version of the gargoyle, found on the Slayer Tower's rooftop. In order to access the roof, players must obtain a brittle key from gargoyles while assigned them for a slayer task. Similar to other slayer bosses, such as Cerberus and the Abyssal Sire, the Grotesque Guardians can only be killed while the player is assigned gargoyles as a slayer task.

name: Dust devil
examine: A dust devil is a Slayer monster that requires level 65 Slayer to kill. They are located in the Smoke Dungeon and the Catacombs of Kourend. The use of a facemask or a Slayer helmet is required to fight dust devils as they use clouds of dust, sand, ash, and whatever else they can inhale to blind and disorient their victims. Dust devils cannot be assigned as a Slayer task until starting Desert Treasure.[1]

name: Dwarf
examine: Dwarves are a race characterised by their short stature and love of mining and beer. They are low-levelled enemies and can occasionally be given out as Slayer tasks by Turael. Even though the level 10 dwarves between Falador and the Barbarian Village appear to have steel pickaxes, they do not drop them, although they do drop bronze pickaxes.

name: Dwarf gang member
examine: Dwarf gang members are the cronies of Hammerspike Stoutbeard, and are encountered during the One Small Favour quest. They live in the Dwarven Mine below Ice Mountain.

name: Eadburg
examine: Eadburg is the Burthorpe Castle chef, and can be found wandering around the ground floor[UK]1st floor[US] of the castle.

name: Earth elemental
examine: Earth elementals are found beneath Seers' Village during the Elemental Workshop I and Elemental Workshop II quests. There are several roaming around in the quest area, but the player can also cause one to appear by mining a rock in the earth room.

name: Earth warrior
examine: Earth warriors are a type of humanoid earth elemental found in a dirt-lined chamber in the Edgeville Dungeon. This area is in the Wilderness so it is advised to come prepared for player killers.

name: Earth Warrior Champion
examine: The Earth Warrior Champion can only be fought after receiving the earth warrior champion scroll as part of the Champions' Challenge minigame.

name: Earth wizard
examine: The earth wizard is a monster that is located in the meadow north-east of Rimmington and south of Falador. The wizard can be seen wearing green robes, a green cape, and wielding a staff of earth.

name: Eduard
examine: Eduard is one of the citizens residing in Canifis. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack him, he will turn into a werewolf. He is more friendly if you are wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Einar
examine: Einar is a subject of Miscellania. He lives in the Miscellania castle in the northern room on the 1st floor[UK]2nd floor[US]. Killing him will take away 4.72% Managing Miscellania favour.

name: Elder Chaos druid
examine: Elder Chaos druids are high-level mages that are extremely dangerous compared to their low-level counterparts, the chaos druids. Elder Chaos druids use Wind Wave, which is fairly accurate if players are not properly equipped. They can also cast a teleportation spell that brings players within meleeing distance if the player tries to evade the battle (if there are multiple targets, they will attempt to teleport the player running that has done the most damage to them before others, even if they are attacking someone else). The special closely resembles that of abyssal demons. Elder Chaos druids are a popular place for multicombat player killing. It is suggested to use Protect from Magic when killing these; otherwise, they can be very dangerous and can kill unsuspecting players very quickly. The altar nearby can be used to restore prayer points.

name: Elf Archer
examine: Elf Archers are rebel elves found in Lletya. After completion of the Regicide quest, slayer masters can assign them as a Slayer task.[1] They are usually killed on task or for teleport crystals used to teleport to Lletya or, upon completion of Song of the Elves, Prifddinas.

name: Elf Warrior
examine: Elf warriors are rebel elves who can be found in Lletya. Players who have completed Regicide can receive them as a Slayer task.[1] They are usually killed either as a Slayer task or to obtain teleport crystals which grant quick teleportation to Lletya.

name: Elvarg
examine: Elvarg is the dragon that players have to kill in the Dragon Slayer I quest. She resides in the dungeon below Crandor. She is a green dragon, and is considerably stronger than the usual kind. Unlike other chromatic dragons, Elvarg has a ranged dragonfire attack. Despite being a dragon, she is not vulnerable to dragonbane weapons.

name: Enclave guard
examine: Enclave guards are ogres that guard the Ogre Enclave dungeon in the heart of Gu'Tanoth. During the Watchtower quest, players must use a cave nightshade on them twice (on different occasions) in order to be able to enter the enclave. After the quest, a cave nightshade does not have to be used to enter the cave, but the following message will appear: You run past the guard while he's busy.

name: Energy sprite
examine: Energy sprites are monsters within the Clan Wars Ethereal arena, where they fuel the energy for the mystic symbols, which players can use to teleport around the arena. Killing them cuts off the energy, and thus prevents players from using the symbols. The energy sprites respawn in exactly one minute.

name: Enormous Tentacle
examine: Enormous Tentacles are the tentacles of the Kraken that resides in the Kraken Cove. Four must surface by disturbing the four whirlpools in the boss area, and then disturbing the larger whirlpool, in order for the Kraken to surface.

name: Enraged barbarian spirit
examine: The enraged barbarian spirit is a level 166 spirit that can be found in the Ancient Cavern. They are along with many other high-levelled monsters, including mithril dragons and waterfiends. They are capable of large amounts of damage, with 18 being their highest hit, but they have low accuracy. Protect from Melee can be used to completely avoid damage.

name: Enraged Boar
examine: An Enraged Boar can be found on the southern island of The Node.

name: Ent
examine: Ents are monsters found in the dungeon beneath the Woodcutting Guild and in the forests north and east of the Chaos Temple. Ents are found on members' worlds exclusively.

name: Entrana firebird
examine: The Entrana firebird is a unique bird found only on the holy isle of Entrana, on the northern part of the island. During Heroes' Quest, the player must kill it to receive the fire feather. You must have ice gloves to pick up the feather it drops.

name: Essyllt
examine: Essyllt is a member of the Iorwerth Clan and the true leader of the mourners in West Ardougne, in reality the Prifddinas Death Guard. Before Song of the Elves, he can be found in his office in the Mourner Headquarters in West Ardougne.

name: Evil Chicken
examine: The Evil Chicken is a magical high-level chicken found in the Champions' Guild chicken coop. While fighting the Evil Chicken, players will suffer drastically reduced experience gain, at a rate of only 2.5% the norm, meaning they may not necessarily gain experience on each consecutive successful hit. The chicken respawns at a fixed rate.

name: Evil Chicken (Recipe for Disaster)
examine: The Evil Chicken is a version of the Evil Chicken fought during the Freeing Sir Amik Varze subquest of Recipe for Disaster. He is found in the Evil Chicken's Lair, and drops the egg needed to create the Brulee supreme.

name: Evil spirit
examine: The Evil spirit is the boss in Rum Deal. It only attacks with Melee, so turning on Protect from Melee is sufficient in protecting a player from most damage. High-levelled players should not worry about this battle, as the spirit is rather weak and has few hitpoints for its level.

name: Experiment
examine: Experiments can be found in the experiment cave which can be accessed during Creature of Fenkenstrain quest. They are accessed after the star amulet is placed on the easternmost memorial with the indent on it and then pushed to reveal their dungeon.

name: Experiment No.2
examine: Experiment No.2 is found in the manhole near the Witch's House during and after the Grim Tales quest. This monster has both a melee and ranged attack, although it will only use one style depending on your distance from it.

name: Fareed
examine: Fareed, the Warrior of Smoke is one of the four guardians of the Diamonds of Azzanadra, fought only in the Desert Treasure quest. Fareed possesses the unique ability to disarm players who are not wearing ice gloves when they are attacking him close up.

name: Farmer
examine: Farmers are level 7 humans found on farms. Farmers are fairly weak and can be fair melee training for lower levels. Players with level 10 Thieving can pickpocket farmers, gaining 14.5 experience.

name: Fear reaper
examine: Fear reapers are creatures encountered during and after the A Soul's Bane quest. During the quest, they will only appear after peeking into the various dark holes throughout the room. After the quest, they roam freely, and are a fair bit stronger. Fear reapers can easily be safespotted using magic, ranged, or a halberd.

name: Feral Vampyre
examine: Feral Vampyres are dangerous creatures found in the Haunted Woods, near the Abandoned Mine, and in the God Wars Dungeon. They are aggressive, and will attack anyone. They appear to be a weaker, more animalistic creature than other vampyres, and can be harmed by all weapons. Feral vampyres always drop vampyre dust. Having garlic in your inventory does not weaken feral vampyres.[1]

name: Ferocious barbarian spirit
examine: A Ferocious barbarian spirit appears as a result of using mangled bones at the pyre site around Otto's whirlpool, south of Barbarian Outpost.

name: Fever spider
examine: Fever spiders are Slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 42 to kill, found only on Braindeath Island, in the brewery basement. This indirectly means players must also have started the Rum Deal quest in order to access them. Players must wear slayer gloves while fighting them, or face being damaged repeatedly and becoming diseased. Fever spiders are considered to be a relatively fast task due to the large quantity of spiders and their low Defence.

name: Fire elemental
examine: The Fire elemental is a living inferno. It appears during the Elemental Workshop I and Elemental Workshop II quests. The fire elemental can be found in the Elemental Workshop, along with water elementals, earth elementals and air elementals.

name: Fire giant
examine: Fire giants are powerful giants that are popular for training Ranged and Slayer. They are also the strongest of the standard giants, being significantly stronger than their Ice and Moss relatives.

name: Fire Warrior of Lesarkus
examine: Leka,[1] the Fire Warrior of Lesarkus, is a temple guardian encountered while exploring during the Temple of Ikov quest. He guards a door leading to Winelda the witch.

name: Fire wizard
examine: The fire wizard is a monster that is located in the meadow north-east of Rimmington and south of Falador. The wizard can be seen wearing red robes, a red cape, and wielding a staff of fire.

name: Fiyr Shade
examine: Fiyr Shades lurk behind the silver door in the Mort'ton Shade Catacombs. They initially appear as very dark moving shadows on the ground and then rise from the depths to attack or retaliate. On occasion they have also been known to leave their catacombs to attack trekkers and ramblers in the town above their dark burial place. Their remains can be cremated with Magic pyre logs or Redwood pyre logs, requiring a Firemaking level of 80 and 95 respectively. The Salve amulet and Salve amulet (e) work on Fiyr Shades but do not stack with the Black mask (i).

name: Flambeed
examine: Flambeed is the second boss in the Recipe for Disaster quest. He is similar to the boss Fareed from Desert Treasure. He attacks using fairly strong melee attack and close-range Magic. Players are advised to wear ice gloves while fighting him as when he lands a hit on the player, if they are not wearing ice gloves, their weapon will be unequipped. Flambeed is weak to Water spells, melee attacks (especially crush) and Ice arrows.

name: Flaming pyrelord
examine: The Flaming pyrelord is a superior variant of the pyrefiend. It has a chance of spawning once after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Flawed Golem
examine: The Flawed Golem is one of the golems found in the Ruins of Camdozaal. It can be found by awakening the Rubble lying in the section south of the bank chest.

name: Flesh Crawler
examine: Flesh Crawlers are medium level monsters found in the second level of the Stronghold of Security. They drop the bottom of sceptre, one of four parts of the Skull sceptre. Flesh crawlers drop herbs often, and are frequently killed for their uncommon Ranarr drops.

name: Flight Kilisa
examine: Flight Kilisa is one of the aviansie bodyguards of Kree'arra, along with Wingman Skree and Flockleader Geerin. She uses melee attacks with a max hit of 15 hitpoints.

name: Flockleader Geerin
examine: Flockleader Geerin is one of the Aviansie bodyguards of Kree'arra, along with Flight Kilisa and Wingman Skree. She uses Ranged attacks with a max hit of 25 hitpoints. When fighting Kree'arra, it is very unlikely Flockleader Geerin will do any damage at all, as most players use the Protect from Missiles prayer to defend from Kree'arra.

name: Flower
examine: Flowers are plants that surround the Hespori patch in the west-wing of the Farming Guild. During the fight the flowers will open up three times: at the beginning of the fight, after the Hespori reaches 66% of its health, and once again when it reaches 33% of its health. They have 10 hitpoints each and always die in one hit. The Hespori cannot be attacked while any of them are active, all of them must be subdued before the Hespori can be harmed.

name: Foreman
examine: The foreman looks after the Ship Yard on Karamja. He can be found walking around on the southern tip of the docks.

name: Forester
examine: Foresters can be found throughout the Woodcutting Guild. They can either be fought or spoken to by players.

name: Forgotten Soul
examine: Forgotten Souls are monsters found in the Crumbling Tower on the Isle of Souls. Their stats and drop table are similar to those of Chaos druids, although they have more hitpoints and are classified as ghosts, making them weak to the effects of the salve amulet.

name: Forgotten Soul (Soul Wars)
examine: Forgotten Souls are monsters found in the Soul Wars minigame. They are the only monsters that can be killed for Soul fragments.

name: Fortress Guard
examine: Fortress Guards are found only at the Black Knights' Fortress. They wear black cloaks and resemble generic town guards, and have various weapons such as swords, spears, and halberds which can hit different amounts at different speeds. The player must disguise themselves as one of these guards to get into the fortress during the Black Knights' Fortress quest. They are unaggressive unlike the Black Knights found near them.

name: Fox
examine: Foxes are attackable monsters found in the Fremennik Province and in Hosidius.

name: Fragment of Seren
examine: The Fragment of Seren was an entity whom Lord Iorwerth tried to summon to Gielinor and is fought as the final boss of the Song of the Elves quest. She was referred to as the Dark Lord by the Iorwerth Clan in order to trick King Lathas into believing they were summoning Zamorak, whom he worshipped in secret.

name: Freidir
examine: Freidir is a citizen of Rellekka located in a hut with Inga in the south-east part of Rellekka. His hut is located exactly north of Lanzig's hut. He also drops lyres which can be used in The Fremennik Trials, rather than having to make them with 25 Fletching. At level 45 Thieving and after The Fremennik Trials, this npc can be pickpocketed for 40 coins and 65 Thieving experience.

name: Frog
examine: Frogs can be found in the Lumbridge Swamp. They are the smallest and weakest type of frog. They were released with the permanent free-to-play update to help provide new combat training options for the large amounts of new players.

name: Frogeel
examine: A Frogeel is a hybrid of a Giant frog and a cave eel. Players can create frogeels in Creature Creation, in the basement dungeon of the Tower of Life building once they complete the Tower of Life quest.

name: Fumus
examine: Fumus is one of the four mages guarding Nex in the Ancient Prison, within the God Wars Dungeon. Having mastered smoke magic, he enhances Nex's powers over smoke. As with all of Nex's mages, he is immobile.

name: Gadderanks
examine: Gadderanks is a blood tithe collector involved in the In Aid of the Myreque quest. To protect his wife and son from the vampyres Gadderanks works for the vampyres, collecting blood tithes from the inhabitants of Morytania to sustain their vampyric overlords. In this capacity he is accompanied by two Vampyre Juvinates.

name: Galina
examine: Galina is one of the citizens of Canifis. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is more friendly if you are wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Galvek
examine: Galvek is the final boss of the Dragon Slayer II quest. He was a dragon incubated by the Dragonkin Zorgoth, who planned to use Galvek to destroy humanity after being imprisoned for ages because he was presumed to be a violent Dragonkin. Zorgoth gave it the name "Galvek" because it was the Dragonkin word for "Fate". Galvek is a special breed of dragon, as it is more serpent-like and has the ability to control other dragons.

name: Gang boss
examine: A Gang Boss is encountered in Great Kourend during the Shayzien Tackle organised crime activity, requiring 40% Shayzien favour to attack. They appear at select locations along with a group of 4-14 gangsters. They will despawn from all worlds 5 minutes after the time they were scheduled to appear.

name: Gangster
examine: Gangsters are encountered in Great Kourend during the Shayzien Tackle organised crime activity, requiring 40% Shayzien favour to attack. They appear at select locations in groups of 4-14 along with a Gang boss. They will despawn from all worlds 5 minutes after the time they were scheduled to appear - any gangsters that were in combat during this time will die and if you have inflicted any damage to them, you will receive the appropriate loot.

name: Gardener
examine: Gardeners are low level human non-player characters, often found in Falador Park. During the Pirate's Treasure quest, a level 4 gardener attacks the player when they use a spade to dig up the casket.

name: Gargoyle
examine: Gargoyles are Slayer monsters located in the Slayer Tower's top floor and basement, requiring 75 Slayer in order to be harmed. Those found in the basement are only available to players who are assigned gargoyles as their Slayer task. If they attempt to kill them off-task, Raulyn will prevent them from attacking.

name: Gelatinnoth Mother
examine: The Gelatinnoth Mother is a monster encountered during the final battles in the Recipe for Disaster quest. She is the equivalent to the Dagannoth mother from the Horror from the Deep quest, although Gelatinnoth Mother will switch colours after a certain amount of damage/hits is dealt. She will turn different colours every 15 to 20 seconds, not counting damage/hits dealt in the current colour, and her colour shows her weakness to a certain type of magic spell or attack.

name: General Danknuck
examine: General Danknuck was a high ranking goblin general who lead the final attempt on the invasion on Falador during the 2014 Goblin Invasion event. He could only be harmed with an event rpg, and had similar drops to Painted Goblins, albeit in higher quantities. He was removed from the game at the end of the event.

name: General Graardor
examine: General Graardor is the leader of Bandos' forces within the God Wars Dungeon. He is the only known living member of the Ourg race in Old School RuneScape.

name: General Khazard
examine: General Khazard, also known as Khazard, is the main antagonist of the Fight Arena quest. His followers believe that he is an undead maniac who died over 200 years ago, but he is in actuality a Zamorakian Mahjarrat. He has established a large territory between Ardougne and Yanille and is at war with the gnomes.

name: Georgy
examine: Georgy is a werewolf found in Canifis. If the player is not wielding a wolfbane dagger when they attack, Georgy will turn into a werewolf, much stronger than his human form. He is more friendly if the player wears a ring of charos. He cannot be killed as part of a werewolf Slayer task.

name: Ghast
examine: Ghasts are lingering souls of people that starved to death in Mort Myre swamp. When they first appear they are invisible and have no combat level, and try to turn food into useless rotten food; if players have no food they will do damage instead. Building the Fire of Dehumidification in the area stops these attacks (requires the completion of Making Friends with My Arm).

name: Ghost
examine: A ghost is an undead monster that is found in various places and dungeons. As they are undead, Crumble Undead and the salve amulet work well on them. Ghosts are rarely used for training, because they drop nothing in most locations.

name: Ghost (Grave of Scorpius)
examine: Several ghosts can be found near the Grave of Scorpius, where the Spirit of Scorpius can also be found. These ghosts can be talked to, even without wearing a ghostspeak amulet. Talking to them will cause them to attack the player, after telling them "We are waiting for you to join us.".

name: Ghost (Melzar's Maze)
examine: A room full of ghosts can be found on the 1st floor[UK]2nd floor[US] of Melzar's Maze. They must be killed in order to obtain the orange key, which can unlock the orange doors and progress through the maze.

name: Ghoul
examine: Ghouls are found just west of Canifis, north of the swamp and west of the fairy ring code CKS. Though they may appear to be undead, and are often mistaken for such, they are in fact still alive and thus immune to both the Crumble Undead spell and to the effects of the salve amulet and salve amulet (e). A ghoul bone is needed to complete the Rag and Bone Man II. Killing a ghoul is a requirement for the easy Morytania  Diary.

name: Ghoul Champion
examine: The Ghoul Champion can only be fought after receiving the ghoul champion scroll as part of the Champions' Challenge minigame.

name: Giant bat
examine: Giant Bats are relatively low-level flying monsters found at a number of locations in RuneScape. Despite them being generally weak monsters they may sometimes pose a threat to players due to their aggressiveness toward any players level 54 or lower. Giant bats can be used as a slightly higher-level alternative for regular Bats for Slayer assignments.

name: Giant Champion
examine: The Giant Champion can only be fought after receiving the giant champion scroll as part of the Champion's Challenge minigame.

name: Giant crypt rat
examine: Giant crypt rats are a stronger variant of giant rat that lurk in the Barrows tunnels. Giant crypt rats are one of the many obstacles between a player and the chest containing rewards where they constantly distract players from completing puzzles. As with all monsters in the crypts, they are aggressive to any player regardless of their Combat level.

name: Giant crypt spider
examine: Giant crypt spiders are a stronger variant of giant spider found in the tunnels of the Barrows. Giant crypt spiders are one of the many obstacles between a player and the chest containing rewards where they constantly distract players from completing puzzles. As with all monsters in the crypts, they are aggressive to any player regardless of their Combat level.

name: Giant frog
examine: Giant frogs are monsters found in the Lumbridge Swamp, the Lumbridge Swamp Caves and Dorgesh-Kaan South Dungeon. The level 99 variants are the toughest monster in the dungeon. They are found to the south of the cave system, just outside the entrance to Juna's Chasm of Tears.

name: Giant lobster
examine: Giant lobsters are encountered during the Slug Menace quest in Witchaven Dungeon. They are aggressive to all players, even to those more than twice their combat level. After the quest is complete, they can no longer be found in the dungeon.

name: Giant lobster (Ghosts Ahoy)
examine: The giant lobster is fought during Ghosts Ahoy in the wrecked pirate ship directly north of Alice's husband's farm, which is west of Port Phasmatys. It emerges from a chest which contains the Map scrap, when players attempt to open it. Once it has been defeated, the player can then search for the scrap.

name: Giant Mole
examine: The Giant Mole (Talpidae wysonian[1]) is a boss found in the Falador Mole Lair, just under Falador Park, alongside some baby moles. The Giant Mole's origin and creation are described as "a slight accident involving a bottle of Malignius-Mortifer's-Super-Ultra-Flora-Growth-Potion".[2]

name: Giant mosquito
examine: Giant mosquitoes are found on the island of Mos Le'Harmless, near the entrance to the Mos Le'Harmless Cave.

name: Giant rat
examine: Giant rats are common, low-levelled monsters. They can often be found in swamps and sewers, and are often killed by low-levelled players training their Combat skills as they are weak and can be easily found around Lumbridge and Varrock.

name: Giant Roc
examine: The Giant Roc is a large avian monster encountered during the quest My Arm's Big Adventure.

name: Giant Rock Crab
examine: Giant rock crabs are massive versions of the weaker Rock crab. They lie in wait for prey, disguised as large boulders. When approached, they attack, unless they have become tolerant, in which case they remain as "boulders" - attempting to cast a spell on them gives the message "You can't attack this NPC."

name: Giant rockslug
examine: The Giant rockslug is a superior variant of the rockslug. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Giant Scarab
examine: The Giant Scarab is fought during the final battle of the Contact! quest. It summons level 68 Locust riders and Scarab mages to aid it in battle. The scarab is the sixth-highest level quest only monster that is fought via conventional means in the game.

name: Giant Sea Snake
examine: The Giant Sea Snake is encountered at the end of the Royal Trouble quest. It is not as strong as its combat level suggests, but an antipoison potion, preferably super, is vital, as the snake is poisonous with damage that starts at 9. It fights with melee up close and ranged from a distance, but it cannot detect the use of prayers. Like its offspring, it is vulnerable to Magic. It drops the heavy box which is needed to finish the quest, and it can only be fought once.

name: Giant skeleton (Shadow Dungeon)
examine: Giant skeletons are a more powerful variant of skeleton found in the Shadow Dungeon, which can be accessed using a ring of visibility during or after the Desert Treasure quest. They are seldom killed due to their significantly higher combat stats than regular skeletons, being located in a multicombat area, as well as lacklustre drops. As with most monsters in the Shadow Dungeon, they allow other monsters to pass through them.

name: Giant skeleton (Tarn's Lair)
examine: Giant skeletons are a more powerful variant of skeleton found in Tarn's Lair. They are seldom killed due to their significantly higher combat stats than regular skeletons and dangerous location.

name: Giant snail
examine: A Giant snail is a monster found during Temple Trekking. They always drop snail shells or a perfect snail shell.

name: Giant spider
examine: Giant spiders are very large spiders most commonly seen around Lumbridge.

name: Glacies
examine: Glacies is one of the four mages guarding Nex in the Ancient Prison, within in the God Wars Dungeon. Having mastered ice magic, she enhances Nex's powers over ice. As with all of Nex's mages, she is immobile.

name: Glod
examine: Glod is a huge, muscular giant who can be found on the cloud at the top of the magic beanstalk in the Grim Tales quest. He has a Combat level of 138. Glod has the ability to bellow threats at players to either make them run in fear of the huge giant or charge at him in anger. He can also heal himself, similar to the gorillas on Ape Atoll, as well as boost his Attack and Strength, making him a bit harder to kill. When Glod is killed he drops the golden goblin which is a quest item needed for the Grim Tales quest.

name: Glough
examine: Glough (pronounced /glʌf/"GLUHF"[1]) is an ill-natured, misanthropic gnome who tries to take over Gielinor. In the Grand Tree quest, he can be found just south-east of the starting point of the Grand Tree; look for a ladder to the East of the ramp (between start of the quest and the agility course) that leads to Glough; take this ladder up to find Glough on the second floor.

name: Glowing crystal
examine: Glowing crystals are large clusters of crystals found in Vasa Nistirio's room in the Chambers of Xeric. These crystals were used by Xeric to bind the former High Priest after he attempted to usurp him, eternally imprisoning his avatar in the chambers.

name: Gnome
examine: Gnomes are a race of small humanoids found in various parts of Gielinor. They can be found primarily in the Gnome Empire, although they are most common in the Tree Gnome Village, Tree Gnome Stronghold, and Battlefield of Khazard. Gnomes fight with either ranged or melee attacks, depending on the weapon they wield. They have different coloured hoods.

name: Gnome Archer
examine: A Gnome Archer spawns once a level 92 Tortoise has been killed. It spawns along with a Gnome Driver and a Gnome Mage. The Gnome Driver will, most of the time, attack the player once it spawns, but its companions tend to ignore the player completely. The player will not receive experience for attacking this monster.

name: Gnome child
examine: Gnome children are young gnomes found in the Tree Gnome Stronghold. Like adult gnomes, they can be killed or pickpocketed. All of them use melee unlike their adult counterparts.

name: Gnome Driver
examine: A Gnome Driver spawns once a level 92 Tortoise has been killed. It spawns along with a Gnome Archer and a Gnome Mage. The Gnome Driver will mostly attack the player once it spawns, but its companions tend to ignore the player completely. The player will not receive experience for attacking a gnome driver.

name: Gnome guard
examine: Gnome guards are gnome warriors in and around the Tree Gnome Stronghold, including in the Grand Tree. They have either a halberd or a sword and shield equipped. They have relatively high Hitpoints for their level and their attacks aren't very accurate.

name: Gnome Mage
examine: A Gnome Mage spawns once a level 92 tortoise has been killed. It spawns along with a Gnome Driver and a Gnome Archer. The Gnome Driver will mostly attack the player once it spawns, but its companions tend to ignore the player completely. The player will not receive experience for attacking this monster. It shoots a blue projectile magic attack that makes a sound similar to ice spells.

name: Gnome troop
examine: Gnome troops are soldiers of the Gnome Army found on the Khazard Battlefield and within the Tree Gnome Stronghold. At Khazard Battlefield, they can be found swamping the Khazard troopers most of the time. When they are attacking or being attacked by Khazard troopers, they will say phrases such as "You will never get us without a fight!" and "Tally ho!"

name: Gnome woman
examine: Gnome women are female gnomes that may be found in the Gnome Stronghold. They may be pickpocketed with 75 Thieving; doing so yields 198.3 Thieving experience.

name: Goat
examine: A Goat is an animal found in the Kharidian Desert south of Al-Kharid. They drop horns used in Herblore to create Combat potions. The greatest amount of spawns are south-west of the Kalphite lair (accessible via fairy ring BIQ; however, the goats near Nardah are much closer to a bank.

name: Goblin
examine: Goblins are one of the most common, low-level monsters found around Gielinor. They are a very popular monster killed by low-level players training their combat skills.

name: Goblin (Goblin Village)
examine: The goblins of Goblin Village are a specific tribe of goblins which seem to be at war amongst themselves over which colour their armour should be. During the Goblin Diplomacy quest, the village leaders General Bentnoze and General Wartface temporarily settle their dispute over armour colour by choosing to wear brown goblin mail instead of the red or green armour, but as becomes evident directly after this quest, this settlement only lasts very shortly. This can also be seen by the continued infighting within the tribe.

name: Goblin (God Wars Dungeon)
examine: Goblins found in the God Wars Dungeon are troops for the Bandosian army, fighting against the other monsters inside the dungeon. While stronger than most goblins found elsewhere, they are still relatively weak followers of Bandos and often killed for kill count.

name: Goblin (historical)
examine: Goblins could originally be found in the Goblin Village and were encountered during the Goblin Diplomacy quest. Twice in 2005 and 2006, goblins were graphically updated and new versions were added. However, the original versions remained in the game cache.

name: Goblin (Vault of War)
examine: Goblins are some of the creatures that can be found in the Vault of War inside the Stronghold of Security, which is the first level of the stronghold. The fact this area in the stronghold is named after war makes this a very fitting location for goblins to be found, considering they are avid followers of Bandos, the god of war.

name: Goblin Champion
examine: The Goblin Champion can only be fought after receiving the goblin champion scroll as part of the Champions' Challenge minigame.

name: Goblin guard
examine: The Goblin guard (known as Sleeping guard before being woken up) is a level 42 goblin with 43 hitpoints, who is guarding the kitchen gate in the dungeon near the Observatory. During the Observatory Quest players must "prod" him to wake him up, he then attacks the player while saying "Oi, how dare you wake me up!". He can be fought after the quest is complete as he respawns in the same place.

name: Goblin lieutenant
examine: Goblin lieutenants were Monsters introduced in the 2013 Goblin Invasion event.

name: Goblin raider
examine: Goblin raiders were found during the 2013 Goblin Invasion event. The level 4 variant first appeared in the Varrock raids on 10 May 2013, and would spawn near the east, west, or south entrance to Varrock. When the Goblin Invasion event officially started on 2 August 2013, the level 30 variant was introduced and had improved drops. Starting from the following raids in Lumbridge, the level 50 variant was introduced.

name: Golem
examine: Golems are summoned by Zalcano while her stone armour is intact. They explode upon reaching Zalcano, recovering her stone armour's health by 50.

name: Gorad
examine: Gorad is an ogre who lives on an island north of Feldip Hills. He is killed during the Watchtower quest. He always drops two things: Big bones and the Ogre tooth required to get the second part of the Ogre relic. The Ogre tooth appears in your inventory and not on the ground so you must have an empty inventory space to receive it.

name: Gorak
examine: Goraks are typeless melee-using monsters encountered during the Fairytale II - Cure a Queen quest, where they are slain for their claws which are an ingredient for the Magic essence potion. They are found in the Gorak Plane (fairy ring DIR) and in the God Wars Dungeon.

name: Grave scorpion
examine: Grave scorpions are low-level monsters found by the Grave of Scorpius, south of West Ardougne. It is worth noting that their hitpoints are lower than standard scorpions, so they may be useful to kill if the player wants to finish a Slayer task of scorpions quickly.

name: Great Olm
examine: The Great Olm (referred to as the Guardian in the Deep by Xeric's followers) is the final boss in the Chambers of Xeric raid. A large, blind, white salamander, it is one of Xeric's greatest possessions.

name: Greater abyssal demon
examine: The Greater abyssal demon is a superior variant of the normal abyssal demon. It has a chance of spawning when an abyssal demon is killed if the player has purchased the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Greater demon
examine: Greater demons are large demonic monsters. They are well known for their rune full helm and hard clue scroll drops.

name: Greater demon (20th Anniversary event)
examine: Greater demons were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. They had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 29 August 2006.

name: Greater Nechryael
examine: Greater nechryael are stronger variants of nechryael that require level 80 Slayer to kill. They are found within the Catacombs of Kourend, Iorwerth Dungeon and the Wilderness Slayer Cave.

name: Greater Skeleton Hellhound
examine: The Greater Skeleton Hellhound is a monster summoned by Vet'ion. Two spawn during the second form of Vet'ion after half of his health has depleted and must be killed as he is immune to attacks while they are present.

name: Green dragon
examine: Green dragons are the weakest of the adult chromatic dragons in RuneScape. They are found in various locations within the Wilderness as well as in the Corsair Cove Dungeon. Green dragons are capable of breathing dragonfire, which can hit up to 50 damage on players who are not wielding an Anti-dragon shield or Dragonfire shield. Using one of these shields will partially block the dragonfire, and using one of these shields with an antifire potion will block the dragonfire completely.

name: Green Guard
examine: A green guard is a Falador Guard painted green. Players on the goblins' side during the 2014 Goblin Invasion event must paint the guards green with an event rpg in order to make them attackable. Players can also '360NoScope-Paint' Guard, but the chance of getting it painted is low.

name: Grey golem
examine: The Grey golem is encountered during the Spirits of the Elid quest. He guards the southernmost door in the River Elid cave and appears in front of the player, exclaiming "You may not pass!" and must be defeated using the Slash attack style. Other styles work, but deal significantly lower damage.

name: Grip
examine: Grip is the head guard of Scarface Pete, fought during the Heroes' Quest. He has the key you need to open the chest with the candlesticks during the thieves' armband section. He lives in Brimhaven and is found at Scarface Pete's Mansion.

name: Grizzly bear
examine: Grizzly bears are large but relatively weak monsters typically found in forests. They are the stronger, aggressive cousins of the non-aggressive black bear.

name: Grizzly bear cub
examine: A grizzly bear cub is a smaller version of a grizzly bear (level 42) in the forests of Isafdar. They are always found near larger grizzly bears.

name: Growler
examine: Growler is a bodyguard of Commander Zilyana, along with Starlight and Bree. It attacks using an accurate magic attack which has a max hit of 16.

name: Growthling
examine: Growthlings are monsters that appear during the fight with Bryophyta. She will occasionally summon growthlings to attack the player. Even though Bryophyta can continue summoning them throughout the fight, there can only be three growthlings present in her lair at any given time.

name: Guard
examine: There are many guards in Gielinor, usually in populated, major cities, such as Falador, Varrock, Ardougne, and others. Guards also patrol the area just south of the wilderness ditch at Edgeville.

name: Guard (Burthorpe)
examine: Guards (Burthorpe) are level 37 humans. A pair of Burthorpe guards flank either side of the main entrance to the Burthorpe Castle. They have average Defence and accuracy for their combat level and have a max hit of 5. Players occasionally train on these two guards for experience and their uncommon mithril platebody and mithril full helm drops.

name: Guard (Cave goblin)
examine: The cave goblin Guards keep order in Dorgesh-Kaan. When spoken to they will sometimes tease the player. If the player fails to pickpocket a cave goblin in the vicinity of cave goblin guards, they may shout "Stop that!" and attack the player.

name: Guard (Deadman Mode)
examine: There are unique level 1337 guards in Deadman Mode who are able to hit up to 30 with a very high accuracy (melee and Ice Barrage). They are capable of Tele Blocking and negating Prayer completely. These guards will kill anyone who enters a safe zone with a PK skull instantly. Getting killed by these guards will lead to a 10 percent loss of experience in protected skills, in addition to the regular penalties.

name: Guard (Desert Mining Camp)
examine: Guards are found throughout the Desert Mining Camp, patrolling the inner camp and the underground mines.

name: Guard (dwarf)
examine: Dwarven guards are found at the main entrance of the Dwarven Mine, south of the Ice Mountain, along with dwarves and Black Guards. They are also found guarding and engaging in combat with nearby goblins if they get too close to the Coal Trucks area.

name: Guard (H.A.M. storeroom)
examine: Several H.A.M. guards are found in the lower level storeroom of the H.A.M. Hideout through a hidden trapdoor during Death to the Dorgeshuun. Zanik will knock out the guards using a crossbow as the room is traversed. After listening in on the secret meeting a guard will appear, and you will be knocked out and transported to the H.A.M. jail cell.

name: Guard (Hosidius)
examine: Hosidius guards can be found around Hosidius, in Great Kourend. In most ways, they act like common guards, sharing the same drops and being pickpocketable at level 40 Thieving for the same 30 coins and 46.5 Thieving experience. However, unlike regular guards, some Hosidius guards are equipped with bows, and thus attack with range.

name: Guard (Prifddinas)
examine: Prifddinas guards are notable for being the highest combat (and thus strongest) guard of any city in Gielinor. These can be killed when assigned elf tasks. Generally, slaying Prifddinas Guards may be favourable over Elf Warriors and Elf Archers found in Lletya due to them being weak to stab, magic and ranged as opposed to the Elf Warriors which are only weak to magic, or the Elf Archers which are only weak to melee and magic. Additionally, less time is spent running when slaying Prifddinas Guards as pairs of guards are stationed close together - and wander a small open space - at each of the four main Prifddinas entrances. Prifddinas Guards respawn after 18 seconds, making these spots efficient alternatives to slaying Lletya elves.

name: Guard (Ranging Guild)
examine: Guards may be found wandering in the Ranging Guild. They welcome the player to the Ranging Guild.

name: Guard (Shayzien)
examine: Kourend guards are Shayzien soldiers located around the kingdom of Kourend. They have identical stats and drops to regular guards. Players with 40 Thieving can pickpocket them.

name: Guard (unused)
examine: The Guard was an unused variant of the Varrock Guards who used a crossbow. Presumably, he would have been located on Varrock's western wall or one of the guard towers, but was ultimately not added for unknown reasons.

name: Guard Bandit
examine: Guard Bandits can be found at the entrance to the Wilderness Bandit Camp. If the player tries to enter the camp, the guards will exclaim "You shall not pass!" and attack the player. Like most Wilderness monsters, Guard Bandits are aggressive to players of all levels. Guard Bandits usually only drop bones, as opposed to the other bandits that reside in the camp.

name: Guard dog
examine: Guard dogs are animals that can be found in various man-made locations. For lower-level players, guard dogs can be tough to defeat with melee, due to their fairly high melee accuracy. They can be slain towards a dog Slayer task, but Jackals may be much easier.

name: Guard dog (Construction)
examine: A guard dog can be built in the Guard space of the Oubliette and Dungeon in a player-owned house. It requires 74 Construction to build and when built, it gives 273 experience.

name: Guardian (Chambers of Xeric)
examine: Guardians are statues which appear in groups of two as a combat encounter in the Chambers of Xeric. These statues must be destroyed in order to pass the room and can only be harmed with pickaxes; all other sources of damage will not count. The dragon warhammer's special attack applies before the attack's damage roll is reduced to zero.[2] Damage done to the guardians is multiplied by a factor as shown in fig.1.[3] The formula is capped to ensure the Crystal pickaxe deals the same damage as the Dragon pickaxe, despite having a higher mining level requirement.[4] Attempting to enter the passage they are guarding will result in the guardian knocking the player back for moderate damage.

name: Guardian Drake
examine: The Guardian Drake is a superior variant of the drake. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Guardian of Armadyl
examine: The Guardians of Armadyl are found in the Temple of Ikov, they are members of an ancient order, tasked with protecting the legendary Staff of Armadyl. If players wish to claim the Staff for Lucien, they must defeat all of the guardians in the room. Players can also talk to or kill a guardian to obtain an Armadyl pendant if they lose theirs.

name: Gunthor the brave
examine: Gunthor the Brave is a barbarian who lives in Barbarian Village. He is located in the Long Hall in the northern part of the village. Gunthor is the highest level barbarian in Barbarian Village. He is stated to be a mighty warrior and a chieftain of the barbarians.

name: Guthan the Infested
examine: Guthan the Infested is the third oldest of the six Barrows brothers. Guthan's crypt is located at the south-east of the Barrows area. He uses melee equipment, which make him vulnerable to Magic attacks. Guthan's set effect is Infestation, which gives him a 25% chance per successful hit to heal him for whatever damage is dealt for that hit.

name: H.A.M. Archer
examine: The H.A.M. Archer is only fought during the Another Slice of H.A.M..

name: H.A.M. Guard
examine: H.A.M. Guards are found in the H.A.M. Hideout, patrolling the entire cave, guarding the Humans Against Monsters' members.

name: H.A.M. Mage
examine: The H.A.M. Mage is only fought during the Another Slice of H.A.M..

name: Halla (Miscellania)
examine: Halla is a citizen of Miscellania, found in her house in the snowy area west of the castle, near Derrik's house. After Throne of Miscellania, killing her will lower a player's approval rating by 5%.

name: Harpie Bug Swarm
examine: Harpie bug swarms are mid-level slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 33 to kill. A lit bug lantern, which requires a Firemaking level of 33 to light is required to damage these monsters (the lantern must be lit and equipped). If you do not have 33 Firemaking, you cannot be assigned harpie bug swarms as a Slayer task.[1]

name: Hazeel Cultist
examine: Hazeel Cultists are followers of the Zamorakian Mahjarrat, Hazeel, located in the southern Ardougne Sewers. Accessing their location requires starting the Hazeel Cult quest and correctly turning the five sewer valves outside. The cultists are eager to resurrect their lord, which the player helps with or refuses.

name: Head (Temple Trekking)
examine: The Head of a swamp creature is fought on a boat ride during the Temple Trekking minigame. It is located in a multi-combat zone with four tentacles. The parts attack only with melee, so Protect from Melee is recommended.

name: Head Guard
examine: Head Guards are elite versions of the Shayzien guards and are found around the kingdom of Kourend. They wield a dragon longsword along with a dragon sq shield, and wear Shayzien armour.

name: Head Menaphite Guard
examine: Head Menaphite Guard is fought during Beneath Cursed Sands. Players should not use protection prayers, as he will shout "Your false gods will not protect you!" and damage them for 1/3rd of their current hitpoints.

name: Head Thief
examine: The Head Thief is the leader of a small band of thieves that operate in the Kandarin area, just south of Ardougne. The thief and his group are involved in the Monk's Friend quest, where it is revealed that they have stolen a Child's blanket from one of the monks' sons. When infiltrating the thieves' lair to retrieve the blanket, the Head Thief will appear and attack, though you do not need to fight him to complete the quest.

name: Headless Beast
examine: The Headless Beast is a headless undead bear encountered during the Getting Ahead quest, it was resurrected by the inexperienced necromancer Neilan Redmark. The Headless Beast attacks mainly with melee. It has a special attack where it slams the ground, causing a rock to fall from the ceiling onto the player's current location, dealing 12-16 damage. This can easily be avoided simply by moving one tile away in any direction. Immune to movement inhibitors from ice spells, bind, snare, and entangle.

name: Hellhound
examine: Hellhounds are mid-to-high level monsters that are often given as a Slayer task to mid-to-high level players. Hellhounds are an excellent source of hard clue scrolls, as they drop them more frequently than other monsters. If players are on a Hellhound Task and they want to make some money off it, they could choose to kill Vet'ion as his Skeleton Hellhound and Greater Skeleton Hellhound spawns will count towards the task and the player may also receive some generous drops from the boss. Killing Cerberus will also count towards a Hellhounds Task. Note that none of Revenant hellhounds, Bouncer, Bouncer's ghost, or the Skeleton Hellhound from In Search of the Myreque can be killed for a Hellhound slayer task.

name: Hellhound (Construction)
examine: A hellhound can be built in the Guard space of the Oubliette and Dungeon in a player-owned house. It requires 94 Construction to build and when built, it gives 2,236 experience.

name: Hengel
examine: Hengel is found upstairs in the house north of Hetty's house in Rimmington, along with his wife Anja. A player can ask him for "free stuff", to which Hengel quickly refuses, asking the player to leave. He can also be pickpocketed for 3 coins.

name: Hero
examine: Heroes are NPCs that walk around East Ardougne wearing what appears to be a Rune platebody and platelegs, but different coloured at places. They also have leather gloves, boots and wield a rune longsword and square shield. Heroes can be pickpocketed by players with level 80 or greater Thieving, which gives 273.3 experience plus coins or other items. Pickpocketing a Hero is a requirement for the Elite Ardougne Diary.

name: Hespori
examine: The Hespori is a sporadic boss. In order to fight it, players must first plant a Hespori seed in the Hespori patch within the west wing of the Farming Guild, which requires level 65 Farming to access (boostable) and 60% Hosidius favour. It takes 22-32 hours to grow, depending on when it was planted. When fully grown, the flower behind the cave entrance will sprout open.

name: Hespori (A Night at the Theatre)
examine: The Hespori is a boss from the quest A Night at the Theatre. It is a harder version of the hespori that can be fought in the Farming guild, and is a hespori in its natural habitat of Morytania.

name: Highwayman
examine: Highwaymen are a level five NPC which are aggressive towards players below a combat level of ten. One will always exclaim "Stand and deliver!" when it targets a player. Players below level ten are advised to quickly run past when encountering them.

name: Hill Giant
examine: A Hill Giant is a type of giant found in several locations around RuneScape, most highly concentrated in the far southern end of the Edgeville Dungeon. These dungeons may be accessed through the entrance located in the house north-east of Barbarian Village and west of the Cooks' Guild if the player has a Brass key. The Edgeville Dungeon area is usually very crowded in free-to-play worlds, as players like to gather Big bones to bury them for Prayer experience. Another free-to-play hill giants area was added near Al-Kharid (located east of the Al-Kharid General Store and Louie's Armoured Legs Bazaar., east past the gap in the gate, then up the Desert Plateau).

name: Hill Giant (Dark)
examine: The Hill Giants found in the Catacombs of Kourend and Giants' Den are a variation of the standard hill giant, with pale skin and dark clothing. Apart from aesthetics they have identical stats, and a largely similar drop table.

name: Hill Giant (Desert Plateau)
examine: Hill Giants of the Desert Plateau are a variation of the standard hill giant, where a small tribe of them can be found south-west of the Citharede Abbey. One lone hill giant wielding a hammer can be found directly south of the anvil on the plateau, who cannot be attacked with melee as he is out of reach.

name: Hobgoblin
examine: Hobgoblins are low-to-medium levelled monsters which hit fairly accurately for their combat level. They come in two variations outside of the God Wars Dungeon, with the level 28 variant usually unarmed and the level 42 variant wielding a spear, although some level 28 hobgoblins found north-east of the Vinery in Hosidius wield spears too. The narrow strip of land alongside the peninsula west of the Crafting Guild, and Tree Gnome Village dungeon (requires a key), contain many level 28 hobgoblins with no level 42 variants present.

name: Hobgoblin Champion
examine: The Hobgoblin Champion can only be fought after receiving the hobgoblin champion scroll as part of the Champions' Challenge minigame.

name: Hobgoblin guard
examine: The hobgoblin can be built in the Guard space of the Oubliette and Dungeon in a player-owned house. It requires 78 Construction to build and when built, it gives 316 experience.

name: Holthion
examine: Holthion is a demon encountered during the Underground Pass quest. When killed, it drops the amulet of holthion, which is needed to obtain Iban's shadow. Protect from Melee should be used during this part of the quest to save hitpoints for coping with its attacks.

name: Hoop Snake
examine: Hoop Snakes are monsters that live in the Tar Swamp area of Fossil Island.

name: Hopeless creature
examine: Hopeless creatures are monsters encountered during A Soul's Bane, in the Dungeon of Tolna. A player must kill all 5 of the hopeless creatures in order for the Bridge of Hope to appear. Each monster must be slain a total of 3 times before they will truly die. Each time a form is killed, they will retreat from the player and shrink in size. It should be noted that every time a player eats, 75% of the monster's current health is restored. These monsters attack with ranged during the quest in their first form, and use melee to attack in their second and third form. When poisoned, hopeless creatures do not carry the poison on to their next forms.

name: Huge spider
examine: The huge spider can be built in the Guard space of the Oubliette and Dungeon in a player-owned house. It requires 86 Construction to build and when built, it gives 447 experience.

name: Husk
examine: Husks are summoned during the fight with The Nightmare. They have low health and use rather inaccurate attacks; the skinny husk uses magic attacks, while the bulky husk uses ranged attacks.

name: Husk (Phosani's Nightmare)
examine: Husks are summoned during the fight with Phosani's Nightmare. Though they have low health, their attacks are accurate and hit much harder than their Nightmare counterparts.

name: Hydra
examine: Hydras are draconic creatures found in the lower level of the Karuulm Slayer Dungeon in Mount Karuulm, requiring level 95 Slayer to kill. They were created by a Dragonkin named Karuulm as a project which is not based on any prior work done by his fellow kin.

name: Hygd
examine: Hygd is a citizen of Burthorpe. She tells the player a little of what is going on in the town.

name: Ice demon
examine: The ice demon is one of the bosses encountered in the Chambers of Xeric.

name: Ice giant
examine: Ice giants are tall, light blue creatures that appear at certain icy areas of the game. Ice giants have two separate variants where they appear to be holding different weapons; a longsword or a warhammer. These monsters can be commonly assigned by the Slayer master Vannaka.

name: Ice Queen
examine: The Ice Queen is a quest NPC fought during the Heroes' Quest. She can be found in her lair beneath White Wolf Mountain.

name: Ice spider
examine: Ice spiders are one of the stronger species of spider. They are seldom killed due to having no drops except for a Wilderness Slayer task.

name: Ice troll
examine: Ice trolls (also styled as Ice Trolls) are level 120-124 monsters encountered during Desert Treasure when the player is trying to get the Ice diamond. Five trolls have to be killed to gain access to the ice cave on the eastern side. They are also encountered during Troll Romance where the player has to navigate through the cave leading to Trollweiss Mountain.

name: Ice troll female
examine: Ice troll females are most commonly found near the smaller ice troll runts. They use powerful Ranged attacks that hit hard and fast. The damage dealt by these females can be reduced by equipping a Neitiznot shield made during The Fremennik Isles. However, the shield doesn't affect the accuracy of the attacks. Their accuracy seem to neglect all defence bonuses from stats and equipment; hence, they almost always are able to deal some damage. Despite possessing melee stats, ice troll females do not make use of it.

name: Ice troll grunt
examine: Ice troll grunts are the foot soldiers of the Ice Troll King on the nothernmost isles of Jatizso and Neitiznot. They can occasionally hit hard through armour although Protect from Melee prevents all damage. The island immediately north of Neitiznot can be an effective training area if one uses the Honour guards that are always fighting the trolls to assist them.

name: Ice Troll King
examine: The Ice Troll King is the boss monster for The Fremennik Isles quest, and is the leader of the ice trolls. He is located on the northern part of the isles in his lair. He uses all three Combat styles, which includes a Melee attack, a Magic attack that freezes players, and a Ranged in which he will throw rocks at players and a special move, which will send players flying across the battleground.

name: Ice troll male
examine: Ice troll males inhabit the islands north of Jatizso and Neitiznot. They use melee attacks that hit a maximum of 20 hit points.

name: Ice troll runt
examine: Ice troll runts are the lowest levels of Ice trolls found on Jatizso and Neitiznot. Despite possessing only a slightly higher combat level than Mountain trolls, they can hit much harder (up to 17) and are much more aggressive, often attempting to engage the player from several squares away. They also have the ability to hit through armour, similar to Verac the Defiled. Yak-hide armour does not reduce the troll's maximum hit. It is advised to use the Protect from Melee prayer whenever engaging more than one at a time. Ice troll runts are often found near Ice troll females; when they're not, they will be spread farther out.

name: Ice warrior
examine: Ice warriors are mid-level elemental warriors. Ice warriors can be formidable foes to those with low levels. Ice warriors can also be assigned by Krystilia for a Wilderness Slayer task.

name: Ice wolf
examine: Ice wolves are level 96 or level 132 enemies that are encountered on the Ice Path during Desert Treasure. They are also found on the top of Trollweiss Mountain, at the Settlement Ruins, near the entrance of God Wars Dungeon and Weiss (inside a fence, these level 132 ice wolves can be killed by range or magic attacks only). They are dangerous, as they can hit 10's and 16's respectively, and are in a multicombat area. While following this path, it is highly recommended that you use Protect from Melee. These can be killed in place of normal wolves for more Slayer experience.

name: Icefiend
examine: Icefiends are found on top of the Ice Mountain, near the Dwarven Mine in member worlds. They are also found in the Zamorakian region of the God Wars Dungeon. Killing an icefiend is one of the three options to cool down the Dwarven rock cake in Recipe for Disaster, the other ones being with ice gloves. You can alternatively wait four hours for the Dwarven rock cake to cool in your bank. Icefiends can also be received as a Slayer task.

name: Icelord
examine: The Icelords are icy beings that live inside the Iceberg, and were found when Pescaling Pax moved much of the Penguin population to the Iceberg to prepare for the invasion of Gielinor. They have four arms, and are quite adept in using these to pummel their enemies into submission, while some prefer to hurl large icicles at adventurers. Pescaling Pax intends to use these as a strike force when they do invade the mainland.

name: Imp
examine: Imps are amongst the smallest creatures in Gielinor. They are central in the Imp Catcher quest due to their unique bead drops. Sometimes, an imp may disappear into a puff of smoke and teleport a short distance away. At level 71 Hunter players may catch imps with magic boxes, including imps found in the God Wars Dungeons.

name: Imp (unused)
examine: Level 3 Imps are unused non-player characters that previously appeared in the Imp Catcher quest. Originally, Wizard Grayzag had a combat level of 41 and could be fought by the player, during which he would summon stronger variants of Imps. In 2006, the quest was reworked; from now on players could only talk to Grayzag instead of fighting him. Therefore, the stronger imps could no longer be encountered in game, although they remained in the game files and were graphically updated several months later.

name: Imp Champion
examine: The Imp Champion can only be fought after receiving the imp champion scroll as part of the Champion's Challenge minigame. Like regular imps, it can teleport small distances, although it will not teleport outside of the arena.

name: Imre
examine: Imre is one of the citizens of Canifis. He can be found in the Hair of the Dog pub. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack, he will turn into a werewolf. He is more friendly if you are wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Infernal Mage
examine: Infernal Mages are slayer monsters that require 45 Slayer to kill. They are sometimes hunted for their frequent drops of death runes and their rare dark mystic boots and hat drops. Players who plan on fighting them should be wary of their accurate magic attack.

name: Infernal pyrelord
examine: The Infernal pyrelord is a superior version of pyrelords. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Insatiable Bloodveld
examine: The Insatiable Bloodveld is a superior variant of the bloodveld. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master. Bloodvelds slain in God Wars Dungeon will not have a chance of spawning their superior variant.[1]

name: Insatiable mutated Bloodveld
examine: The Insatiable mutated Bloodveld is a superior version of Mutated Bloodvelds. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Invrigar the Necromancer
examine: Invrigar is a necromancer found on the top floor of the Necromancer Tower. He will use magic to attack the player and will sometimes summon a level 13 Summoned Zombie to fight with him.

name: Iorwerth Archer
examine: Iorwerth Archers can be found in the Iorwerth Camp just south-west of Prifddinas. They are featured heavily during the Regicide quest. Players who have completed Regicide can receive them as a Slayer task.[1]

name: Iorwerth Warrior
examine: Iorwerth Warriors can be found in the Iorwerth Camp just south-west of Prifddinas. They are featured heavily during the Regicide quest. Players who have completed Regicide can receive them as a Slayer task.[1]

name: Irina
examine: Irina is one of the citizens of Canifis. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is more friendly if you are wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Iron dragon
examine: Iron dragons are one of the six types of metal dragons. Although they are the second weakest of the six, it is especially dangerous to kill them, as with all metal dragons, due to their ability to shoot long-range dragonfire. A dragonfire shield, or an anti-dragon shield, coupled with an antifire potion is necessary for full dragonfire protection. Having only one form of protection will result in some dragonfire damage being inflicted onto the player. Using an anti-dragon shield and the Protect from Magic prayer will not fully protect the player. A super antifire potion or extended equivalent provides complete protection from dragonfire without the need for prayer or shield.

name: Irvig Senay
examine: Irvig Senay is required to be killed to collect a piece of the heart crystal for the Legends' Quest. He attacks with melee (more specifically, slash) and can only be killed once, twice if players choose the "short" route in the quest. He is the middle level of the three warriors (the other two being San Tojalon and Ranalph Devere) that have sought after the pure water source of the Kharazi Jungle spring.

name: Ithoi the Navigator
examine: Ithoi the Navigator is Captain Tock's second-in-command, and one of the crew members who have moored in Corsair Cove after supposedly being cursed.

name: Jackal
examine: Jackals are a species of small, dog-like creatures native to the Kharidian Desert. Jackals are commonly found in the desert's lower reaches, near the cities of Nardah and Sophanem.

name: Jail guard
examine: Jail guards are aggressive bandits found around the Draynor Village jail. They are level 26 and can be dangerous to low level players, especially in numbers, as they are able to wander quite far from the jail and may pursue players on the nearby road or partially into the village. They are equipped with a steel mace, leather body and leather gloves.

name: Jailer
examine: The jailer is found in the Black Knights' Base in Taverley Dungeon. He guards the jail holding Velrak the explorer, who has the dusty key, required to access the deeper parts of the dungeon. Players who are navigating the dungeon for the first time must kill the jailer to obtain the jail key, which can be used to unlock Velrak's cell. The jailer can be safespotted using Ranged or Magic by standing behind the table at the eastern end of the hallway.

name: Jake
examine: Jake is a pirate that can be found on Pirates' Cove. He may be part of the crew of the Lady Zay, but his purpose is unknown.

name: Jal-Ak
examine: Jal-Ak is a monster fought in the Inferno. Jal-Ak is similar to the Tz-Kek fought in the TzHaar Fight Cave. Jal-Ak, however, is much more powerful.

name: Jal-AkRek-Ket
examine: Jal-AkRek-Ket is a monster encountered in the Inferno. It appears when a Jal-Ak has been killed, alongside a Jal-AkRek-Mej and Jal-AkRek-Xil.

name: Jal-AkRek-Mej
examine: Jal-AkRek-Mej is a monster encountered in the Inferno. It appears when a Jal-Ak has been killed, alongside a Jal-AkRek-Xil and Jal-AkRek-Ket.

name: Jal-AkRek-Xil
examine: Jal-AkRek-Xil is a monster encountered in the Inferno. It appears when a Jal-Ak has been killed, alongside a Jal-AkRek-Mej and Jal-AkRek-Ket.

name: Jal-ImKot
examine: Jal-ImKot is one of the monsters found in the Inferno.

name: Jal-MejJak
