examine: Jal-MejJak appears in the Inferno when TzKal-Zuk is at 20% health. They will rapidly heal TzKal-Zuk unless the player attacks them. Doing so causes them to stop healing TzKal-Zuk and start raining lava balls on the ground in front of them, similar to the effect at the Chaos Temple. Each lava ball does 5-10 damage. This damage can potentially be dodged, but doing so risks being hit by TzKal-Zuk, who can kill the player instantly. Thus, the preferred method is to kill them quickly with ranged or magic, while eating through the damage.

name: Jal-MejRah
examine: Jal-MejRah is a monster that is encountered in the Inferno. It is apparently the ancestor of the Tz-Kih.

name: Jal-Nib
examine: Jal-Nib, often colloquially referred to as nibbler, is one of the monsters which can be found in the Inferno. Several of these creatures spawn per wave and can cause damage to three pillars found within the arena. Once a pillar is damaged enough, it will fall.

name: Jal-Xil
examine: Jal-Xil are monsters fought in the Inferno, and are apparently the ancestors of the present day Tok-Xil.

name: Jal-Zek
examine: Jal-Zek are the Inferno's variant of the Fight Cave's Ket-Zek. They attack with powerful Magic and Melee attacks, and are the third strongest monster in the Inferno.

name: JalTok-Jad
examine: JalTok-Jad is one of the monsters which can be found in the Inferno. It is a stronger version of TzTok-Jad, and similarly attacks in all three forms of combat where the player must use the appropriate protection prayers before the attack hits.

name: Jeff
examine: Jeff is a strange fellow that can be thieved as well as attacked. He gives the same amount of coins as well as similar drops and Thieving experience as a man/woman. He hangs out with Narf, Cuffs, and Rusty.

name: Jelly
examine: Jellies are Slayer monsters found in the Fremennik Slayer Dungeon that require a Slayer level of 52 to kill. They give 75 Slayer experience per kill and drop hard clue scrolls and steel weaponry.

name: Jennella
examine: Jennella is a resident of Rellekka. She lives in a house just west of the main entrance. She also drops lyres which can be used in The Fremennik Trials, rather than having to make them with 25 Fletching. At level 45 Thieving and after The Fremennik Trials, she can be pickpocketed for 40 coins and 65 Thieving experience.

name: Jogre
examine: Jogres are a type of ogre that live in the jungles of Karamja. They are large and powerful, but their attacks are slow and they have low defence, allowing them to be killed quickly. They are a threat to lower levels exploring Karamja due to their high damage hits, but they are not aggressive to players who have a combat level of at least 107.

name: Jogre Champion
examine: The Jogre Champion can only be fought after receiving the jogre champion scroll as part of the Champions' Challenge minigame.

name: Jonny the beard
examine: Jonny the beard is a thug, who appears in the Blue Moon Inn in southern Varrock. He is a Black Arm Gang member who is required to be killed (and a scroll picked up and given to Straven, the Phoenix Gang leader) for joining the Phoenix Gang in the Shield of Arrav quest.

name: Joseph
examine: Joseph, like most of the Canifis inhabitants, is not very friendly, however his attitude will change if the player is wearing a Ring of Charos. Also, he will transform into a level 88 Werewolf if he gets attacked. This can be prevented by using a Wolfbane dagger. He cannot be killed as part of a werewolf Slayer task.

name: Jubbly bird
examine: A jubbly is a bird found during the Skrach Uglologwee subquest of the Recipe for Disaster quest. They appear to be a big, purplish version of a normal Chompy. They can be hunted and killed by using ogre bellows on an already bloated toad with a rock from one of the mineable rocks in the area and a ball of wool. Combining the wool and the toad creates a balloon toad which is used as bait.

name: Jubster
examine: A jubster is a hybrid of a lobster and a jubbly bird. Players can create jubsters in Creature Creation, in the basement dungeon of the Tower of Life once they complete the Tower of Life quest.

name: Judge of Yama
examine: The Judge of Yama is a demon encountered during the A Kingdom Divided quest. It is summoned by Sophia Hughes in an attempt to dispose of the player and Commander Fullore, but it killed Sophia as she had betrayed the trust of Yama, her master.

name: Jungle Demon
examine: The Jungle demon is a quest monster fought during the Monkey Madness I quest. It is among the strongest demons in the game. It uses extremely strong magic attacks and, when in range, a halberd-like melee attack. It is possible to let the gnomes around it take it to about 10 hitpoints, while you are hiding across the bridge at the edge of the arena. Afterwards, you can run out to quickly finish it off. However, if the gnomes "kill" the demon, it will restore 20% of its hitpoints, so you cannot fully rely on the 10th Squad to kill it.

name: Jungle horror
examine: Jungle horrors are monsters that live on the island of Mos Le'Harmless. Players must have completed Cabin Fever to gain access to the island. They can be assigned as a Slayer task by Chaeldar and Vannaka. They are a weaker relative of the cave horrors that live inside the caves on the island. A Witchwood Icon is NOT required to kill Jungle Horrors.

name: Jungle savage
examine: Jungle savages are warriors from the Kharazi Jungle similar to the tribesmen located in various other places around Karamja.

name: Jungle spider
examine: Jungle spiders are monsters that can be found on Karamja and the archipelago east of Yanille. They are not displayed on the minimap so they can be a threat to low level players who don't notice them. Jungle spiders appear in the Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup minigame.

name: Jungle spider (Ape Atoll)
examine: Jungle spiders are monsters that can be found on Ape Atoll. Unlike common jungle spiders, they do not drop spider carcasses and are poisonous. Their attacks will almost always inflict poison (1 damage) on the player similar to Cave slime.

name: Jungle Wolf
examine: Jungle wolves are an uncommon type of wolf found in the Kharazi Jungle. They only drop wolf bones when killed. If you get wolves as a Slayer assignment, you can slay these for the task. They are aggressive to all players and will start pursuing from a distance. They are similar to regular wolves, but the main differences are their colour and location.

name: Justiciar Zachariah
examine: Justiciar Zachariah is a Saradominist Justiciar who roams the Wilderness hunting the demon Porazdir. During Mage Arena II miniquest, he has to be defeated in order to obtain his hand for Kolodion's spell. In order to summon him, players have to use an enchanted symbol to locate him, similar to using an enchanted key or strange device.

name: K'ril Tsutsaroth
examine: K'ril Tsutsaroth (pronounced "KRILL TUTT-zee-roth"[1]) is the boss of the Zamorak Fortress in the God Wars Dungeon. To gain access to his chamber, players must have slain 40 Zamorakians throughout the dungeon. He uses melee and magic attacks, and his special attack can occasionally hit through the Protect from Melee prayer should players attempt to use it.

name: Kalphite Guardian
examine: Kalphite Guardians can be found in the Kalphite Lair - deep beneath the Kharidian Desert, which is located south-west of the Shantay Pass, Al Kharid. An alternative route upon completion of Death to the Dorgeshuun, lies south of Dorgesh-Kaan, beyond the Dorgesh-Kaan Agility Course. They can also be found in the Kalphite Cave; a Slayer task is required to kill them there.

name: Kalphite Queen
examine:
The Kalphite Queen (Kalphiscarabeinae pasha), also called the KQ, is the strongest of the Kalphites. The Kalphite Queen, along with dust devils and smoke devils, is notable for dropping the Dragon chainbody.
The Kalphite Queen can inflict large amounts of damage with her Ranged and Magic attacks as they always result in a successful hit. It is recommended for players to bring an emergency teleport such as an Ectophial, royal seed pod or teleport tablet, or only bring items into the lair for which they are willing to pay the gravestone fees.

name: Kalphite Soldier
examine: Kalphite soldiers can be found in the Kalphite Lair south-west of Shantay Pass and in the Kalphite Cave east of the Shantay Pass, although the latter requires having a Slayer task to kill. They guard the entrance to the lair of the Kalphite Queen. These are highly dangerous because of their ability to poison starting at 4 damage without dealing melee damage, and they inhabit a multi-combat area.

name: Kalphite soldier (Construction)
examine: A kalphite soldier can be built in the Monster space of the Treasure Room in a player-owned house. It requires 80 Construction to build and when built, it gives 866 experience.

name: Kalphite Worker
examine: Kalphite workers are worker drones that serve the Kalphite Queen. They are found throughout the Kalphite Lair and Kalphite Cave west and east of the Shantay Pass, respectively. They cannot poison, unlike the majority of Kalphites.

name: Kalrag
examine: Kalrag is a giant spider encountered during Underground Pass and only needs to be fought during the quest. It must be slain in order to soak a player's doll of Iban with Iban's blood, thus progressing the quest. Although players were able to kill it after the quest, this is no longer possible due to an update as the spider will no longer spawn upon progressing Iban's doll.

name: Kamil
examine: (Not to be confused with Karil, one of the Barrows Brothers)

name: Karamel
examine: Karamel is fought during the Recipe for Disaster quest. She is the counterpart of Kamil (from Desert Treasure) and is very similar to the original.

name: Karil the Tainted
examine: Karil the Tainted is the fourth oldest of the Barrows brothers. Karil's crypt is located to the south of the Barrows area. He uses ranged equipment, which make him vulnerable to Melee attacks. Also unlike a player using his equipment, he is also fairly weak to Magic attacks. Karil's set effect is Tainted Shot, which gives him a 25% chance per successful hit to lower the player's Agility by 20%.

name: Kebbit
examine: The kebbit is a level 13 monster encountered in the Eagles' Peak Dungeon during the Eagles' Peak quest, and can only be fought once. It is the only attackable kebbit in the game.

name: Keef
examine: Keef is the head of the city guards in Gu'Tanoth, found near the other city guards past all the bridges (where you solved the riddle a guard gave you in the Watchtower Quest; you may need to bring 20 coins to pass the bridge again). He is fought during Monkey Madness II in order to convince him not to ally with the monkeys of Ape Atoll.

name: Ket-Zek
examine: The Ket-Zek is a monster found in the TzHaar Fight Cave. They begin appearing at wave 31.

name: Khazard commander
examine: The Khazard commander can be found in the Battlefield of Khazard (located south of West Ardougne). He is encountered during the Tree Gnome Village quest. To be able to get to him, players must have fired the ballista during the Tree Gnome Village quest. By firing the ballista, it will break the stronghold allowing the player to climb over the wall to attack him. The commander can not be attacked from outside of the stronghold, even with ranged or magic.

name: Khazard Guard
examine: Khazard Guards are found in General Khazard's Fight Arena, south of Ardougne. During the Fight Arena quest, the guard in the south-eastern corner of the jail, by the staircase, is given Khali brew to get him drunk so that he hands over the khazard cell keys.

name: Khazard Guard (Gerald)
examine: The Khazard Guard (named Gerald) is a guard found in the Fight Arena and is involved in the quest of the same name. Players must knock him out with a Khali brew during the quest and steal the Khazard cell keys from him.

name: Khazard Ogre
examine: The Khazard Ogre is a monster fought during Fight Arena. After it is defeated, General Khazard will send out a Khazard Scorpion to fight next. This is General Khazard's 4th best creature who is used to fight against the Slave fighters along with Bouncer and the Khazard Scorpion.

name: Khazard Scorpion
examine: The Khazard Scorpion is a monster fought during Fight Arena. After it is defeated, General Khazard will send out Bouncer to fight next. This is General Khazard's 3rd best creature who is used to fight against the Slave Fighters along with Bouncer and the Khazard Ogre.

name: Khazard trooper
examine: Khazard troopers are the foot soldiers of General Khazard. The level 64 troopers can be found fighting gnomes in the Khazard Battlefield near West Ardougne or spectating at the Fight Arena. Troopers can be a good starting target for beginning archers, because they use Melee attacks and can be shot at from behind fences. Gnome troops continually attack the Khazard troopers and can help if the player needs extra muscle.

name: Khazard warlord
examine: The Khazard warlord is the boss that players have to fight during the Tree Gnome Village quest. He drops two of the Orbs of protection needed for the Spirit tree. He is a very dangerous foe armed with a Khazard warhammer, and can hit very accurately up to 10 damage. He is also wearing a Khazard platebody and a dark coloured Spiny helmet without the spikes. Even though he attacks with a warhammer, he has the attacking speed of a scimitar. During Tree Gnome Village, the player confronts the warlord, and demands the orbs from him. The Warlord refuses and then attacks the player. When the player has killed the warlord, they can search the warlord's satchel and find the two remaining orbs. The player then needs to bring these back to King Bolren in order to complete the quest. It is advised to have adamant armour or better when fighting him.

name: Killerwatt
examine: Killerwatts are Slayer monsters located in the Killerwatt plane, accessible through a portal at the top floor of Draynor Manor. A Slayer level of 37 as well as the completion of Ernest the Chicken is required in order to kill them. If a player is not wearing a pair of Insulated boots while fighting them, their Ranged attacks will have a much higher maximum hit. Just like their standard ranged attacks however, this damage can be mitigated using Protect from Missiles. A Dwarf multicannon cannot be set up in the Killerwatt plane.

name: King Black Dragon
examine: The King Black Dragon, commonly referred to as KBD, is a three-headed dragon located in his lair, accessible only through the deep Wilderness. The lair itself is not in the Wilderness and he is not considered a wilderness boss. The King Black Dragon has a combat level of 276, which makes him one of the strongest dragons in Old School RuneScape. Players should not take this foe lightly, and they should always take an Anti-dragon shield as his dragonfire breath is very deadly without protection. The King Black Dragon can also be killed as an alternative for a black dragon Slayer task.

name: King black dragon (20th Anniversary event)
examine: The King black dragon was an occupant of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. He had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 29 August 2006.

name: King kurask
examine: The King Kurask is a superior variant of the kurask. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: King Roald
examine: King Roald III (more commonly known simply as King Roald) is the current ruler of the prosperous kingdom of Misthalin. His residence is within Varrock Palace, where the Varrock Palace Secret Guard work to keep him safe. He is located in the south-east side of the Palace on the ground floor. He is notable for being one of the least controversial kings, as he is a very straightforward, stable ruler. He has a wife, Ellamaria, who rules alongside as queen.

name: King Sand Crab
examine: ​King Sand Crabs are aggressive monsters that look like sandy boulders while disguised, but attack when walked by. They are found inside the Catacombs of Kourend in the southeast section of the dungeon, as well as the Crabclaw Caves found south of the Woodcutting Guild.

name: King Scorpion
examine: King Scorpions are aggressive monsters found in the Dwarven Mine, the Lava Maze, in the Wilderness, and some areas on Crandor. They patrol the iron, mithril, adamantite, and copper rocks in the area north of the Mining Guild door, the coal and tin rocks west of the Falador house stairs, Lovakengj, and the mithril and coal rocks on Crandor. It stops being aggressive at level 65 outside Wilderness.

name: King Scorpion (20th Anniversary event)
examine: King Scorpions were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. They had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 8 May 2007.

name: Knight of Ardougne
examine: The Knights of Ardougne are found in the East Ardougne market place. One is also found in the courtyard of the East Ardougne Castle. Most are found attempting to chase away thieves. They will protect all stalls from the silk stall and up by attacking players that they observe stealing from them.

name: Knight of Ardougne (unused)
examine: The Knight of Ardougne is an unused monster that was added to the game files in the RuneScape 2 beta. Presumably, it was supposed to be a variant of the Knight of Ardougne that would be found in East Ardougne marketplace. Like the regular Knight, players had the option to either fight or pickpocket it.

name: Knight of Saradomin
examine: Knights of Saradomin can only be found inside the God Wars Dungeon. They are found in the main area and in Saradomin's Encampment. These knights are hard to kill, so it is recommended that a player uses strong weapons and armour, as well as having high combat levels. However, their defence is low and numerous safespots are available to rangers and mages. They have very poor drops, but are generally killed by medium level players to gain entry to the boss room.

name: Kob
examine: Kob is the leader of the trolls of Troll Stronghold, found on the top level. He is fought during Monkey Madness II in order to convince him not to ally with the monkeys of Ape Atoll.

name: Kolodion
examine: Kolodion is the shape-shifting master of the Mage Arena. He is fought to gain entrance to the Mage Arena, where players fight for their god of choice.

name: Koschei the deathless
examine: Koschei the deathless is a Fremennik warrior that players must fight during The Fremennik Trials quest, in order to complete Thorvald the Warrior's test of bravery and win his vote. The player must defeat Koschei three times without dying; although they are told they must defeat him to win, defeating him three times is considered enough to win, as the test is of bravery, not strength.

name: Kraka
examine: Kraka is a level 91 troll guarding Death Plateau. Since trolls are named after the first thing they ate, he probably ate a cracker (which would most likely be a reference to a Christmas cracker). He has a maximum hit of 23, so it is recommended to use Protect from Melee when fighting him. Like the rest of the "big, bad" trolls in the area, such as Stick, Pee Hat, and Rock, he may drop a rune warhammer or granite shield.

name: Kraken
examine: The Kraken is a stronger and larger version of the cave kraken. It requires level 87 Slayer to kill and cannot be boosted. Located at the Kraken Cove, it can only be attacked if the player has cave krakens as a Slayer task, which also requires level 50 Magic. Alongside its non-boss variants, it is the only monster that drops the trident of the seas and Kraken tentacle.

name: Kree'arra
examine: Kree'arra is one of Armadyl's most trusted generals. He is the most powerful of the surviving aviantese, and leader to the forces of Armadyl's Eyrie in the God Wars Dungeon.

name: Kroy
examine: Kroy is a vampyre who can be found in his laboratory in the Sisterhood Sanctuary directly beneath the Crombwick Manor in the town of Slepe.

name: Kruk
examine: Kruk is a monkey that is the head of the Ninja Monkey Guards of Marim, and is located on the east side of the gate, up on the hill. He is the monkey that shouts for the gates to be opened when you approach in monkey form. He is involved in the Monkey Madness I quest, and players must talk to him before meeting King Awowogei to make an alliance with him. Although he has a combat level, he cannot be attacked until a certain stage in Monkey Madness II, nor does he directly attack the player (he simply knocks the player unconscious instead). He is replaced by Duke during the events in Monkey Madness II.

name: Ksenia
examine: Ksenia is one of the citizens of Canifis, found upstairs in the Hair of the Dog. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is more friendly if you equip a Ring of charos.

name: Kurask
examine: Kurask are slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 70 to damage, as well as usage of leaf-bladed weapons, broad bolts, broad arrows, amethyst broad bolts, or Magic Dart. Kurask are immune to poison and venom. Kurask are also immune to damage from a dwarf multicannon and thralls.

name: Lanzig
examine: Lanzig is a Fremennik citizen found in the south-east corner of Rellekka in the hut just north of the farm where vegetables are growing. At level 45 Thieving and after The Fremennik Trials, he can be pickpocketed for 40 coins and 65 Thieving experience.

name: Large mosquito
examine: Large mosquitoes are monsters encountered during Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup. When killed they give 17.5 Agility experience.

name: Lava beast
examine: Lava beasts are found within the Volcanic Mine on the Fossil Island Volcano. They attack players in the mine, and are weak to water spells, which they take double damage from. Using the Protect from Missiles prayer will reduce their max hit to 1.

name: Lava dragon
examine: Lava dragons are former red dragons that have been transformed after being surrounded by lava for too long. They reside in the Lava Dragon Isle in the Wilderness (between level 36 and 42 Wilderness), and attack with melee as well as with dragonfire. Due to their low magic level, they are particularly weak to magic, thus making Fire Bolt a slow but profitable method of killing them.

name: Leech
examine: Leeches (Hirudinae Acidia) are found in Morytania in the Mort Myre Swamp and the Haunted Woods east of Canifis.

name: Lensa
examine: Lensa is one of the many named citizens of Rellekka and can be found near the entrance. At level 45 Thieving and after The Fremennik Trials, this npc can be pickpocketed for 40 coins and 65 Thieving experience.

name: Leon d'Cour
examine: Leon d'Cour is the human Champion of Champions, and the last boss in the Champions' Challenge minigame. He can only be fought after all the other champions have been defeated.

name: Lesser demon
examine: Lesser demons are the second weakest standard demon, above the imp. They are sometimes killed by Free-to-play players, as they are one of the strongest monsters on those servers and can drop the desireable rune med helm. Lesser demons have a somewhat low Defence, allowing players to hit them almost constantly for experience. Like most demons they are susceptible to the effects of demonbane weapons.

name: Lesser demon (20th Anniversary event)
examine: Lesser demons were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. They had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 29 August 2006.

name: Lesser demon (Melzar's Maze)
examine: A Lesser demon is found in the basement of Melzar's Maze, past Melzar the Mad. It must be killed to obtain the green key, which can unlock the green door and complete the maze.

name: Lesser Demon Champion
examine: The Lesser Demon Champion can only be fought after receiving the lesser demon champion scroll as part of the Champions' Challenge minigame.

name: Lev
examine: Lev is a non-player character who can be found wandering about the middle of Canifis. Like many NPCs in Canifis, he will turn into a werewolf when attacked, unless the player is wielding a Wolfbane dagger.

name: Liliya
examine: Liliya is one of the citizens of Canifis. She can be found up the ladder in the general store. If the player is not wielding a wolfbane dagger when they attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is friendlier towards the player if they are wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Lizard
examine: Lizards (Lacertilia giganteus) are Slayer monsters found in the Kharidian Desert that require level 22 Slayer to kill. Ice coolers, which can be bought from any slayer master, are required to kill them. The cooler will be consumed, so multiple coolers are necessary for slayer trips.

name: Lizard man (20th Anniversary event)
examine: Lizard men were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. While they were mentioned in a Behind the Scenes article on 31 March 2004 as a future update, they were ultimately never released.

name: Lizardman
examine: Lizardmen are reptilian humanoids that inhabit the Kebos Lowlands and within the Lizardman Canyon. Secretly created from a native species of lizard during the 37th decade (1,040 years ago) under the rule of King Shayzien VII, he had intended the lizardmen to become his personal army to enforce his tyrannical rule of Great Kourend. After he returned from the dead as Xeric, the lizardmen continued to serve him loyally, seeing him as their god. Today, long after his exile, they still remain loyal, constantly attempting to invade Great Kourend.

name: Lizardman brute
examine: Lizardmen brute are reptilian humanoids that inhabit the Lizardman Canyon, the Lizardman Settlement and the Battlefront. Players are only able to kill them within the Canyon once they earn 5% Shayzien favour; killing them elsewhere requires no favour. Each lizardman killed increases Shayzien favour by 0.1%.

name: Lizardman shaman
examine: Lizardman shamans are giant reptilian humanoids that are stronger than their normal lizardmen and lizardmen brute counterparts. They are often sought after for their dragon warhammer drops. They never become tolerant to the player.

name: Lizardman shaman (Chambers of Xeric)
examine: Lizardman shamans are monsters found in the Chambers of Xeric, in the lizardmen shaman room.

name: Loar Shade
examine: Loar Shades are undead creatures that can be found wandering Mort'ton. They initially appear as shadows and transform into shades when they are in combat. They have a chance to temporarily lower a player's Strength by 1 which can stack. Loar Shades are capable of floating over water and can climb onto bridges that have gaps in the fences.

name: Lobstrosity
examine: Lobstrosities are giant lobsters located in the south-east corner of the Underwater area of Fossil Island. Most weapons and shields cannot be equipped in this area. Weapons that can be equipped and used to kill lobstrosities include the merfolk trident, trident of the seas/swamp, brine sabre, and magic secateurs. Lobstrosities may also be killed with magic.

name: Locust
examine: Locusts are monsters that live behind the buildings in the city of Sophanem and the swamp east of Ruins of Ullek. When killed, they drop Locust meat, which can prolong a player's stay fighting them, as it can be eaten immediately without needing to be cooked.

name: Locust rider
examine: Locust riders are encountered during the Contact! quest, inside the Sophanem Dungeon. The level 98 riders attack using somewhat slow, but strong Ranged attacks with a max hit of 22. The level 106 version uses a spear for melee and has a lower max hit of 15, but attacks faster than the rangers. Remember that you need to bring a light source when you are in the dungeon.

name: Long-tailed Wyvern
examine: Long-tailed Wyverns are Slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 66 in order to be harmed. They reside in the Wyvern Cave on Fossil Island. Like with other Wyverns, an elemental, mind, dragonfire or ancient wyvern shield provides significant protection against their icy breath, and they are vulnerable to the effects of dragonbane weapons. These monsters require completion of the Bone Voyage quest to be assigned as a Slayer task.

name: Lost barbarian
examine: The Lost barbarian is an attackable NPC found in the Ancient Cavern, south of the Brutal green dragons.

name: Lucien
examine: Lucien is a Mahjarrat and a powerful mage and necromancer. He sided with Zamorak in his rebellion against Zaros.

name: Lynx
examine: A lynx is a cat-like monster that roams south of the Secluded Chapel in Shayzien.

name: Lynx Tamer
examine: Lynx Tamers are Shayzien soldiers found by the caged lynxes in the Shayzien Encampment. They share the same drop table as normal guards.

name: Magic axe
examine: Magic axes are monsters that resemble translucent Iron battleaxes. They can be given as a Wilderness Slayer assignment by Krystilia.

name: Malevolent Mage
examine: The Malevolent Mage is a superior variant of the Infernal Mage. It has a chance of spawning once after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Mammoth
examine: Mammoths are a species of elephant-like creatures that inhabit the area southeast of the Ferox Enclave.

name: Man
examine: Men are generic NPC civilians of RuneScape, particularly common in towns such as Lumbridge, Falador, among other settlements. They are also less commonly found outside of towns, and in remote places. Oddly enough, guards do not react to players killing these civilians.

name: Man (Canifis)
examine: Men were formerly the citizens of Canifis. If players were not wielding a wolfbane dagger when attacking them, they would turn into wolfmen.

name: Man (level 4)
examine: Men are citizens of West Ardougne. They are similar to men found throughout RuneScape, but can only be attacked and talked to, and not pickpocketed. Their appearance is slightly different, in keeping with the theme of West Ardougne supposedly being afflicted with a plague, and their dialogue is slightly different, reflecting their plight under Mourner rule.

name: Maniacal monkey
examine: Maniacal monkeys are located in Kruk's Dungeon which the player visits during Monkey Madness II.

name: Maniacal Monkey Archer
examine: Maniacal Monkey Archers are encountered in Kruk's Dungeon.

name: Marble gargoyle
examine: The Marble gargoyle is a superior variant of the gargoyle. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Market Guard
examine: The Market Guard is an attackable NPC that guards the stalls in Rellekka Marketplace. They are non-aggressive towards players, but they will attack a player they spot Thieving from the stalls around them. To steal or buy from a stall, the player must become a Fremennik by completing The Fremennik Trials quest. They don't hit too quickly, but when they do, they usually hit hard. They have a decent amount of life points, making them a feasible training monster, but their drops are of limited value.

name: Market Guard (Draynor)
examine: The Market Guards are guards found in Draynor Village. Unlike regular guards these guards cannot be pickpocketed. One market guard is seen in the Draynor Bank Robbery video attacking Cool Mom227 after she stole from a seed stall.

name: Me
examine: Me is a foe encountered during the quest Lunar Diplomacy in the Dream World. It is fought during the quest, and is an exact copy of the player wearing full Lunar equipment, only inversed in colour. Despite its high Combat level, it is very weak.

name: Melzar the Mad
examine: Melzar the Mad is one of the three wizards, along with Thalzar and Lozar, who escaped from Crandor when the dragon Elvarg destroyed it, and is the only one of them to have survived. He has since lost his sanity, leading to his nickname, and has secluded himself and his piece of the map to Crandor in his maze north-west of Rimmington. He is fought during the Dragon Slayer I quest.

name: Menaphite Akh
examine: The Menaphite Akh is the final boss encountered during the Beneath Cursed Sands quest.

name: Menaphite Shadow
examine: The Menaphite Shadow is summoned by the Menaphite Akh during the Beneath Cursed Sands quest. It will use ranged or magic attacks.

name: Menaphite Thug
examine: Menaphite Thugs can be found at the southern end of Pollnivneach. They will always reward 137.5 Thieving experience and 60 coins for each successful pickpocket. They are the lowest ranked members of the Menaphites, a gang which controls the southern half of Pollnivneach and is constantly at war with the Bandits. They are commonly used by players to train the Thieving skill because upon completion of The Feud quest players may use a blackjack to knock them out and then pickpocket them (up to 260,000 experience can be gained per hour this way). This requires a Thieving level of 65 or higher. Knocking out and pickpocketing one is a requirement for the Hard Desert Diary.

name: Mercenary
examine: Mercenaries are the personal guards of Captain Siad, the head of the Desert Mining Camp. The four of them are led by a Mercenary Captain and their duty is to protect said captain and the entrance to the camp. They will attack the player if he is wielding a weapon or wearing armour outside the Desert Mining Camp a task fulfilled by guards inside the camp.

name: Mercenary Captain
examine: The Mercenary Captain is the leader of all of the Mercenaries in the Desert Mining Camp, and was hired to guard the entrance of it to prevent people from going in and discovering the slave-trade that was going on there. The Mercenary Captain plays a role in the quest The Tourist Trap, in which he is portrayed as a hot-headed and angry individual, and must be provoked to the point of outrage so that he initiates combat with the player himself, rather than having his mercenaries do his dirty work for him, upon which he is killed and drops a Metal key which can open the gate to the Mining Camp.

name: Milla
examine: Milla is one of the citizens of Canifis. If a player is not wielding a wolfbane dagger when they attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is more friendly if you are wearing a ring of charos.

name: Mind Golem
examine: The Mind Golem is one of the golems found in the Ruins of Camdozaal. It can be found by awakening the Rubble lying in the section south of the bank chest, in the enclave containing six piles of rubble that is located east of the Flawed Golems.

name: Minotaur
examine: Minotaur are found on level one of the Stronghold of Security. They drop the right skull half, one of four parts of the Skull sceptre. These monsters are great for training due to their low defence, but have high attack damage making them dangerous for un-equipped players.

name: Mithril dragon
examine: Mithril dragons can be found and fought in the Ancient Cavern. To access the Ancient Cavern, the player needs to start the pyre ship section of Firemaking in Barbarian Training. Be wary as these monsters are extremely powerful. Their release broke the King Black Dragon's long-standing record as being the strongest dragon in RuneScape. It is strongly recommended to use antifire potions in conjunction with an anti-dragon shield (or a Dragonfire shield) when fighting these along with the appropriate protection prayer.

name: Mogre
examine: Mogres are Slayer monsters and a type of ogre that are found in Mudskipper Point. They can only be killed by players who have completed the Skippy and the Mogres miniquest and level 32 Slayer. Mogres appear when disturbed by the player, who must lure them using Fishing explosives on an Ominous Fishing Spot.

name: Molanisk
examine: Molanisks are Slayer monsters that require level 39 Slayer to kill giving 52 Slayer experience per kill. A Slayer bell is necessary to fight them. Players should remember to bring a light source when fighting them, as they are only found underground. Despite what their level would suggest, Molanisks do unusually low damage, meaning a relatively mid-level player with half-decent armour should easily be able to kill several of them.

name: Monk
examine: Monks are worshippers of Saradomin who live in monasteries, churches, and on the island of Entrana. Monks will heal the player 2 + 20% of their Hitpoints if the player talks to them and asks them to do so, unless on a PVP world. The monks of Kandarin Monastery however, do not provide this option.

name: Monk of Zamorak
examine: Monks of Zamorak are evil clerics that follow Zamorak, god of chaos. They are found in several locations, including the Asgarnian chaos temple, Taverley Dungeon, Paterdomus, Battlefield mine and Deep Wilderness Dungeon. A level 17 Monk of Zamorak is in a cage under the stairs on the ground floor of Varrock Palace. He is often used in free-to-play servers to train magic using the Curse spell.

name: Monkey (monster)
examine: Monkeys are small, level 3 monsters that may be found in a variety of locations. They are not ideal for training combat, as they have a low amount of hitpoints and have few useful drops. However, monkey bones do give slightly more Prayer experience than regular bones.

name: Monkey Archer
examine: A Monkey Archer is a monster found on Ape Atoll and features heavily in the Monkey Madness I quest as well as playing some role in the Recipe for Disaster quest. Its bones are necessary to make a small Ninja monkey greegree. They attack with ranged from small platforms.

name: Monkey Guard
examine: Monkey Guards are level 167 gorillas that reside in the Temple of Marimbo, found on Ape Atoll. They reside on the ground floor[UK]1st floor[US] and 1st floor[UK]2nd floor[US] of Ape Atoll's Temple of Marimbo and are the strongest guard found on Ape Atoll. They have a large amount of health and throw vicious punches that can hit up to 14. When they have very low health, they will beat their chest, causing them to heal 25 hitpoints, which is about 20% of their maximum health; they appear to be able to do this indefinitely but only while in melee range. Monkey Guards drop larger versions of monkey bones, which give 18 prayer experience points when buried. However, these are not tradeable.

name: Monkey Guard (ninja)
examine: Monkey Guards will appear if players talk to a monkey on Ape Atoll while in human form. One or two of these may appear along with one of the named ninja monkeys. The named monkeys are Duke, Uodai, Ouhai, Oipuis, and Uyoro.

name: Monkey Zombie
examine: Monkey Zombies are encountered during Monkey Madness I in the Ape Atoll Dungeon. They drop Monkey bones that are needed to make a Zombie greegree. They appear to be green undead monkeys.

name: Monster
examine: Monster is the official term for an attackable character or being that is not player-controlled. A monster can range from a not-so-harmful Rat to the extremely strong Chaos Elemental. Monsters are often fought by players for training, entertainment, and loot. Killing monsters is one of the most popular activities in Old School RuneScape. Nearly all monsters drop remains.

name: Monstrous basilisk
examine: The Monstrous basilisk is a superior variant of the Basilisk. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Monstrous Basilisk (The Fremennik Exiles)
examine: Monstrous Basilisks are larger variants of normal basilisks, encountered during the quest The Fremennik Exiles. It appears during the section where basilisks attempt to attack and take over Rellekka. Defeating it will add 10% completion of defending the region from the basilisks. Like other basilisks, players will need to be protected from its gaze ability, so players should battle them with V's shield, which is collected shortly before the invasion.

name: Mosquito swarm
examine: Mosquito swarms are monsters fought during the Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup minigame. When killed, level 17 and 20 swarms give 35 and 75 agility experience respectively.

name: Moss giant
examine: Moss giants are large, humanoid creatures found in areas that are tied to nature.

name: Moss Guardian
examine: Moss Guardians are the guardian spirits of Glarial's Tomb, and are significantly larger and stronger than ordinary moss giants. They are encountered during the Waterfall Quest when the player enters the tomb to obtain Glarial's amulet, and must later be killed during the Roving Elves quest to obtain the consecration seed. They can only be fought unarmed, as it is impossible to take weapons, armour or ammunition into the tomb. They cause a magical splashing effect when they attack, and will occasionally hit with Magic instead of Melee.

name: Mosschin
examine: Mosschin is the third of the goblin high priests that players fight during the quest Land of the Goblins. Upon his defeat, he will speak to the player.

name: Mother
examine: Mother (full name Mother's Left One) is the leader of the town of Weiss, and the father of Snowflake.

name: Mountain troll
examine: Mountain trolls are aggressive creatures which can be found patrolling various mountainous areas.

name: Mounted terrorbird gnome
examine: Mounted terrorbird gnomes are gnomes riding terrorbirds. They are stronger than regular unmounted terrorbirds. They are found spread around and to the south of the Tree Gnome Stronghold and the Battlefield. They may be killed for the bird slayer task. They attack with melee and are weak for their level, and consequently aren't very hard to kill.

name: Mourner
examine: Mourners are a collection of elves and humans who have joined the Prifddinas Death Guard. They are located all across West Ardougne, and some are located at the gate of Arandar (entrance to Tirannwn). Some of the Mourners drop the mourner outfit, items used in Mourning's End Part I and Part II. As a side note, use caution when fighting the level 11 mourners as they will drain all your combat stats (including Hitpoints) to 20 when attacked.

name: Mourner (boss)
examine: A level 13 Mourner is fought during Biohazard. When the player infiltrates the Mourner Headquarters, they will encounter a mourner on the top floor who sees through their disguise. After he is killed, he drops a key, which can be used to access the crates containing the Distillator required for the quest.

name: Mourner (Song of the Elves)
examine: Mourners are fought during the West Ardougne uprising during Song of the Elves. 10 mourners must be killed within West Ardougne, then 11 mourners must be killed in basement of the Mourner Headquarters.

name: Mouse
examine: Mice are encountered during the Grim Tales quest while the player is shrunk. The mouse's drops look large when viewed on the floor, but they appear normal-size inside a player's inventory. Picking up and re-dropping large drops yields normal sized drops. Presumably, the mouse is as large as a rat if the player were normal-sized (such as the ones found around Lumbridge) but has a higher combat level because the player is smaller.

name: Mudskipper
examine: A mudskipper is an attackable fish found in the Mogre Camp. Large mudskippers are level 31, while their smaller counterparts are level 30.

name: Mugger
examine: Muggers have a combat level of 6 and can be a threat for new players.

name: Mummy
examine: Mummies are undead monsters found in the Pyramid Plunder minigame and during Desert Treasure. The mummies that drop ancient staves are in Jaldraocht Pyramid south of Bandit Camp, and can only be accessed once the four Diamonds of Azzanadra have been recovered during Desert Treasure.

name: Mutated Bloodveld
examine: Mutated bloodvelds are stronger variants of bloodvelds that require level 50 Slayer to kill. They are found within the Catacombs of Kourend, Iorwerth Dungeon and the Meiyerditch Laboratories.

name: Muttadile
examine: The Muttadiles are bosses encountered in the Chambers of Xeric. It is a dog-like creature that has horribly mutated into a giant crocodilian beast. The original muttadile was pregnant at the time when Xeric transformed it into its current form and as such its offspring was warped too. The two beasts now act as guardians of the chambers.

name: Myre Blamish Snail
examine:
The Myre Blamish Snail is a very common snail which lives in the Mort Myre Swamp.
This type of snail drops two items upon its death; a Blamish myre shell and a Thin snail. Their respawn time is around 30–40 seconds. A chisel can be used on the dropped Blamish myre shell (with level 15 Crafting) to make a myre snelm.

name: Nail beast
examine: Nail beasts are encountered on all three paths of the Temple Trekking minigame and are the only monster to drop nail beast nails. The combat levels of Nail beasts are based on the difficulty (length) of the event chosen: they are level 69 on easy (long), level 98 on medium (medium), and level 141 on hard (short). The number encountered also depends on the chosen escortee: with an easy escortee, players will see between two and three Nail beasts, with a medium escortee they will see between three and four, and on with a hard escortee anywhere between four and six will appear.

name: Narf
examine: Narf is a strange fellow that can be thieved as well as attacked. He gives the same amount of coins as well as the similar drops and Thieving experience as a man. He is most likely in a gang of thieves including Jeff, Rusty and Cuffs. When talked to, the player automatically comments that his name is strange, and Narf responds, "Well, at least I don't call myself (player's username)! Where do you get a name like that?"

name: Nazastarool
examine: Nazastarool is an undead encountered during Shilo Village quest. He has three forms; the first being a level 91 Zombie, second a 68 Skeleton and finally a 93 Ghost. All three forms have to be fought during the quest. A very easy way to kill him is to either range or use magic on him, as he can get stuck behind obstacles. All three forms may also be safespotted with a Halberd. He is found in Rashiliyia's Tomb.

name: Nechryael
examine: Nechryael are demonic Slayer creatures, which require a Slayer level of 80 in order to harm. They are found in the Slayer Tower, and their stronger variant, Greater nechryael, can be found in the Catacombs of Kourend,  Iorwerth Dungeon, and the Wilderness Slayer Cave. Nechryael are known for their rune boots drop, which are one of the few boots to provide a Strength bonus when worn. They are also known for their frequent drop rates of seeds and combat runes.

name: Nechryarch
examine: The Nechryarch is a superior variant of nechryael and greater nechryael. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Necromancer
examine: Necromancers are found just outside Shayzien as well as between Lovakengj and Arceuus. They are accompanied by zombies and dark warriors.

name: Necromancer (Necromancer Tower)
examine: The Necromancer is found on the ground floor of the Necromancer Tower. He will attack with his fists, with curse spells, and by summoning Summoned Zombies to aid him. He has a noticeably long respawn time, possibly something to do with the fact that he raises himself from the dead to achieve his "Mortal return".

name: Newtroost
examine: A Newtroost is a hybrid of a newt and a rooster. Players can create newtroosts in Creature Creation, in the basement dungeon of the Tower of Life building once they complete the Tower of Life quest.

name: Nex
examine: Nex is one of Zaros' most powerful followers. She is imprisoned in the Ancient Prison, sealed away beneath the God Wars Dungeon. An immensely powerful entity and one of Zaros's most powerful weapons of war, Nex is a nihil (properly called Zarytes) from Freneskae and possesses physical traits of the icyene, demons, aviantese and vampyres.

name: Nezikchened
examine: Nezikchened is a level 187 black demon that has to be defeated three different times during the Legends' Quest. He is also among the strongest demons in the game. At the start of each fight he drains a player's prayer points. Like all demons, he is also vulnerable to the effects of demonbane weapons. He has a very peculiar habit of calling the player 'Vacu'. According to Gujuo 'Vacu' was the name for priests who were enslaved by the 'spirits of the underworld'.

name: Night beast
examine: The Night beast is a superior variant of the dark beast. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master. Like their standard variant, they will only use their Magic attack if attacked first (which will always be the case since they are not aggressive) or from afar.

name: Nikita
examine: Nikita is one of the citizens of Canifis. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is more friendly if you are wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Nikolai
examine: Nikolai is one of the citizens of Canifis. He can be found in the Hair of the Dog pub. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack, he will turn into a werewolf. He is more friendly if you are wearing a ring of charos.

name: Nuclear smoke devil
examine: The nuclear smoke devil is a superior variant of the smoke devil. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Nylocas Athanatos
examine: Nylocas Athanatos spawn during the second phase of the Verzik Vitur during the Theatre of Blood. These nylocas do not target players but instead attend to Lady Verzik, healing her much like the Nylocas Matomenos. If it is hit with a weapon capable of afflicting poison or venom (or when the serpentine helm is equipped), the Nylocas Athanatos will instead burst and deal damage to Verzik, indicated by a green aura appearing over it.

name: Nylocas Hagios
examine: Nylocas Hagios are part of the wave prior to the Nylocas Vasilias encounter in the Theatre of Blood. They spawn alongside Nylocas Toxobolos and Nylocas Ischyros as they attempt to destroy the pillars. They also appear during the Verzik Vitur encounter, spawned periodically during the second and third phase whereupon they chase after players and burst when they get near, dealing high damage.

name: Nylocas Ischyros
examine: Nylocas Ischyros are part of the wave prior to the Nylocas Vasilias encounter in the Theatre of Blood. They spawn alongside Nylocas Toxobolos and Nylocas Hagios as they attempt to destroy the pillars. They also appear during the Verzik Vitur encounter, spawned periodically during the second and third phase whereupon they chase after players and burst when they get near, dealing high damage.

name: Nylocas Matomenos
examine: Nylocas Matomenos spawn during The Maiden of Sugadinti and Verzik Vitur encounters in the Theatre of Blood. They will heal the boss for their remaining hitpoints if they reach her, so binding them in place using ice spells is necessary to prevent massive amounts of hitpoints being restored.

name: Nylocas Prinkipas
examine: Nylocas Prinkipas are part of the wave prior to the Nylocas Vasilias encounter found only in the Theatre of Blood/Hard Mode. Three of them spawn throughout the encounter alongside Nylocas Hagios, Nylocas Ischyros and Nylocas Toxobolos as they attempt to destroy the pillars. However, they remain in the middle of the room attacking the players instead of targeting the pillars. It changes its combat style by changing its carapace, which also indicates its weakness: blue for magic, green for ranged and white for melee. Attacking it with the wrong combat style will cause it to reflect the hit back towards the player as well as healing from the hit. It will change every 10 ticks (6 seconds), and it will always change to one of the other two styles (meaning it will not stay on one style twice in a row).

name: Nylocas Toxobolos
examine: Nylocas Toxobolos are part of the wave prior to the Nylocas Vasilias encounter in the Theatre of Blood. They spawn alongside Nylocas Hagios and Nylocas Ischyros as they attempt to destroy the pillars. They also appear during the Verzik Vitur encounter, spawned periodically during the second and third phase whereupon they chase after players and burst when they get near, dealing high damage.

name: Nylocas Vasilias
examine: Nylocas Vasilias is the third encounter in the Theatre of Blood, and spawns after killing off the hordes of Nylocas Hagios, Ischyros, and Toxobolos.

name: Obor
examine: Obor, the Hill Titan, is the hill giant boss residing in his lair, located in the locked gates found at the western wall of the hill giant area in the Edgeville Dungeon.

name: Ocga
examine: Ocga is an attackable citizen of Burthorpe with many dialogues when spoken to, often welcoming the player. He may also speak about the Burthorpe Imperial Guard, White Knights, and Trolls, who unfortunately took his baby son.

name: Ochre Blamish Snail
examine: The Ochre Blamish Snail is a common snail which lives in the Mort Myre Swamp. Their attacks deal Ranged damage despite having a similar animation to Curse, and can only be used in melee range. They appear to have a max hit of 1, despite what is stated by Monster Examine.

name: Ogre
examine: Ogres are found in several locations, most notably the Ogre city of Gu'Tanoth. The ogres found in the Combat Training camp can only be fought using ranged, magic or melee using a halberd.

name: Ogre chieftain
examine: Ogre chieftains are ogres that can be found in the Feldip Hills and inside the Ogre Enclave. Players can kill ogre chieftains towards an ogre Slayer task.

name: Ogre shaman
examine: Ogre shamans are monsters found in the Ogre Enclave during the Watchtower quest.

name: Ogress Shaman
examine: Ogress Shamans are found in the Corsair Cove Dungeon.

name: Ogress Warrior
examine: Ogress Warriors are found in the Corsair Cove Dungeon. They are a good way for free-to-play ironmen to obtain rune battleaxes and rune full helms, as well as law/nature runes.

name: Oipuis
examine: Oipuis is an intelligent monkey guard that resides in the island city of Marim. Oipuis is one of several guards that can appear if they talk to a monkey on Ape Atoll while in human form. He may appear along with several Monkey Guards.

name: Oomlie bird
examine: Oomlie birds are found within the Kharazi Jungle. Like Jungle savages, these enormous version of chickens are not aggressive (however using the bull roarer near them will cause them to attack you with the message "A nearby Oomlie bird takes a dislike to the sound you are making" appearing in your chatbox). They can be killed for their Oomlie meat, the main ingredient of Oomlie wraps. To create one, the player needs the Raw Oomlie and a Palm leaf found in the surroundings by shaking Leafy palm trees.

name: Orc (20th Anniversary event)
examine: Orcs were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. During 2004, an Orc could be found wandering the Tree Gnome Village maze, but this was removed long before the release of Old School RuneScape.

name: Orc (historical)
examine: Orcs were former monsters who could originally be found in RuneScape 2. A Behind the Scenes article in March 2004 promised that RuneScape would be adding "Many new monsters such as Orcs, Lizardmen and more." As a result, two Orcs were added to the game who could be found in the south-west corner of the Gnome Maze.

name: Ork
examine: Orks are stocky, green-skinned humanoids. They have small tusks protruding from their jaws, and prefer to wield large axes and/or maces.

name: Othainian
examine: Othainian is a demon encountered during the Underground Pass quest. When killed, it drops the amulet of othanian, which is needed to obtain Iban's shadow. Protect from Melee should be used during this part of the quest to save hitpoints for coping with its attacks.

name: Otherworldly being
examine: Otherworldly beings are unusual Zanarian monsters. They are commonly assigned as Slayer tasks by Vannaka. They are found south of the bank in Zanaris and can be safespotted by standing next to the flower pond and attacking the ones on the other side. Be wary, they do move around quite a lot and aren't easy to safespot.

name: Ouhai
examine: Ouhai is an intelligent monkey guard that resides in the island city of Marim. Ouhai is one of several guards that can appear if they talk to a monkey on Ape Atoll while in human form. He may appear along with several Monkey Guards.

name: Outlaw
examine: Outlaws are monsters featured in the What Lies Below quest, during which they have to be killed in order to obtain five Rat's papers that are used to create the full folder. Outlaws are found in their encampment near the fairy ring west of the Grand Exchange and north of the shed, which leads into the Edgeville Dungeon. Like highwaymen, they will shout "Stand and deliver!" They appear to be wielding a steel scimitar with a recoloured handle.

name: Padulah
examine: Padulah is located on the isle of Ape Atoll. He is the head guard in charge of protecting the Sacred Statue of Marimbo, the monkey god. He hits very hard with melee and is surrounded by Monkey Archers who hit very hard with ranged.

name: Painted Goblin
examine: A painted goblin is a goblin painted white. Players on the guards' side during the 2014 Goblin Invasion event must paint the goblins white with an event rpg in order to make them attackable. Also while a goblin is painted, guards nearby will attack and kill it. Goblins may de-spawn if there are many goblins around, and it hasn't died, even during combat, and even in the death animation.

name: Paladin
examine: Paladins are found in East Ardougne, wandering near the castle and market. They are from Ardougne's Holy Order of Paladins, and wear the symbol of Saradomin. Three paladins are found in the Underground Pass and must be killed during the quest. They have special drops related to the quest.

name: Palmer
examine: Palmer is a pirate who can be found at the Pirates' Cove. He may be part of the crew of the Lady Zay, along with Jake and Wilson who are found nearby, but his purpose is unknown.

name: Parasite
examine: Parasites are thrown at players by The Nightmare while fighting her. After the parasite has grown, it will burst out of a player, damaging them. Drinking a dose of Sanfew serum or Relicym's balm will weaken the parasite.

name: Parasite (Phosani's Nightmare)
examine: Parasites are thrown at players by Phosani's Nightmare while fighting her. After the parasite has grown, it will burst out of the player, damaging them. Drinking a dose of Sanfew serum or Relicym's balm will weaken the parasite.

name: Pee Hat
examine: Pee Hat is a level 91 troll guarding Death Plateau. Protect from Melee is highly recommended as he can hit up to 23. Like the rest of the troll bosses in the area (Stick, Rock, and Kraka), he may drop a Rune warhammer or Granite shield.

name: Penance Fighter
examine: Penance Fighters are only encountered during the Barbarian Assault minigame. Like Penance Rangers, they can only be killed by the Attacker. There are four ways to damage this monster:

name: Penance Healer
examine: The Penance Healer is a creature only encountered during the Barbarian Assault minigame. They will heal other Penance creatures and can only be killed with poisoned foods, or by firing the egg cannon at them. The food required to kill them changes every 30 seconds. A single poisoned food will cause a total of 54 damage over time. Therefore, Healers on Wave 8 and Wave 9 must be killed by using more than 1 food as they have a high amount of health. Unlike other monsters, Penance Healers tick poison damage every 3 seconds.

name: Penance Queen
examine: The Penance Queen is the boss monster of the Barbarian Assault minigame. She spawns in Wave 10 after all monsters are killed, or alternatively after a 4 minute delay if not all monsters are killed. She uses ranged attacks in rapid succession that can easily hit up to 13, and simultaneously strikes all players fighting her. Her melee attack can also hit up to 13. Players may not use protection prayers whilst fighting her. She can easily wipe out a whole party of players, especially if there is no cooperation between team members.

name: Penance Ranger
examine: Penance Rangers are only encountered during the Barbarian Assault minigame. Like Penance Fighters, they can only be killed by the Attacker. There are four ways to damage this monster:

name: Penance Runner
examine: Penance Runners are only encountered while playing the Barbarian Assault minigame. The Runners cannot be attacked by conventional means such as melee or ranged attacks. Instead players must kill the Runners by luring it to the Runner trap with bait or by shooting eggs via the Egg Launcher. It is the job of the Defender to prevent Runners from running south and entering the cave opening, which results in 3 points being deducted from the group score for each escaping Runner.

name: Penda
examine: Penda is a citizen in Burthorpe, a bar patron and hangs out more at The Toad and Chicken than his own house.

name: Penguin (monster)
examine: Penguins are low-levelled monsters found on Here Be Penguins, only accessible by using the AJS fairy ring, and also inside an exhibit in the Ardougne Zoo. They have no drops apart from bones, and are therefore rarely killed.

name: Pestilent Bloat
examine: The Pestilent Bloat is the second encounter in the Theatre of Blood. It was created by a crazed vampyre known as "The Butcher" upon Verzik Vitur's request.

name: Phantom Hand
examine: Phantom Hands are summoned by Xamphur when he is fought during the A Kingdom Divided quest.

name: Pheasant
examine: Pheasants are birds that are featured in the Freaky Forester random event, in which the player is tasked with killing a pheasant with a specific number of tails, and delivering its meat to the Freaky Forester. Despite the Freaky Forester asking for the meat from a pheasant with a specific number of tails, he will accept meat from any pheasant.

name: Phosani's Nightmare
examine: Phosani's Nightmare is a more difficult version of The Nightmare, encountered by selecting Drink-from on the Pool of Nightmares in the Sisterhood Sanctuary. It can only be fought in a solo encounter and the player must have had defeated the normal version of the Nightmare at least once.

name: Phrin Shade
examine: Phrin Shades lurk behind the first door of the Mort'ton shade catacombs dungeon. They initially appear as dark moving shadows on the ground and then rise from the depths to attack. Their remains can be cremated with any pyre logs. The Salve amulet and Salve amulet (e) work well on this shade which is very useful if shades are assigned for a slayer task.

name: Pirate
examine: Pirates are non-player characters that can be found in the Asgarnian Ice Dungeon and the Pirates' Hideout at level 55 Wilderness or around Brimhaven, in the Port Sarim Jail, and around the Pirates' Cove at level 23. They are also fought during Cabin Fever.

name: Pirate Guard
examine:
Pirate guards are posted just west of the Brimhaven Agility Arena, and are also found in ScarFace Pete's mansion. Pirate guards resemble the old Varrock town guards, but with black equipment instead of bronze equipment.
You can speak to Pirate guards, but they do not provide you with any useful information.

name: Pit Scorpion
examine: Pit scorpions are scorpions found in the dungeon of the Legends' Guild and Ardougne Zoo.

name: Plague frog
examine: Plagued Frogs are frogs that recently infested the banks of the desert city of Sophanem. They are low levelled, and because they have no drops, are very rarely killed.

name: Poison Scorpion
examine: Poison Scorpions are found in the Taverley Dungeon and Brimhaven. They are poisonous, and their poison starts at 3 Hitpoints per hit. As such, a form of antipoison is recommended when fighting them.

name: Poison spider
examine: Poison spiders are monsters that can be found in many locations, including the Wilderness. They are aggressive and attack with Melee, being fairly accurate and able to inflict a poison that starts at a 6. Contrary to popular belief, Protect from Melee does not prevent them from causing poison.

name: Poltenip
examine: Poltenip is one of the guards in Nardah. He, along with Radat and Tarik, guard Awusah, the mayor of Nardah.

name: Porazdir
examine: Porazdir is a Tsutsaroth demon[1] who was once one of Zamorak's most trusted generals during the God Wars. Said to kill any in his path without mercy, even if they are demons, Porazdir is described as "completely mad", and regularly clashes with Justiciar Zachariah.[2]

name: Portal (Pest Control)
examine: The Portals are key features in the Pest Control minigame. They spawn monsters, and should be destroyed to win the game. There are four portals in one game of Pest Control, and players are ordered to destroy them in a random rotation. Their health is 200 hitpoints for a novice game, and 250 hitpoints for intermediate and veteran games. Killing one portal will heal the Void Knight in the centre by 50 hitpoints. The portals can be healed by Spinners, and players are advised to kill these before attacking the portal.

name: Possessed pickaxe
examine: Possessed pickaxes are an animated NPC found in the Haunted Mine and the Catacombs of Kourend. They look like a normal pickaxe until the player walks past them, when they become animated. Possessed pickaxes are weak against magic and crushing attacks.

name: Possessed Priest
examine: The Possessed Priest is a sub-boss featured in the quest Icthlarin's Little Helper. He wears a Menaphite robe and attacks using Strike Spells.

name: Pyrefiend
examine: Pyrefiends are Slayer monsters that require level 30 Slayer to kill. As their attacks are magic based, it is recommended to wear armour with a high magic defence bonus, such as dragonhide. Pyrefiends and Harpie bug swarms are the only monsters to drop steel boots.

name: Pyrelord
examine: Pyrelords are stronger variants of pyrefiends that require level 30 Slayer to kill. They are found within the Sisterhood Sanctuary and on the north side of the Isle of Souls.

name: Queen spawn
examine: Queen spawn appear in Wave 10 of the Barbarian Assault minigame. Unlike the other Penance, anyone can attack the spawn regardless of their position, but it is not recommended to do so as the Penance Queen will just create more spawns. Spawns will spawn every 6 seconds to a maximum of four. Spawns give no combat experience when you damage them.

name: Rabbit
examine: A Rabbit is an animal that is found in various places across RuneScape. Three rabbits can be seen on the ground from inside the Air Altar, but they are most often too far away to be attacked (although they can be attacked if the player and the rabbit are within range). There are also attackable (with Magic or Ranged) rabbits inside the Nature Altar.

name: Rabbit (Prifddinas)
examine: The rabbit is a monster that is found in a cave in the Gwenith Hunter area north of Prifddinas. Contrary to its low combat level, it is much more dangerous than it suggests, possessing as much health as the Corporeal Beast and dealing extremely high damage coupled with a high attack speed.[1]

name: Radat
examine: Radat is one of the guards in Nardah. He, along with Poltenip and Tarik, guard Awusah, the mayor of Nardah.

name: Ragnar (Miscellania)
examine: Ragnar is a subject of Miscellania currently located in the Miscellania market.

name: Ragnvald
examine: Ragnvald is a subject of Miscellania located in the Miscellania market. If killed, the players Managing Miscellania approval rating is reduced by 5%.

name: Ram
examine: A ram is a male sheep. Players cannot shear rams like they can sheep; instead they can attack them.

name: Ranalph Devere
examine: Ranalph Devere is one of the three long-dead warriors required to be killed to collect the heart piece for the Legends' Quest. There are several of these warriors around the cave and killing one causes all of them to stop being hostile, but you can still attack them and they will fight back. However, if you attack another one, you will be unable to kill him as he can only be killed once. He attacks with melee.

name: Ranis Drakan
examine: Ranis Drakan is one of the three vampyre nobles who rule over the Sanguinesti region, alongside his siblings Vanescula Drakan and Lowerniel Drakan, overseeing Morytania and Darkmeyer for his brother alongside Vanescula.

name: Rannveig
examine: Rannveig is a subject of Miscellania currently located in the Miscellania market.

name: Rat
examine: Rats are small animals that can be found in numerous locations, mostly in cities, sewers and dungeons. Thus, they are common animals found throughout RuneScape, typically Combat level 1 or 3.

name: Ravager
examine: Ravagers are short, humanoid creatures with large claws in the Pest Control minigame. Their appearance is closely related to that of a mole with over sized claws and red eyes. Although they do not attack the Void Knight directly, they are capable of tearing down the gates and barricades with just a few swipes of their claws, giving Torchers and Defilers a clearer shot at the Void Knight. As such, they must be killed as quickly as possible to protect the Void Knight from the torchers and defilers. Ravagers are non-aggressive, and have low defence and attack. However, they have high strength and thus can hit quite hard for their levels, so Protect from Melee is advised if targeting them.

name: Reanimated abyssal
examine: A Reanimated abyssal can be spawned with the spell Master Reanimation. It can be reanimated where it was killed, but a player can only reanimate the ensouled head that they loot themselves. If a player teleports or trades the ensouled head, it must be reanimated by the Dark Altar. Killing the creature will grant the player 1,300 Prayer experience.

name: Reanimated aviansie
examine: A Reanimated aviansie can be spawned with the spell Master Reanimation. It can be reanimated where it was killed, but a player can only reanimate the ensouled head that they loot themselves. If a player teleports or trades the ensouled head, it must be reanimated by the Dark Altar.

examine: A Reanimated bloodveld can be spawned with the spell Expert Reanimation at level 72 Magic. If a player teleports or trades the ensouled head, it must be reanimated by the Dark Altar. Killing the reanimated bloodveld requires level 50 Slayer and will grant the player 1,040 Prayer experience (and 35 Slayer experience if on task).

name: Reanimated chaos druid
examine: A Reanimated chaos druid can be spawned with the spell Adept Reanimation. It can be reanimated where it was killed, but a player can only reanimate the ensouled head that they loot themselves. If a player teleports or trades the ensouled head, it must be reanimated by the Dark Altar. Killing the creature grants 584 Prayer experience. Killing it while in the Wilderness with a task from Krystilia counts towards the task.

name: Reanimated dagannoth
examine: A Reanimated dagannoth can be summoned by casting the Arceuus spell Expert Reanimation on an ensouled dagannoth head near the Dark Altar or where the creature originally died. Killing the creature grants 936 Prayer experience and gives +1.5% Favour for the Arceuus House (assuming you're not already at 100%).

name: Reanimated demon spawn

Even though Skotizo can continue chanting the summoning phrase, there can only be three reanimated demon spawns present in the arena at any given time.

name: Red dragon
examine: Red dragons are second-to-most powerful of the adult chromatic dragons. As with all adult dragons, an anti-dragon shield and/or antifire potion is essential when fighting them to mitigate damage from their dragonfire. The red dragonhides and dragon bones that they drop are worth substantial amounts of money.

name: Red dragon (20th Anniversary event)
examine: The Red dragon was an occupant of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. Red dragons had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 29 August 2006.

name: Redeyes
examine: Redeyes is the fourth of the goblin high priests that players fight during the quest Land of the Goblins. Upon his defeat, he will speak to the player.

name: Renegade knight
examine: Renegade Knights are knights devoted to serving the evil sorceress Morgan Le Faye. They imprisoned the Knights of the Round Table and Merlin during King's Ransom. They can be accessed by taking the crate behind the candle shop in Catherby after the quest Merlin's Crystal.

name: Repugnant spectre
examine: The Repugnant spectre is a superior variant of the normal deviant spectre. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master. They are found exclusively within the Catacombs of Kourend.

name: Respiratory system
examine: The respiratory system is encountered during the fight with the Abyssal Sire.

name: Revenant cyclops
examine: The revenant cyclops is a type of revenant that inhabits the Revenant Caves, which is a PvP-enabled area that is part of the Wilderness. Like all revenants, they can restore their health when it falls below 50% and will react to a player's protection prayers; wearing a charged bracelet of ethereum will reduce all revenants' damage by 75%.

name: River troll
examine: River trolls appear when attempting to fish in the Enchanted Valley. If Swan Song has been completed, the troll will burst out of the water saying that the player killed the Sea Troll Queen before attacking.

name: Riyl Shade
examine: Riyl Shades are found in the Shade Catacombs beneath Mort'ton, and are fought in the Shades of Mort'ton minigame.

name: Riyl shadow (Temple Trekking)
examine: Riyl shadows can be encountered in Temple Trekking, while travelling along the easy path through Mort'ton.

name: Robert the Strong
examine: Robert the Strong was a famous hero who battled against the Dragonkin in the Fourth Age during the Dragonkin Conflicts and forced them into hiding.

name: Rock (Troll)
examine: Rock is the strongest troll on Death Plateau, possessing a higher max hit and a significantly faster attack rate than Stick, who spawns next to him. Players must be very cautious when fighting him, as he can hit a max of 30 and has a fair amount of hitpoints. Since he only attacks with melee, Protect from Melee is recommended. Like the other named trolls on the plateau, such as Stick, Pee Hat, and Kraka, he may drop a Rune warhammer or Granite shield.

name: Rock Crab
examine: Rock Crabs are aggressive monsters that look like harmless rocks while disguised, but attack when walked by. Unlike most other enemies and NPCs, Rock Crabs are not marked with yellow dots on the player's minimap; this is probably due to the crabs' appearance, which camouflages them as rocks.

name: Rock golem (monster)
examine: The rock golem can be found in the Enchanted Valley, accessible using the fairy ring code BKQ, appearing when attempting to mine a rock. The rock golem will use Ranged attacks and Protect from Missiles will negate all damage.

name: Rock lobster
examine: Rock lobsters are found in the Waterbirth Island Dungeon's fifth sub-level, in Room 16. They are similar to giant rock crabs in the fact that they are initially disguised as large rocks, but they will attack the player as they approach. They have very high Defence (though they are weak to Magic attacks) and can hit up to 15 Hitpoints, but rarely hit over 11 Hitpoints. Their attack speed is as fast as darts on Rapid (they attack every second game tick), making them incredibly dangerous.

name: Rockslug
examine: Rockslugs are Slayer monsters that require level 20 Slayer to kill. In order to kill a rockslug, a bag of salt must be used when it has less than 5 Hitpoints. If a bag of salt is used on a rockslug with 5 or more Hitpoints, the bag will be consumed but have no effect. If a rockslug's health is reduced to 1 but a bag of salt is not used on it, the rockslug will stop retaliating and wander off. Players can buy the "Slug salter" perk from a Slayer master for 80 Slayer points, which will automatically salt the rockslug when it falls below 5 Hitpoints, provided that the player has a bag of salt in their inventory. Alternatively, a brine sabre can be used to kill them without the need for bags of salt.

name: Rocnar
examine: A Rocnar can be built in the Floor space of the Oubliette in a player-owned house. It requires 83 Construction to build and when built, it gives 387 experience.

name: Rogue
examine: Rogues are human monsters that can also be pickpocketed, with level 32 Thieving. Pickpocketing a rogue grants 36.5 Thieving experience. It is the only pickpocketing target found exclusively in the Wilderness. The level 135 variant cannot be pickpocketed.

name: Rooster
examine: A rooster is a low-level monster that is very similar to a chicken, and indeed they are found together.

name: Rowdy Guard
examine: Rowdy Guards are unused NPCs who could previously be found in the Desert Mining Camp disciplining the Rowdy slaves. In 2006, The Tourist Trap was reworked, and the rowdy guards were replaced by a new NPC simply named Guard who fulfilled much the same purpose. As a result, they have never been present in Old School RuneScape.

name: Rowdy slave
examine: A rowdy slave is a human slave found at the Desert Mining Camp south of the Shantay Pass where players must go for the quest The Tourist Trap. Note that they will only drop slave robes if you do not already have them. They are the only attackable slaves and sometimes will attack you. If you want to get the Slave clothes back, you can kill one near the guard in the first section of the underground mining camp.

name: Rune dragon
examine: Rune dragons are metal dragons first encountered during Dragon Slayer II, in which the player must fight one during Zorgoth's assault. After completion of the quest, they can be found in the eastern chamber of the Lithkren Vault.

name: Rune dragon (Construction)
examine: A rune dragon can be built in the Monster space of the Treasure Room in a player-owned house. It requires 99 Construction to build and when built, it gives 5,000 experience.

name: Runite Golem
examine: Runite Golems are found in the Resource Area east of the Deserted Keep. They are weak to melee, especially pickaxes. A higher Mining level means more damage will be dealt. When it dies its head will become a runite rock for 1 minute before disappearing, which can be mined with 85 Mining. Once defeated anyone can mine it. Once mined it respawns in 5 minutes. There are only two of them in each world.

name: Rusty
examine: Rusty is a strange fellow that can be thieved as well as attacked. He gives the same amount of coins as well as similar drops and Thieving experience as a man. When you talk to him he asks if you are carrying anything valuable, and, after you question him further, says, "It's been ages since anyone said they had something worth stealing." then stammers "Not that I'd dream of stealing something, of course." He hangs out with Narf, Cuffs, and Jeff, presumably his gang of thieves.

name: Salarin the twisted
examine: Salarin the twisted is an evil druid in Yanille's Agility dungeon. He can be found at the end of the dungeon, in an area that requires level 67 Agility to enter (64 with an Agility potion or 62 with a Summer pie). He is currently one of only three NPCs able to drop the Sinister key, alongside the Magpie impling and the Chaos Fanatic.
