This key opens the Sinister chest that contains nine herbs: 2 Harralander, 3 Ranarr weed, 1 Irit, 1 Kwuarm, 1 Avantoe, and 1 Torstol. Salarin is a target for many players because of this drop. Players should keep in mind that the Sinister key is an uncommon drop.

name: San Tojalon
examine: San Tojalon is one of the long-dead warriors the player must defeat to collect the heart piece for the Legends' Quest. He attacks with melee and can only be killed once, twice if players chose the "short" route in the quest. Killing San Tojalon causes him and his duplicates to stop being hostile.

name: Sand Crab
examine: Sand Crabs are aggressive monsters that look like harmless sandy rocks while disguised, but attack when walked by. They are found along the southern coast in Hosidius, Crabclaw Caves, Crabclaw Isle and Isle of Souls. No favour is required to access or kill them and are available to all players. The dwarf multicannon cannot be used against Sand Crabs. Killing a Sand Crab is a task in the Easy Kourend & Kebos Diary.

name: Sand Snake
examine: The Sand Snake is the monster protecting the chest containing the Royal accord of twill at the end of the Crabclaw Caves during The Depths of Despair. The dwarf multicannon cannot be used against the sand snake. It can be killed using only Ring of recoils without having to deal direct damage.

name: Sarachnis
examine: Sarachnis, the mother of the temple spiders, is a mid-level boss found in the Forthos Dungeon, in a former burial tomb south of the Spider Den. She can be killed as part of a spider Slayer task.

name: Saradomin priest
examine: Saradomin priests are found in the God Wars Dungeon. They are located in the main area and Saradomin's Encampment. Like their Spiritual mage-aligned counterpart, they attack using Saradomin Strike, except it doesn't drain the player's prayer points.

name: Saradomin wizard
examine: Saradomin wizards appear when doing hard clue scroll coordinates outside of the Wilderness. They call out "For Saradomin!" upon appearing.

name: Scarab Mage
examine: Scarab Mages are encountered during the Contact! quest. They attack using Magic. Their magic attack looks like a swarm of beetles and hits up to 17 hitpoints.

name: Scarab Swarm
examine: Scarab swarms are swarms of poisonous scarab beetles. Although their max hit is low, they are highly accurate with an extremely fast attack speed and are very likely to poison any players that they attack. They can crawl up from the ground randomly in some pyramid areas, and have a chance of spawning when the gold chest is opened in Pyramid Plunder.

name: Scarab Swarm (Beneath Cursed Sands)
examine: The Scarab Swarm is summoned by the Champion of Scabaras during Beneath Cursed Sands. He spawns them after exclaiming: The children of Scabaras are eternal!. They are very similar to the standard Scarab Swarm, but unlike the regular variant, they leave behind a trail of black flames, which hurt the player if they run across them. It is recommended to kill them as quickly as possible, when the Champion of Scabaras spawn them, as they make running around the chamber more difficult and dangerous. The flame trail will linger for a while, but will disappear before the Champion summons a new swarm.

name: Scarabs
examine: Scarabs are lower levelled versions of Scarab swarms, which randomly spawn inside the Jaldraocht Pyramid from cracks in the ground. They are identical in appearance and behaviour to scarab swarms, including their extremely fast attack speed and ability to poison, making them dangerous for lower levelled players.

name: Scavenger beast
examine: Scavenger beasts are monsters found in the Chambers of Xeric. They are found in ruins and drop various items needed for puzzles and materials for skilling. They closely resemble Skavids found in the Feldip Hills region of Kandarin, as they appeared prior to their graphical update on 5 December 2006. They may be a subspecies of Skavid native to Mount Quidamortem.

name: Scavenger runt
examine: Scavenger runts were monsters found in the Chambers of Xeric. They could be found in ruins and drop various items needed for puzzles and materials for skilling. Compared to scavenger beasts, they dealt less damage and had fewer hitpoints, but they dropped two items when killed as opposed to three.

name: Scion
examine: Scions are matured spawns during the fight with the Abyssal Sire. The spawn matures into a scion if it is not killed within 12 seconds. Scions boast more health, accuracy and damage.

name: Scorpia
examine: Scorpia is a large female scorpion that resides in a cave beneath the Scorpion Pit. She is a powerful scorpion that can drop one of three shards required to forge odium wards and malediction wards.

name: Scorpia's guardian
examine: Scorpia's guardians appear while fighting Scorpia. Two appear on the next attack after Scorpia reaches 99 health or lower, even if you splash. Unlike her and her offspring, the guardians do not attack the player but instead heal Scorpia, shown with a curse projectile animation. The guardians can be killed to stop their healing effects or can be bound with ice or binding spells. If they do not heal Scorpia in 15 seconds, they will despawn. Unlike Tz-Tok Jad's Yt-HurKot, they will not appear if they heal her back to full health.

name: Scorpia's offspring (monster)
examine: Scorpia's offspring are tiny scorpions that inhabit Scorpia's cave. Their Ranged attack is incredibly accurate and drains Prayer for every splash.

name: Scorpion
examine: Scorpions are monsters mainly located in free-to-play areas. They can be dangerous to low level players training Mining.

name: Scorpion (20th Anniversary event)
examine: Scorpions were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. They had this appearance during RuneScape 2 until a graphical update on 8 May 2007.

name: Screaming banshee
examine: The screaming banshee is a superior variant of the banshee. It has a 1/200 chance of spawning while on a Slayer task of banshees after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Screaming twisted banshee
examine: The screaming twisted banshee is a superior variant of the twisted Banshee. It has a 1/200 chance of spawning while on a Slayer task of banshees after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Sea Snake Hatchling
examine: Sea snake hatchlings are encountered near the end of the Royal Trouble quest, in the Miscellania and Etceteria Dungeon just before facing the Giant Sea Snake. The snakes are poisonous. Players fighting them should bring poison protection of some sort, such as Antipoison, Antipoison+, or Antipoison++.

name: Sea Snake Young
examine: Sea Snake Young are found in the Miscellania and Etceteria Dungeon, which can be entered during and after the Royal Trouble quest. The snakes are poisonous; their poison damage starts at 8 Hitpoints during the quest and 7 Hitpoints after the quest. Players fighting them should bring poison protection of some sort, such as Antipoison, Antipoison+, or Antipoison++. They attack with Melee and are vulnerable to Magic.

name: Sea troll
examine: Sea trolls are trolls encountered during the Swan Song quest. They first ambush the player and the Wise Old Man when first entering the colony. Players may also encounter sea trolls while fishing for monkfish during the quest. After completing the quest, Sea trolls will no longer attack the player while fishing for monkfish.

name: Sea Troll Queen
examine: The Sea Troll Queen is a boss monster encountered during the quest Swan Song. She is the monarch of the Sea Trolls, and the apparent leader of the attack on the Piscatoris Fishing Colony by the Sea trolls.

name: Seagull
examine: Seagulls are small birds that can be found on the docks of Port Sarim and Corsair Cove. Their low max hit and negative defence bonus makes them a prime target for beginners.

name: Sergeant (Shayzien)
examine: Sergeant are elite versions of the soldiers and found in the Shayzien Encampment. They wield a dragon longsword along with a dragon sq shield, and wear Shayzien armour.

name: Sergeant Grimspike
examine: Sergeant Grimspike is one of three sergeants found guarding General Graardor in the Bandos section of the God Wars Dungeon, alongside Sergeant Strongstack and Sergeant Steelwill. Sergeant Grimspike uses rather accurate ranged attacks with a max hit of 21 Hitpoints.

name: Sergeant Steelwill
examine: Sergeant Steelwill is one of the three sergeants found guarding General Graardor in the Bandos section of the God Wars Dungeon, along with Sergeant Strongstack and Sergeant Grimspike. Sergeant Steelwill uses a magic attack with a max hit of up to 16 hitpoints.

name: Sergeant Strongstack
examine: Sergeant Strongstack is one of the three sergeants fighting for General Graardor, along with Sergeant Grimspike and Sergeant Steelwill. Strongstack uses melee attacks and attacks by drifting to each player in the room assuming there is more than one.

name: Servant (Burthorpe)
examine: The servant is one of Prince Anlaf's helpers, found within Burthorpe Castle. He tells players he is busy with his duties and redirects them to Eohric if they want to ask questions.

name: Shade
examine: Shades are monsters that reside on the fourth level of the Stronghold of Security (the Sepulchre of Death) and in the Catacombs of Kourend. The shades in the Stronghold of Security are found next to the ladder leading to the fourth floor, while the ones in the Catacombs of Kourend are found in the northernmost area of Reeking Cove, south from the steel dragons. Be aware that any experience gained while fighting the shades in the Stronghold of Security is drastically reduced, including Slayer experience (however, this does not affect the Prayer experience granted by the ectoplasmator).

name: Shade (Temple Trekking)
examine: Shades can be encountered in Temple Trekking, while travelling along the hard path through Mort'ton.

name: Shadow
examine: Shadows are monsters which play a major role in the Mourning's End Part II quest, found within the Temple of Light. They have few Hitpoints and low Defence, however use accurate Melee attacks which can hit up to 13; having high Defence or activating the Protect from Melee prayer is HIGHLY recommended.

name: Shadow Hound
examine: Shadow Hounds are dog-like monsters found in the Shadow Dungeon. They can be accessed by wearing a ring of visibility during or after the Desert Treasure quest. They are seldom killed due to being located in a multicombat area, as well as providing no drops except bones. As with most monsters in the Shadow Dungeon, they allow other monsters to pass through them.

name: Shadow Portal
examine: The Shadow Portal is summoned by the Champion of Scabaras during Beneath Cursed Sands. If either the player or the Champion of Scabaras walk over the portal, they'll take damage. If the portal isn't destroyed within a short while it will explode dealing up to 35 damage to the player.

name: Shadow spider
examine: Shadow spiders are one of few monsters that are hidden on the player's minimap. If a player initiates combat, it will drain the player's Prayer points by half of the current amount, rounded up. If a player is in combat with them over a long period, they will continue to drain the player's Prayer at regular intervals. Wearing a spectral spirit shield reduces the Prayer drain by half.

name: Shadow warrior
examine: A Shadow warrior is a deceased knight, back from the plane of death. However, they are not considered undead, so the salve amulet has no effect on them. These monsters don't appear on the mini map. Shadow warriors appear to be wielding battleaxes, but they attack at the same speed as scimitars. After completion of Legends' Quest, Shadow warriors are a possible Slayer task from Chaeldar and Vannaka.

name: Shadow Wyrm
examine: The Shadow Wyrm is a superior variant of the wyrm. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master. Shadow Wyrms cannot be safespotted like regular wyrms in the slayer only area, but Protect from Magic will prevent all damage while at range.

name: Shaeded Beast
examine: The Shaeded Beast is a monster that has possessed Olbertus, a treasure hunter. It can be seen in the Altar of the Sun if players are wearing a ring of visibility, and becomes fully visible if players choose to kill Olbertus instead of giving him five dragonstones.

name: Shantay Guard
examine: Shantay Guards can be found guarding the Shantay Pass in southern Al Kharid. There are 3 attackable level 22 guards, and one who manages who passes through the gate. The attackable guards only drop bones, and are not often fought.

name: Shifter
examine: Shifters are creatures in the Pest Control minigame that excel in melee combat and can teleport across the island and even pass through walls. For this reason, they are very dangerous for those on defence since they can teleport right next to the Void Knight and attack them. They appear to have the bottom half of a spider with the scythes of a praying mantis (similar to the Abyssal demon). Their colouring varies, depending on their combat levels. Although it has the ability to teleport other monsters, such as Ravagers and Torchers (even up on to towers), they can only teleport others a very short distance. Unlike other pests, shifters are immune to the effects of poison.

name: Shipyard worker
examine: Shipyard workers are men employed by the gnome Glough to work in his large Shipyard in eastern Karamja. They can be attacked. They feature in the quest Monkey Madness I.

name: Sigmund
examine: Sigmund is a high-ranking member of Humans Against Monsters, a former advisor to Duke Horacio and the main antagonist in the Dorgeshuun quest series. He has been involved in three attempts to destroy the Dorgeshuun goblins. The first was during the Lost Tribe quest, the second during the Death to the Dorgeshuun quest, and again in the Another Slice of H.A.M. quest.

name: Sir Bedivere
examine: Sir Bedivere is one of King Arthur's weaker knights. Players must help him break out of jail in the King's Ransom quest.

name: Sir Carl
examine: Sir Carl is a knight of the Royal Army of Ardougne, killed by the player during the Underground Pass quest to collect the green paladin's badge. He gives the player food if they talk to him before throwing his badge down the well.

name: Sir Gawain
examine: Sir Gawain is the one of King Arthur's knights. Players must help him break out of jail in the King's Ransom quest.

name: Sir Harry
examine: Sir Harry is a paladin and a member of the Royal Army of Ardougne that must be killed during the Underground Pass quest in order to collect the red paladin's badge. He gives the player food if they talk to him before throwing his badge down the well.

name: Sir Jerro
examine: Sir Jerro must be killed during the Underground Pass quest to collect the blue paladin's badge. He will gives the player food if they talk to him before killing him.

name: Sir Kay
examine: Sir Kay is one of King Arthur's knights. Players must help him break out of jail in the King's Ransom quest.

name: Sir Lancelot
examine: Sir Lancelot is the strongest of King Arthur's knights. Players must help him break out of jail during the quest King's Ransom.

name: Sir Leye
examine: Sir Leye is one of the Temple Knights that test your skills during the Recruitment Drive quest. You must fight him as a woman, using no armour, weapons, food, or potions. This is due to a famous legend stating that Sir Leye had been blessed by Saradomin himself, and that no "man" can defeat him.

name: Sir Lucan
examine: Sir Lucan is one of King Arthur's knights. Players must help him break out of jail in the King's Ransom quest.

name: Sir Mordred
examine: Sir Mordred can be found on the top floor of Keep Le Faye near Catherby. He is fought during the Merlin's Crystal quest. He can be fought, but when he reaches 0 hitpoints, Morgan Le Faye will appear and ask that you spare him. If you ignore Morgan Le Faye and continue to attack him, he will regenerate all of his hitpoints and you must fight him again while Morgan Le Faye wanders around aimlessly.

name: Sir Palomedes
examine: Sir Palomedes is one of King Arthur's knights. Players must help him break out of jail in the King's Ransom quest.

name: Sir Pelleas
examine: Sir Pelleas is the one of King Arthur's knights. Players must help him break out of jail in the King's Ransom quest.

name: Sir Tristram
examine: Sir Tristram is one of King Arthur's knights. Players must help him break out of jail in the King's Ransom quest.

name: Skeletal miner
examine: A skeletal miner is an undead monster. It appears on the second and 4th level of the Abandoned Mine as a corpse with the examine text "Well, at least he doesn't have to worry about getting 'black lung'." and will animate occasionally when walked past to attack you. It counts as a skeleton for the purpose of Slayer tasks.

name: Skeletal Mystic
examine: Skeletal Mystics are skeleton mages found within the Chambers of Xeric.

name: Skeletal Wyvern
examine: Skeletal wyverns are Slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 72 in order to be harmed. They are found at the end of the Asgarnian Ice Dungeon. Like other wyverns, they require an elemental shield, mind shield, dragonfire shield, dragonfire ward, or ancient wyvern shield to reduce damage from their icy breath; however, it is not required to be slain. They are also the only monster that drops granite legs.

name: Skeleton
examine: Skeletons are undead monsters found in various locations across RuneScape, often in graveyards and dungeons. Being an undead monster, it is weak to Crumble Undead and the Salve amulet. They are also often weak against crush attacks.

name: Skeleton (Ape Atoll)
examine: These Skeletons are undead gorillas found in the multi-combat Ape Atoll Dungeon. Players are required to run past them during the Monkey Madness I quest in order to reach Zooknock. Players are advised to use Protect from Melee against these monsters, as they attack accurately and can easily overwhelm with their sheer numbers.

name: Skeleton (Barrows)
examine: Skeletons are undead monsters lurking in the Barrows tunnels. Skeletons are one of the many obstacles between a player and the chest containing rewards where they constantly distract players from completing puzzles. As with all monsters in the crypts, they are aggressive to any player regardless of their Combat level. Two of them are commonly killed alongside a bloodworm each run as a quick way to optimise the player's reward potential for the most runes. They may spawn whenever the player opens a door in the tunnels.

name: Skeleton (Draynor Manor)
examine: A Skeleton can be found in a closet inside Draynor Manor. It features in the Ernest the Chicken quest, where it is found guarding the rubber tube required to fix Professor Oddenstein's machine.

name: Skeleton (mage)
examine: Skeletons are found in Tarn's Lair. They have the same appearance as Skeleton Mages, and also share the same stat-reducing attack which reduces Attack, Strength and Defence stats by 3-4 levels, exclaiming "I infect your body with rot...". They are able to recognize the player's protection prayers and will switch attack styles accordingly, although their melee attack is weaker and less accurate than their Magic attack.

name: Skeleton (Melzar's Maze)
examine: Five skeletons can be found on the 2nd floor[UK]3rd floor[US] of Melzar's Maze. They must be killed in order to obtain the yellow key, which can unlock the yellow doors and progress through the maze.

name: Skeleton (Shayzien Crypts)
examine: Skeletons are level 132 undead monsters found in the Shayzien Crypts. The crypts were constructed long before the founding of Great Kourend 1,510 years ago, but within the last few hundred years were overrun by zombies and skeletons.

name: Skeleton (Tarn's Lair)
examine: Skeletons are undead monsters that can be found inside Tarn's Lair and right outside it in the Abandoned Mine. These skeletons are unique in appearance and their item drops are unlike their regular counterparts.

name: Skeleton (The Restless Ghost)
examine: The skeleton is an undead monster encountered during the quest The Restless Ghost. When the player takes the ghost's skull from the altar in the basement of the Wizards' Tower, the skeleton animates and attacks them. The skeleton is not a particularly dangerous enemy, and it is not required to kill it in order to complete the quest. The player can simply leave after retrieving the skull, and the skeleton will disappear after a while.

name: Skeleton brute
examine: A skeleton brute is a level 132 undead monster located in the Ancient Cavern.

name: Skeleton Champion
examine: The Skeleton Champion can only be fought after receiving the skeleton champion scroll as part of the Champions' Challenge minigame.

name: Skeleton fremennik
examine: Skeleton fremenniks are stronger versions of regular skeletons in the Brine Rat Cavern, led by Ulfric.

name: Skeleton guard
examine: A skeleton, also known as bones, can be built in the Guard space of the Oubliette and Dungeon in a player-owned house. It requires 70 Construction to build and when built, it gives 223 experience.

name: Skeleton heavy
examine:
The Skeleton heavy can be found in the Ancient Cavern. It can appear when a player rummages a skeleton lying on the ground.
As with all undead, they are weak to the Salve amulet as well as the Salve amulet (e).

name: Skeleton Hellhound
examine: The Skeleton Hellhound is a monster summoned by Vanstrom Klause during the In Search of the Myreque quest to kill the remaining Myreque members. In order for the quest to be completed, the Skeletal Hellhound must be defeated, which should not be a problem for a moderately levelled player, as it is fairly weak. Crumble Undead does not work against this monster, and the salve amulet seems to have no effect. After dying, the Skeleton Hellhound will drop 4 big bones and two uncut rubies, which appear to be the eyes of the monster.

name: Skeleton Hellhound (Vet'ion)
examine: The Skeleton Hellhound is a monster summoned by Vet'ion. Two spawn during the first form of Vet'ion after half of his health has depleted and must be killed as he is immune to attacks while they are present.

name: Skeleton hero
examine: The skeleton hero can be found in the Ancient Cavern, which to access the player must have completed Barbarian training. The hero can appear when a player rummages a skeleton lying on the ground and, after rising, will attack the player.

name: Skeleton Mage
examine: Skeleton Mages are a rare variant of skeleton that make use of Magic to attack. Thus, it is recommended to wear magic-resistant armour such as dragonhide armour. They play a role in the Swan Song quest, where the player creates an army of them to help defeat the sea trolls.

name: Skeleton thug
examine: The Skeleton thug can be found wandering around the Ancient Cavern. It is one of the weaker monsters in the Ancient Cavern.

name: Skeleton warlord
examine: Skeleton warlords can be found in the Ancient Cavern, which is accessible from the Baxtorian Falls. They have a seemingly average accuracy and max hit for their level, and are generally best to be avoided as one heads for the Mithril dragons.

name: Skoblin
examine: Skoblins are skeletal goblins summoned by Strongbones during the quest Land of the Goblins and the miniquest Hopespear's Will.

name: Skogre
examine: Skogres are encountered during the Zogre Flesh Eaters quest and live south of Castle Wars. An aggressive Skogre may also appear when you bury Zogre bones inside Jiggig . Their name is a portmanteau of "skeleton ogre".

name: Skotizo
examine: Skotizo is a demonic boss located beneath the Catacombs of Kourend. Accessing his lair requires the use of a dark totem on the altar found in the centre of the Catacombs; one dark totem permits only one attempt, which makes it a sporadic boss.

name: Skraeling (Etceteria)
examine: Skraelings, or Skraelingjar are the warriors that guard Etceteria. Failing to steal from a stall the Etceteria market will trigger them to say: "Get your hands off there!" and attack the thief.

name: Skraeling (Miscellania)
examine: Skraelings, or Skraelingjar are the warriors that guard Miscellania. If you fail to steal from a stall the Miscellania market, they will say: "Get your hands off there!" and attack you.

name: Slagilith
examine: The Slagilith is an enemy encountered during the One Small Favour quest, inside the Goblin Cave. It is summoned when attempting to free Petra Fiyed from the rock face; the player fails to properly cast the spell contained within their scroll, thus accidentally animating some rocks nearby.

name: Slash Bash
examine: Slash Bash is an undead ourg encountered during the Zogre Flesh Eaters quest. He uses both melee and ranged attacks. It is vital to have Relicym's balm or Sanfew serum, and at least swordfish or better when fighting him, as the disease can drain stats by up to 15. He is very difficult as he can drain your prayer and switch between devastating range and powerful melee. However, it is possible to use magic or ranged from behind the stand or a stack of bones, and then he can only damage the player using range.

name: Sleepwalker (monster)
examine: Sleepwalkers are NPCs summoned by The Nightmare at the beginning of the second and final phases of the fight. The number of sleepwalkers summoned are dependent on the amount of players in the fight, ranging from 1-24.

name: Sleepwalker (Phosani's Nightmare)
examine: Sleepwalkers are NPCs summoned by Phosani's Nightmare at the end of the first four phases of the fight. Aside from their appearance, they are the same as the sleepwalkers encountered in The Nightmare encounter.

name: Slug Prince
examine: The Slug Prince is encountered in the Witchaven Dungeon during The Slug Menace quest. He can only be fought once and requires 30 Slayer to kill. The people of Witchaven are obviously very mad at you for killing the Slug Prince, as after you kill him they tell you to leave them alone.

name: Small Lizard
examine: Small Lizards are Slayer monsters found north-north- east of Nardah east of fairy ring (DLQ). An Ice cooler must be used on a lizard when it has 1-4 hitpoints left in order to kill it. They can be killed for Desert Lizard slayer tasks.

name: Smoke devil
examine: The smoke devil is a mutated version of a dust devil, found at the Smoke Devil Dungeon. These require a minimum of 93 Slayer and an active Slayer task to be harmed. A Slayer helmet, Slayer helmet (i), or a Facemask is required to kill these. This monster, along with its boss variant and superior variant, are the only monsters to drop the Occult necklace.

name: Smokedevil
examine: The Smokedevil was an unused slayer monster added to the cache with the release of the Slayer skill. Both the Smokedevil and the Dust Devil (then named Dustdevil) were not initially present in the game. The name and examine suggest that originally, the Dustdevil would have been encountered in the Kharidian Desert, while the Smokedevil would have only been located underground in the Smoke Dungeon. However, when the desert was expanded a few months later, the Dustdevil was moved to the Smoke Dungeon instead.

name: Snailfeet
examine: Snailfeet is the second of the goblin high priests that players fight during the quest Land of the Goblins. Upon his defeat, he will speak to the player.

name: Snake
examine: Snakes (Serpentes Fellis) are serpentine monsters. On Karamja, they can be found near level 3 monkeys and level 14 scorpions. Unlike their bush snake cousins, the Karamjan snakes do not poison.

name: Snake (Ape Atoll)
examine: Jungle snakes are level 24 monsters found on Ape Atoll. They are poisonous and also aggressive to players who are not wearing a greegree. They are not recommended to train on, due to the low hitpoints, remote location, their high max hit relative to their combat level, and the fact that they can inflict poison regardless of whether or not their attacks hit the player, similar to Cave slime. The poison can be prevented by using any antipoison potion (super or better recommended).

name: Snake (Mos Le'Harmless)
examine: Striped snakes can be found in the jungle of Mos Le'Harmless. Unlike the generic snakes found on Karamja, the Mos Le'Harmless snakes are poisonous, with their poison damage starting at 3.

name: Snakeling
examine: Snakelings are summoned during the fight with Zulrah.

name: Snothead
examine: Snothead is the first of the goblin high priests that players fight during the quest Land of the Goblins. Upon his defeat, he will speak to the player.

name: Sofiya
examine: Sofiya is one of the citizens of Canifis. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is more friendly if you are wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Soldier (Burthorpe)
examine: Soldiers are members of the Burthorpe Imperial Guard. There are some Soldiers that you cannot attack who are doing military drills in the main area of Burthorpe. They appear to be wearing spiny helmets coloured black without the spikes. When talking to them they will say a random sentence in Latin. They are trained by Sergeants.

name: Soldier (Shayzien)
examine: Soldiers are members of the Shayzien Army found in the Shayzien Encampment. They have identical stats and drops to regular guards, but cannot be pickpocketed

name: Soldier (tier 1)
examine: A soldier (tier 1) is a Shayzien soldier from Great Kourend. Players can fight him in the Combat Ring to obtain Shayzien armour (tier 1), providing they have at least 60% Shayzien favour and level 20 Defence.

name: Soldier (tier 2)
examine: A soldier (tier 2) is a Shayzien soldier from Great Kourend. Players can fight him in the Combat Ring to obtain Shayzien armour (tier 2), providing they have at least 70% Shayzien favour.

name: Soldier (tier 3)
examine: A soldier (tier 3) is a Shayzien soldier from Great Kourend. Players can fight her in the Combat Ring to obtain shayzien armour (tier 3), providing they have at least 80% Shayzien favour.

name: Soldier (tier 4)
examine: A soldier (tier 4) is a Shayzien soldier from Great Kourend. Players can fight him in the Combat Ring to obtain Shayzien armour (tier 4), providing they have at least 90% Shayzien favour.

name: Soldier (tier 5)
examine: A soldier (tier 5) is a Shayzien soldier from Great Kourend. Players can fight her in the Combat Ring to obtain Shayzien armour (tier 5), provided that they have 100% Shayzien favour and have a set of tier 4 or 5 Shayzien armour on them or in their bank.

name: Soldier (Yanille)
examine: Soldiers are similar to Guards except they are higher level and are found only in Yanille. They are under the command of Colonel Radick.

name: Solus Dellagar
examine: Solus Dellagar is the main antagonist of the Wanted! quest whom the player defeats. He is capable of using a highly lethal form of Ice Barrage, although when the player fights him he attacks exclusively with much weaker melee. He can also cast Teleother Camelot, which he forcibly uses on the player (the player has no option to cancel).

name: Sorebones
examine:
Sorebones are the surgical zombie pirates under the command of the evil and short surgeon Mi-Gor. After the player defeats Barrelchest, the monks inform the player that they have escaped with Mi-Gor back into the ocean. Their name seems to be a parody of the term "sawbone", a title given to surgeons.
They must be fought during The Great Brain Robbery quest in order to collect the components needed for Dr Fenkenstrain. The sorebones get replaced with Barrelchest by the end of the quest, but they reappear after the quest is completed.

name: Sotetseg
examine: Sotetseg is the fourth encounter in the Theatre of Blood. It is a dark beast that has been corrupted through Haemalchemy.

name: Soulless
examine:
Soulless are soul-less humans found in the Underground Pass.
They do not have to be killed, but can be killed for bones.

name: Sourhog
examine: A sourhog is a boar-like monster introduced in A Porcine of Interest. It requires reinforced goggles to kill, or a Slayer helmet after the quest. If no protection is used the caustic saliva they spit will burn the player's eyes, draining the player's current Attack and Defence by 90% and cause 20-30 damage each hit accompanied by the player exclaiming Argh! My eyes!.

name: Sourhog (A Porcine of Interest)
examine: The Pig Thing is a sourhog that the player encounters during a cutscene in A Porcine of Interest. The sourhog sneaks up on the player while they are investigating the skeleton in the Sourhog Cave, then uses it's caustic saliva to attack the player resulting in them fainting. Some time later the player is rescued by Spria. When first encountered, the sourhog cannot be attacked. After being taught about sourhogs and provided with Reinforced goggles by Spria, the player returns to the cave and defeats the sourhog, completing the quest.

name: Spawn
examine: Spawns are summoned during the fight with the Abyssal Sire. They have low health and use rather inaccurate melee and ranged attacks. If the spawn is not killed within 12 seconds, it will mature into a scion.

name: Spawn (Dragon Slayer II)
examine: A Spawn is a creature which appears during the Dragon Slayer II quest. Upon investigating the ancient mural, it will leap out of a nearby strange egg and begin attacking the player.

name: Spawn of Sarachnis
examine: Spawn of Sarachnis are spiders summoned by Sarachnis during the fight against her. The blue one attacks with magic and the orange one attacks with melee.

name: Speedy Keith
examine: Speedy Keith is one of the three leaders of the Wilderness Bandit Camp. Like the other two leaders, Black Heather and Donny the lad, he is not aggressive. Attempting to talk to Speedy Keith yields the message: "Speedy Keith is not interested in talking".

name: Spider
examine: Spiders are found all over Gielinor, but most notably in the Stronghold of Security, where they can be found at Combat level 24 and in large numbers. Most level 2 spiders have a relatively slow attack speed, with only the spiders in the Underground pass being an exception. Spiders are usually considered a nuisance and drop no items. It should also be noted that the level 24 spiders are aggressive and can hit up to 6 damage. They give 22 Slayer experience per kill.

name: Spider (Ape Atoll)
examine: Spiders can be found around Ape Atoll, they are aggressive and will poison the player.

name: Spider (araxyte)
examine: Araxytes, known simply as "spider" in-game, are venomous spiders found in the Morytania Spider Nest. As they are abundant in numbers, able to inflict venom, and in a multicombat area, it is dangerous to fight them without prayer or a method to stave off venom.

name: Spider (Ungael)
examine: Spiders are found in the dragonkin's Ungael laboratory beneath Ungael. They are able to inflict venom on the player.

name: Spidine
examine: A Spidine is a hybrid of a Raw Sardine and a Deadly red spider. Players can create spidines in Creature Creation, at the south-east altar in the basement dungeon of the Tower of Life building, once they complete the Tower of Life quest.

name: Spiked Turoth
examine: The Spiked Turoth is a superior variant of the turoth. It has a chance of spawning after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Spinner
examine: Spinners are monsters in Pest Control that appear as spinning tops or jellyfish that levitate. Their role is to repair the Portal it came from and should be defeated if the portals are to be destroyed quickly. It is recommended that players kill the Spinners first before attacking the portal, especially if more than one Spinner is present.

name: Spinolyp
examine: Spinolyps are small, Dagannoth-like creatures found in the deepest sublevel of Waterbirth Island Dungeon in the same room as the Dagannoth Kings. It is recommended to bring some form of antipoison as they are able to poison. Their Magic attack takes the appearance of Water Strike and is considered ranged-based magic as it rolls against the player's Ranged defence.[1] As such, it will always be more beneficial to use a guthan's platebody over a karil's leathertop, for example. A successful hit by their Magic attack also drains 1 prayer point; this prayer drain effect is halved when using a spectral spirit shield.[2] Their ranged attack is poisonous and resembles the one used by Ranged-using Dagannoth. Each attack can hit up to 10.

name: Spiritual mage
examine: The Spiritual mage is a potent Magic Slayer monster found in the God Wars Dungeon that can easily kill low-level players. Protect from Magic and high prayer bonus is highly recommended for anyone wanting to 'camp' these monsters. Like all monsters in the God Wars Dungeon, they are aggressive to any players that do not wear items showing loyalty to their god. Spiritual mages require 83 Slayer to kill. Completion of Death Plateau is required before Spiritual creatures can be assigned as a Slayer task[1]. Just like Spiritual rangers and Spiritual warriors, which require 63 and 68 Slayer respectively, there are spiritual mages for each god.

name: Spiritual ranger
examine: Spiritual rangers are powerful Ranged Slayer monsters found in the God Wars Dungeon. There are five types of spiritual rangers: Saradominists, Zamorakians, Bandosians, Armadyleans and Zarosians. Spiritual rangers require 63 Slayer to kill, and the Troll Stronghold quest must be partially complete to gain access to the God Wars Dungeon. Spiritual creatures cannot be given as a Slayer task if the player has not completed the Death Plateau quest.

name: Spiritual warrior
examine: The Spiritual warrior is a powerful Slayer monster found in the God Wars Dungeon. There are five types of spiritual warriors: Saradominists, Zamorakians, Bandosians, Armadyleans and Zarosians. Spiritual warriors require 68 Slayer to kill (note Spiritual creatures cannot be given as a Slayer task if the player has not completed the Death Plateau quest). Just like Spiritual rangers and Spiritual mages, there are Spiritual warriors from each god.

name: Spitting Wyvern
examine: Spitting wyverns are Slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 66 in order to be harmed. They reside in the Wyvern Cave on Fossil Island and are the weakest of the Fossil Island wyverns. Like with other Wyverns, an elemental, mind, dragonfire ward, dragonfire or ancient wyvern shield (not including Anti-dragon Shield) provides significant protection against their icy breath. These monsters require completion of the Bone Voyage quest to be assigned as a Slayer task. Additionally, players can benefit from using dragonbane weapons to deal additional damage per second.

name: Splatter
examine: Splatters are monsters in the Pest Control minigame. Their appearance is a giant, wrinkled ball with a single eye in the middle and liquid inside them. They will bounce towards the fort and detonate, causing 5-24 typeless damage to all players and monsters in a 3x3 radius, as well as damaging nearby gates or barricades. This will also happen if they are killed.

name: Stag
examine: Stags are monsters that can be found roaming the Enchanted Valley (fairy ring code BKQ) and near Mynydd in Tirannwn.

name: Starlight
examine: Starlight the unicorn is a bodyguard of Commander Zilyana, along with Growler and Bree. She uses powerful melee attacks to bring down her enemies, which has a max hit of 15. She is the strongest known Unicorn in the game.

name: Steel dragon
examine: Steel dragons are powerful dragons found in the Brimhaven Dungeon and the Catacombs of Kourend. Steel dragons are the fourth strongest metallic dragons, behind mithril, adamant and rune dragons. They have a chance of dropping the draconic visage. Like their fellow metallic brethren, steel dragons can use long-range dragonfire in addition to using melee.

name: Steel dragon (Construction)
examine: A steel dragon can be built in the Monster space of the Treasure Room in a player-owned house. It requires 95 Construction to build and when built, it gives 3,162 experience.

name: Stick
examine: Stick is a troll that is encountered on Death Plateau. Players wishing to fight him should be careful, as he has a lot of hitpoints and can hit a max of 27. Since he only attacks with melee, the Protect from Melee prayer would be useful. Like the rest of the "big, bad" trolls in the area, such as Rock, Pee Hat, and Kraka, he may drop a Rune warhammer or Granite shield.

name: Stone Guardian
examine: Stone Guardians are found in the Karamjan Temple in the south-east corner of the Kharazi Jungle.

name: Stranger
examine: The stranger is a mysterious person who sometimes appears and attacks players when they have one or more Diamonds of Azzanadra in their inventory. He wields a poisoned dragon dagger.

name: Strongbones
examine: Strongbones is the last of the goblin high priests that players fight during the quest Land of the Goblins. When fighting him, he has the power to summon Skoblins to his aid. Upon his defeat, he will speak to the player. He is the most eloquent of the goblin high priests and speaks with the largest vocabulary.

name: Strongest monster
examine: The strongest monster in Old School RuneScape in terms of bosses and all monsters (based on combat level) is currently Verzik Vitur with a combat level of 1520. The strongest quest monster is currently Galvek, with a combat level of 608.

name: Suit of armour
examine: Suits of armour guard the prison door of the Cauldron of Thunder utilised in Druidic Ritual.

name: Sulphur Lizard
examine: Sulphur lizards are creatures found in the middle level of the Karuulm Slayer Dungeon in Mount Karuulm, requiring level 44 Slayer to kill. As they are only found within the volcano, players must wear the boots of stone, boots of brimstone or granite boots to protect themselves from the extreme heat of the dungeon floor. Additionally, players that have completed the elite Kourend & Kebos Diary can wear any type of footwear, or no footwear, without being rapidly burned.

name: Summoned Zombie
examine: Summoned Zombies are occasionally summoned by Invrigar the Necromancer and the Necromancer in the Necromancer Tower south of East Ardougne.

name: Suqah
examine: Suqah are a race of strange-looking but powerful creatures native to Lunar Isle. Players must have at least started Lunar Diplomacy to have access to Lunar Isle. Despite their fearsome nature, they have a peaceful relationship with the Moon Clan, but are aggressive to outsiders, effectively serving as guards.

name: Svetlana
examine: Svetlana is one of the citizens of Canifis. If you are not wielding a wolfbane dagger when you attack, she will turn into a werewolf. She is more friendly if you are wearing a Ring of charos.

name: Swamp Crab
examine: Swamp Crabs are aggressive monsters that disguise themselves as harmless Swampy logs. When a player approaches them, they will attack in a fashion that is identical to Rock Crabs. They can be found in multi-combat areas directly south of Port Phasmatys and along the path leading from Port Phasmatys to Slepe. It is recommended that lower-level players wanting to kill these stay near Port Phasmatys, as the path traverses through the Haunted Woods and players may encounter Feral Vampyres and Leeches.

name: Swamp frog
examine: Swamp frogs are frogs found west of Molch. There are many more found in the village, some are in an inaccessible enclosure used by the lizardmen as a source of food. However to the west of the enclosures there are some free roaming.

name: Swamp snake
examine: A swamp snake is a monster found in the Temple Trekking minigame. When it reaches 0 hitpoints, it should turn into a dead swamp snake.

name: Swordchick
examine: A Swordchick is a hybrid of a chicken and a swordfish. Players can create swordchicks in Creature Creation, in the basement dungeon of the Tower of Life building once they complete the Tower of Life quest.

name: Taloned Wyvern
examine: Taloned Wyverns are Slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 66 in order to be harmed. They reside in the Wyvern Cave on Fossil Island. Like with other Wyverns, an elemental, mind, dragonfire or ancient wyvern shield provides significant protection against their icy breath, and they are vulnerable to the effects of dragonbane weapons. These monsters require completion of the Bone Voyage quest to be assigned as a Slayer task.

name: Tanglefoot
examine: The tanglefoot is the boss of Fairytale I - Growing Pains. It drops the Queen's secateurs, which are needed to complete the quest.

name: Tar Monster
examine: Tar Monsters reside in the Tar Swamp area of Fossil Island. They hide underneath the tar and only appear as Tar Bubbles. Once a player steps near, they will emerge and attack using a typeless attack style.

name: Target
examine: A target is an object found in the Water Ravine Dungeon. It is found in the room that the black golem guards. It must be hit with a ranged attack.

name: Tarik (Nardah)
examine: Tarik is one of the guards in Nardah. He, along with Poltenip and Radat, guard Awusah, the mayor of Nardah.

name: Tarn
examine: Tarn Razorlor is an evil necromancer that dwells in his lair beneath the Abandoned Mine. He is the boss monster in the miniquest called The Lair of Tarn Razorlor, and is guarded by his undead minions, animated steel suits, and Terror dogs.

name: Tekton
examine: Tekton is one of the bosses encountered in the Chambers of Xeric. He was the artisan that created the chambers.

name: Temple guardian
examine: The Temple guardian (also known as Spots) is a dog-like monster that dwells in the entrance of the underground passageway to Canifis.

name: Temple Spider
examine: Temple Spiders are a more powerful variant of deadly red spiders found in the eastern section of the Forthos Dungeon.

name: Tentacle (Temple Trekking)
examine: A Tentacle is part of a five part swamp creature encountered during the Temple Trekking activity on the hard path. It has a max hit of 12, while the creature's head has a max hit of 20. It is recommended to poison a tentacle, as that will poison the whole monster. If all four tentacles are not killed before the head, the head will regenerate.

name: Terror dog
examine: Terror dogs are Slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 40 (unboostable) to kill. They are first encountered during the miniquest Lair of Tarn Razorlor, in which the player must fight two terror dogs, alongside some animated armour in addition to Tarn Razorlor himself. Upon completion of the miniquest, more terror dogs will appear in the room the player battled Tarn Razorlor in.

name: Terrorbird
examine: Terrorbirds (Aves Terror) are animals used by the gnomes as mounts. They are found on the west side of the Tree Gnome Stronghold. They are also involved in the Rag and Bone Man II quest, where the ones that don't have any gnomes mounted upon them will drop a special bone needed for the quest.

name: The Draugen
examine: The Draugen is a monster encountered during The Fremennik Trials quest that must be defeated in order to gain council member Sigli's vote. It can only be found by using a Hunters' talisman given by Sigli. This works very much like a Runecraft talisman, telling the player in which direction to travel to find the Draugen.

name: The Everlasting
examine: The Everlasting is the second boss fought in the quest Dream Mentor. This monster has fairly high Defence against melee and Ranged, but no Magic defence, so players should use Magic e.g. trident of the seas or Iban Blast in order to kill it effectively. It can be safespotted using the lectern to the north. After this monster is killed, it transforms into its third form, The Untouchable.

name: The Illusive
examine: The Illusive is the fourth and final boss fought in the quest Dream Mentor. Unlike the previous forms, it is much weaker in combat stats. It is similar in mechanics to the Giant Mole as it digs away during combat; fighting it requires patience, as players can only hit it once or twice before it digs and resurfaces elsewhere. It is most weak to Magic, so players should use trident of the seas or Iban Blast in order to kill it effectively. Using Magic is also beneficial because the player can attack it from a distance as it digs around.

name: The Inadequacy
examine: The Inadequacy is the first boss fought in the quest Dream Mentor. Due to its fairly high Defence level and a low Magic level, players should use Magic e.g. trident of the seas or Iban Blast in order to kill it effectively. This monster is very powerful and should not be underestimated, as it uses accurate and hard-hitting attacks. It summons Doubts, which serve as an annoyance to the player, as all of them are killed when the boss dies. After this monster is killed, it transforms into its second form, The Everlasting.

name: The Jormungand
examine: The Jormungand is a massive basilisk and the final boss of The Fremennik Exiles. After being subdued by V many years ago, he is reawakened by Bakuna.

name: The Kendal
examine: The Kendal is a monster from the Mountain Daughter quest. He is located in the cave north of the Mountain Camp.

name: The Maiden of Sugadinti
examine: The Maiden of Sugadinti is the first encounter in the Theatre of Blood. She was formerly a human known as Serafina. A myth was spread by the vampyres that she had successfully completed the Theatre of Blood and was granted freedom from the vampyres; however, this was simply a ruse to instill false hope into the citizens of Meiyerditch so that they could provide entertainment for the vampyres.

name: The Mimic
examine: The Mimic is a sporadic boss who can be fought by presenting a mimic casket to the strange casket found upstairs in Watson's house. Mimics can be obtained from an elite or master reward casket after asking the strange casket to enable the chance to obtain a mimic casket (which is disabled by default). The elite reward casket has a 1/35 chance of being a mimic, while master reward caskets have a 1/15 chance.[1]

name: The Nightmare
examine: The Nightmare of Ashihama, often simply referred to as The Nightmare, is a large, otherworldly horror who feeds on the life force of sleeping people, giving her victims horrible nightmares until their life force is completely drained and expires. There are no requirements to fight The Nightmare other than access to Morytania.

name: The Shaikahan
examine: The Shaikahan is a lionlike creature that prowls the eastern jungle of Karamja (usually south of fairy ring DKP) and is involved in the Tai Bwo Wannai Trio quest, where the player must help Tamayu defeat it. According to Tamayu, it is very agile, and possesses extreme regenerative abilities, making it difficult to fight under normal circumstances[1]. He describes it standing as tall as a man, with fore claws sharp enough to rip through metal, and with glowing eyes that "burn the embers of death".[2] He also claims it to be 'a source of indescribable evil' and 'a beast more foul than your dreams could imagine' that hunts in the jungle for anyone 'foolish enough' to come across it.[3] Swan Song reveals that the Wise Old Man encountered and defeated it at some point in recent history.

name: The Untouchable
examine: The Untouchable is the third boss fought in the quest Dream Mentor. This monster has very high Defence against melee and Ranged, but no Magic defence, so players should use Magic e.g. trident of the seas or Iban Blast in order to kill it effectively. It can be safespotted using the lectern to the north. After this monster is killed, it transforms into its fourth and final form, The Illusive.

name: Thermonuclear smoke devil
examine: The thermonuclear smoke devil, often referred to as Thermy, is the boss version of the smoke devil, found in the Smoke Devil Dungeon. It requires a minimum of 93 Slayer to damage. Located at the Smoke Devil Dungeon south of Castle Wars, the Thermonuclear smoke devil can only be attacked on a smoke devil task, with the exception of one kill for the Western Provinces Diary (provided that the player has 93 Slayer without boosting).

name: Thief
examine: A thief is a criminal found in various places around RuneScape, and can be a challenge for new or low level players. They can be either male or female. One of their characteristics is that they will stop attacking and try to escape when at low health.

name: Thing under the bed
examine: The Thing under the bed is a creature that can be found under the Wise Old Man's bed in Draynor Village. In members worlds, players can help the Wise Old Man do small tasks, one of which is to fight the Thing under the bed.

name: Third Age Mage
examine: The Third Age Mage is a monster that is spawned when fighting The Mimic. It is spawned alongside the Third Age Ranger and Third Age Warrior. It does not need to be defeated to beat The Mimic.

name: Third Age Ranger
examine: The Third Age Ranger is a monster that is spawned when fighting The Mimic. It is spawned alongside the Third Age Warrior and Third Age Mage. It does not need to be defeated to beat The Mimic.

name: Third Age Warrior
examine: The Third Age Warrior is a monster that is spawned when fighting The Mimic. It is spawned alongside the Third Age Ranger and Third Age Mage. It does not need to be defeated to beat The Mimic.

name: Thora (Miscellania)
examine: Thora is a subject of Miscellania currently located in the Miscellania market.

name: Thorhild
examine: Thorhild is a subject of Miscellania found in Miscellania Castle.

name: Thrantax the Mighty
examine: Thrantax the Mighty is a ghost that players must bring under their control during the Merlin's Crystal quest. If they fail, Thrantax will attack them.

name: Thrower Troll
examine: A thrower troll is a troll that attacks with ranged. They are relatively annoying monsters that throw rocks at passing adventurers, regardless of being engaged in combat or not. They are rarely ever on their own, preferring to be together in groups. Unlike most other monsters, the thrower troll's attacks are always successful hits. As they are found in multi-way areas, being attacked by three or more thrower trolls at once can be deadly.

name: Thrower troll (Trollheim)
examine: A thrower troll is a troll that attacks with ranged. They are relatively annoying monsters that throw rocks at passing adventurers, regardless of being engaged in combat or not. They are rarely ever on their own, preferring to be together in groups. Unlike most other monsters, the thrower troll's attacks are always successful hits. As they are found in multi-way areas, being attacked by three or more thrower trolls at once can be deadly.

name: Thug
examine: Thugs are level 10 monsters who are found exclusively in the Wilderness on members' servers. Having relatively high health and decent drops in comparison to other similarly level monsters make them an excellent monster to train on. Thugs are an excellent source of easy clue scrolls if they are killed while wearing a ring of wealth (i). Thugs in the Edgeville Dungeon respawn quickly and attack players aggressively regardless of level, making them an excellent source of low-effort, good-profit combat in terms of experience awarded and the herbs they drop.

name: Tok-Xil
examine: The Tok-Xil is a monster found in the TzHaar Fight Pits and Fight Caves. It resembles a rocky golem. It uses a ranged attack, with which it fires its spines at the player, and melee attacks, where it punches the player. Both attacks can hit up to around 13-14 damage.

name: Tok-Xil (Construction)
examine: A tok-xil can be built in the Monster space of the Treasure Room in a player-owned house. It requires 85 Construction to build and when built, it gives 2,236 experience.

name: Tolna
examine: Tolna Talvoy is the child of Launa and Brana Talvoy. When he was young, he left home as he wanted something greater than what he had.[1] He heard rumours of a lost civilisation east of Varrock and went in search of it, but when he reached the site, a rift opened up in the ground and swallowed him.[2]

name: Torag the Corrupted
examine: Torag the Corrupted is the second youngest Barrows brother. Torag's crypt is located to the south-west of the Barrows area. He uses melee equipment, which makes him vulnerable to Magic attacks. Torag's set effect is Corruption, which gives him a 25% chance per successful hit to lower the player's energy by 20%; having 50% energy would result in 10 percentage points of it being drained, leaving the player with 40% energy.

name: Torcher
examine: Torchers are creatures in Pest Control that look like winged snakes with bat wings and will actively attack the Void Knight. They have a long distance magical attack which can harm both players and the Void Knight. They can even launch this attack over walls, though if they are in the spaces right in front of one of the three gates, they cannot shoot over it, so keeping them closed will block those directly in front of it.

name: Tormented Soul
examine: The Tormented Soul is a monster encountered during The Ascent of Arceuus quest where five must be defeated in the Tower of Magic before heading upstairs.

name: Tortoise
examine: The Tortoise (Testudines giganteus) are trained tortoises used by the Gnomes in battle. They can be found north-west of the Grand Tree in the Tree Gnome Stronghold, just north of the swamp. Trainer Nacklepen is in charge of their combat development.

name: Tortured gorilla
examine: Tortured gorillas are found on Ape Atoll during and after the quest Monkey Madness II. They are also found in the Crash Site Cavern after completion of Monkey Madness II.

name: Tortured soul
examine: Tortured souls are level 59 monsters found in north-eastern Morytania, near the Ectofuntus outside of the entrance to Port Phasmatys.

name: Tough Guy
examine: The Tough Guy is a Menaphite henchman fought during The Feud quest. He will appear after Ali the Operator instructs the player to talk to the Menaphite Leader. The Tough guy appears at the southern end of Pollnivneach. The Tough guy is immune to poison, so poisoned weapons don't matter. He looks similar to the Menaphite Thug. Taking too long to kill him will result in him despawning. The Tough Guy has high magic defense.

name: Tower Archer
examine: Tower Archers are located on top of the archer tower in the Ranging Guild. They are aggressive to players of all levels. The archers have an attack range of 11. You must have an attack range of at least 9 to be able to hit the archers. Magic spells are permitted.

name: Tower guard
examine: Located in Yanille, the Tower guard is another of the many kinds of guards. However, these guards cannot be pickpocketed. They are around the city and some are located in the Watchtower.

name: Trapped Soul
examine: A Trapped Soul is encountered during the quest The Ascent of Arceuus. The Trapped Soul was a former and revered Shayzien general, who was resurrected by Xamphur. Players are requested by the Tasakaal to kill the Trapped Soul as compensation to help the citizens of Arceuus. Players can find the Trapped Soul by investigating the Ancient Grave south-east of Mount Karuulm which will result in tracks. Investigating the plants and tree stump along the tracks will allow you to find the Trapped Soul. When found, you will receive a chat message: A trapped soul that was lurking in the plants jumps out and attacks you!

name: Tree spirit
examine: Tree spirits are monsters which can be found in the Enchanted Valley using the fairy ring code bkq when attempting to cut down a tree. Because of the common nature rune drops supplemented by drops of rune and adamant axes and various seeds, tree spirits can be good money, although not much experience will be gained. The tree spirit's combat level varies depending on that of the player's, a minimum of 14, and up to a maximum of level 159.

name: Tree spirit (Lost City)
examine: The Dramen Tree Spirit only appears in Entrana Dungeon when doing the Lost City quest. Players have to fight it with limited armour and weapons, as it only appears on Entrana.

name: Treus Dayth
examine: Treus Dayth is the boss monster in the Haunted Mine quest. He has the power to possess objects around him and send them hurtling towards players. He is summoned when the player attempts to pick up the Innocent-looking Key.

name: Tribesman
examine: Tribesmen are people that inhabit the jungles of Karamja. They can be found in various areas around Karamja, notably near Brimhaven around a cauldron and in the Tai Bwo Wannai village. They may also be encountered during the Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup minigame when players attempt to cut the jungle bushes. Though their attacks have a fairly low max hit, any successful hit from them will inflict a potent poison, dealing 11 poison damage per hit. As a result, players are advised to bring antipoison when travelling through their areas.

name: Troll (20th Anniversary event)
examine: Trolls were occupants of the Realm of Memories during the 20th Anniversary event. During 2004, a troll could be found jailed in the Clock Tower Dungeon, but this was removed long before the release of Old School RuneScape. Eventually, they were replaced with shorter Mountain trolls.

name: Troll (Construction)
examine: A troll can be built in the Guard space of the Oubliette and Dungeon in a player-owned house. It requires 90 Construction to build and when built, it gives 1,000 experience.

name: Troll (historical)
examine: The Troll was a former character that appeared in RuneScape 2. It is arguably the most obscure character to have existed since the transition to RuneScape 2, with very little information and no screenshots of the monster surviving.

name: Troll general
examine: Troll generals are huge and powerful Giant trolls that live in the Troll Stronghold, on the top floor.

name: Troll spectator
examine: Troll spectators are trolls found in the Troll arena, where fights with Dad and Arrg take place. They watch instead of fight, just as the name suggests. They may be battled though, and are exactly the same as mountain trolls. They are non-aggressive, but if the player kills Dad, they will immediately attempt to attack the player.

name: Tstanon Karlak
examine: Tstanon Karlak is one of K'ril Tsutsaroth's bodyguards and can be found in the God Wars Dungeon, along with Zakl'n Gritch and Balfrug Kreeyath. Tstanon attacks with Melee and has a maximum hit of 15. Tstanon is usually not considered a threat compared to K'ril, since most players already have Protect from Melee active while fighting the Zamorak bosses.

name: Turoth
examine: Turoth are Slayer monsters that require a Slayer level of 55 to kill. They drop herbs and seeds commonly, though not as frequently as aberrant spectres, as well as frequent nature runes. In addition, they also drop the leaf-bladed sword.

name: Twig
examine: Twig is a troll that guards the prison in Troll Stronghold and appears in the Troll Stronghold quest. He holds the Cell key 1, which is needed to open the cell where Godric is held.

name: Twisted Banshee
examine: Twisted Banshees are stronger variants of banshees that require level 15 Slayer to kill. They are found exclusively within the Catacombs of Kourend, in a multicombat area. There is a safespot in the walkway between the two rooms. Players must wear earmuffs or a slayer helmet while fighting them in order to avoid the effects of their screams; which causes the player to take 7 damage and have their stats greatly reduced in Attack, Strength, Defence, Ranged, Magic, Prayer, and Agility with every attack received. They use magical melee, and their attacks are fairly accurate.

name: Typhor
examine: Typhor is a basilisk knight and a general of the basilisk army. It is fought during the penultimate battle of The Fremennik Exiles quest while Brundt the Chieftain engages Vritra in battle.

name: Tyras guard
examine: Tyras guards can be found at the Tyras Camp in Tirannwn. Tyras guards equip steel halberds as weapons, therefore a player can be attacked either next to a guard or one square away.

name: Tz-Kek
examine: The Tz-Kek is a level 45 monster found in the TzHaar Fight Pits and Fight Caves. It resembles a roughly man-high, amorphous blob of lava.

name: Tz-Kih
examine: The Tz-Kih is a monster found in the TzHaar Fight Pits and Fight Caves.

name: TzHaar-Hur
examine: The TzHaar-Hur are the weakest monsters in Mor Ul Rek. As they are TzHaar crafters, they are never armed, but they have four arms which they use to punch anyone who wishes to fight them.

name: TzHaar-Ket
examine: The TzHaar-Ket are inhabitants of Mor Ul Rek. Some of them can be found wielding a Tzhaar-ket-om. Some will have no weapon wielded, while some wield up to three Tzhaar-ket-em to accompany, or a Toktz-ket-xil.

name: TzHaar-Mej (monster)
examine: The TzHaar-Mej are both the leaders of the TzHaar people and powerful mages. They fight with both melee and magic using their staves. When attacked within 6 squares of other higher level TzHaar (Ket and Xil), the mage will cry out "Kot kl, zek e JalYt!" which roughly translates to "Save me, attack the human!" This will cause the nearby TzHaar to aid the TzHaar-Mej in combat.

name: TzHaar-Xil
examine: The TzHaar-Xil is an inhabitant of the Mor Ul Rek. They can be found wielding three Toktz-xil-ak, a set of Toktz-xil-ul (which they use in both melee or ranged style), or a Toktz-xil-ek. TzHaar-Xil are the second strongest race in TzHaar, excluding some Fight Cave monsters. The meleers can conveniently be ranged or maged from safespots around the various sulphur vents and fissures in the cave, though this is harder due to the fact that they are spread out more and the lack of safespots. Their appearance is small relative to other TzHaar creatures, and they are coloured black/red.

name: TzKal-Zuk
examine: TzKal-Zuk, often referred to as Zuk, is the last monster encountered in the Inferno. It is currently the second strongest monster in Old School RuneScape, and the strongest monster that must be challenged alone.

name: TzTok-Jad
examine: TzTok-Jad, commonly called Jad for short, is one of the strongest monsters in Old School RuneScape and the boss of the TzHaar Fight Cave minigame. With a combat level of 702, TzTok-Jad has a max hit of 97 and can easily kill most players in one hit with any of its three attacks: a Melee attack with its bite (max hit of 97), a blast of Magic in the form of a fireball (max hit of 95), and a boulder falling from the ceiling as a Ranged attack (max hit of 97). To add to the challenge, players must fight through waves of monsters in the TzHaar Fight Cave in order to reach TzTok-Jad and must do so solo and without being able to restock on supplies from the previous waves.

name: Ugthanki
examine: Ugthanki are camels found in the Kharidian Desert, south of Shantay Pass. Ugthanki are the only creatures that drop ugthanki meat, which is used to make ugthanki kebabs.

name: Ulfric
examine: Ulfric Longbeard is a skeletal boss monster who appears during Olaf's Quest. There is a ranging safespot at his grave. It is a good idea for players to turn on Protect from Melee to avoid the use of food. His max hit is rather low compared to monsters of a similar level, with the fact that Ulfric is inaccurate, makes him a very easy boss for players about his level.

name: Umbra
examine: Umbra is one of the four mages guarding Nex in the Ancient Prison, within in the God Wars Dungeon. Having mastered shadow magic, she enhances Nex's powers over shadow. As with all of Nex's mages, she is immobile.

name: Undead chicken
examine: Undead chickens are the reanimated remains of the chickens owned by farmers Alice and her now-ethereal husband. The same occurrence has happened to their cows who are now undead cows. They can be found west of the Ectofuntus near Port Phasmatys.

name: Undead cow
examine: Undead cows can be found west of Port Phasmatys in Morytania near the Farming allotment. As their name suggests, they are undead, so a salve amulet or a salve amulet (e) is effective to deal more melee damage. They are sometimes killed for their bones for the Ectofuntus, most commonly during Ghosts Ahoy and Animal Magnetism.

name: Undead Druid
examine: Undead Druids are followers of Ranul, the god of the moon, who have become corrupted and undead. They can be found in various sections of the Forthos Dungeon: the Crypt of the Moon east of the western dungeon entrance, the Temple Library (which has a nearby altar where players can recharge prayer) and the small chamber south of the Spider Den near Brother Aimeri, which requires a knife or slash weapon to access.

name: Undead Lumberjack
examine: Undead Lumberjacks are found during Temple Trekking. They will spawn during the second version of the broken bridge event. When spawning, they continuously spawn in groups of 5 and come out of the water one by one. After a group has spawned it takes about 30 seconds for the next group to spawn. Should a clothing piece not drop, a new undead lumberjack will spawn shortly after one is killed. Only one unique drop will be dropped per trip. It is, however, possible to get multiple pieces from one event if multiple lumberjacks are killed at the same time. A Dragon halberd special attack is a good option to kill more at once. Barrages work too. They do not give any combat experience.

name: Undead one
examine: The Undead ones play a critical part in the Shilo Village quest. Both skeletal and zombie undead ones are found in Ah Za Rhoon and Rashiliyia's Tomb, whereas the zombie undead ones are also found at the entrance to Shilo Village. They are decent training for people using Ranged, Magic, or a halberd.

name: Undead Zealot
examine: Undead Zealot are zombies that have a 5% chance to spawn[1] when a player opens any chest in the Shade Catacombs. Only the player who opens the chest to spawn them will be able to attack them.

name: Ungadulu
examine: Ungadulu is a shaman who is possessed by Nezikchened during the Legends' Quest. He has a combat level of 70, which becomes 169 when his demonic possession overcomes him. Despite this, Ungadulu cannot be attacked with melee or ranged weapons; he will throw players out of the Octagram, hitting them for between 4 and 10 damage. However, players can manually cast combat spells on him both inside and outside the Octagram to damage and kill him without being thrown by his spell.

name: Unicorn
examine: Unicorns wander around forested areas in RuneScape. On members servers, unicorns drop the unicorn horn, which are used in Herblore to make anti-poison potions. Unicorns are also one of the oldest monsters in the game, which appeared initially during the beta of RuneScape Classic. They are also one of the most updated monsters, having been graphically updated four different times.

name: Unicorn Foal
examine: A unicorn foal is a unicorn's offspring. They wander around forested areas in Gielinor. This monster is often found in the same area as the adult unicorn. Its coat is more of a golden colour opposed to that of the adults. It does not drop unicorn horns. Being weak and inferior to the unicorn, it may try to retreat from a battle.

name: Unicow
examine: A unicow is a hybrid of a cow and a unicorn. Players can create unicows in Creature Creation, in the basement dungeon of the Tower of Life building once they complete the Tower of Life quest.

name: Unusual Chicken
examine: Unusual Chickens were large chickens found throughout Lumbridge castle, Falador square, Varrock square, Camelot, and East Ardougne as part of the 2014 Thanksgiving event. They could be killed to receive thanksgiving dinners.

name: Uodai
examine: Uodai is an intelligent monkey guard that resides in the island city of Marim. Uodai is one of several guards that can appear if they talk to a monkey on Ape Atoll while in human form. He may appear along with several Monkey Guards.

name: Urium Shade
examine: Urium Shades lurk behind the gold door in the Mort'ton Shade Catacombs. They initially appear as moving shadows on the ground and then rise from the depths to attack or retaliate. Their remains can be cremated with redwood pyre logs, requiring a Firemaking level of 95. The Salve amulet and Salve amulet (e) work on Urium Shades but do not stack with the Black mask (i).

name: Uyoro
examine: Uyoro is an intelligent monkey guard that resides in the island city of Marim. Uyoro is one of several guards that can appear if they talk to a monkey on Ape Atoll while in human form. He may appear along with several Monkey Guards.

name: Valgerd
examine: Valgerd is a subject of Miscellania found in the Miscellania market.

name: Vampyre Juvenile
examine: Vampyre Juveniles are the lowest rank of vampyres. They can be found in the woods east of Burgh de Rott, in Meiyerditch, lower areas of Darkmeyer and inside the Crombwick Manor. They can be harmed by any weapon, but become mist and retreat at low health unless they are held with the special attack of the Rod of ivandis or Ivandis flail and then fed a Guthix balance, at which point they may return to human form, die instantly, or become a feral vampyre.

name: Vampyre Juvinate
examine: Vampyre Juvinates inhabit the woods east of Burgh de Rott, outside Ver Sinhaza in Meiyerditch, and are also fought during In Aid of the Myreque and Temple Trekking. They can only be harmed by silver weapons or efaritay's aid, and can be defeated by using the special attack of the Rod of ivandis or Ivandis flail and a dose of Guthix balance potion when it is below half health. This can result in the juvinate dying (granting 100 Prayer experience), reverting to human, or turning into an even more powerful feral vampyre (which are vulnerable to weapons other than silver). If the juvinate reverts into a human, they will thank you and give you a reward.

name: Vanguard
examine: The Vanguard are a trio of Xeric's former commanders encountered in the Chambers of Xeric.

name: Vanstrom Klause
examine: Vanstrom Klause, formerly Ascertes Hallow, is a vampyre noble, one of the brutal henchmen of Lord Drakan, and the leader of the Vyrewatch. Vanstrom is a murderous fiend who strikes terror into the hearts of the Myreque, a resilient group of guerrilla fighters from Morytania dedicated to fighting their vampyric overlords. Vanstrom is Safalaan Hallow's father, the former King Ascertes Hallow, who was transformed into a vampyre by Lowerniel Drakan after his capture during the Siege of Hallowvale.

name: Vasa Nistirio
examine: Vasa Nistirio is one of the bosses encountered in the Chambers of Xeric, who accompanied Xeric during his exile as his High Priest. After obtaining untold power from the glowing crystals, he went mad with power and attempted to overthrow Xeric, only to be defeated and bound to them to serve as a guardian of the chambers as punishment.

name: Venenatis
examine: Venenatis is a large poison spider that resides east of the Bone Yard, and is the only monster to drop the treasonous ring. She uses multi-target Magic and long-ranged melee attacks. She is able to drain Prayer as well as perform a lethal stun attack that can hit up to 50 damage, and may combine it with another attack if the player does not have Protect from Magic active, which is capable of instantly killing the player. Unlike the other Wilderness bosses, Venenatis' lethal attack has a chance of failing.

name: Vera
examine: Vera is a werewolf located in the Hair of the Dog in Canifis. When fighting her, it is recommended to equip a Wolfbane dagger if you are a low level, otherwise she will turn into a werewolf. She cannot be killed as part of a werewolf Slayer task in her human form.

name: Verac the Defiled
examine: Verac the Defiled is the youngest of the six Barrows brothers. Verac's crypt is located to the north-west of the Barrows area. He uses melee equipment, which make him vulnerable to Magic attacks. Verac's set effect is Defiler, which gives him a 25% chance per attack to ignore Defence, armour bonuses and protection prayers.

name: Verzik Vitur
examine: Lady Verzik Vitur is a vampyre who rules over Ver Sinhaza. She is the hostess as well as the final boss of the Theatre of Blood, and currently the strongest monster in Old School RuneScape.

name: Vespine soldier
examine: Vespine soldiers are offspring of Vespula. They will only appear if the team allows a lux grub's growth meter to reach zero, at which point it will transform into a vespine soldier, while also healing Vespula and the abyssal portal. Players will need to deal with the vespine soldiers while also working against Vespula if this occurs.

name: Vespula
examine: Vespula is one of the bosses encountered in the Chambers of Xeric. It is a parasitic wasp from the Abyss that Xeric and his followers stumbled upon when attempting to open a new dimensional tear.

name: Vet'ion
examine: Vet'ion (pronounced "VET-ee-un") is a Zamorakian skeletal champion that resides north of the Bone Yard and south of Lava Dragon Isle, and he is the only monster to drop the ring of the gods. Like other bosses in the Wilderness, he can also drop the dragon pickaxe.

name: Vitreous Jelly
examine: The Vitreous Jelly is the superior variant of jellies. It has a 1/200 chance of spawning while on a Slayer task of jellies after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Vitreous warped Jelly
examine: The Vitreous warped Jelly is the superior variant of Warped Jellies. It has a 1/200 chance of spawning while on a Slayer task of jellies after purchasing the unlock Bigger and Badder for 150 Slayer reward points from any Slayer master.

name: Viyeldi
examine: Viyeldi is a spirit encountered during the Legends' Quest, when Nezikchened - disguised as Echned Zekin - asks you to kill him. When you first enter his room, Viyeldi pretends to be a hat on the ground until picked up. Upon beginning a conversation with him, he informs you of a different path you could take in the quest. You can choose to carry out Nezikchened's request, and kill Viyeldi using the Dark dagger that Echned Zekin gives you at the source of the holy water spring, or you could listen to him, and kill the warriors for the fragments of the Heart crystal to progress.

name: Vorkath
examine: Vorkath (roughly translated as pathetic failure/weakling/runt in the dragonkin's language) is a draconic boss-monster first encountered during the Dragon Slayer II quest as the penultimate boss. Created by Zorgoth during the Fourth Age's Dragonkin Conflicts, the blue dragon is one of his subjects that has survived his experiments in the laboratory beneath the dragonkin fortress on Ungael. Despite its phenomenal strength, Zorgoth abandoned this Vorkath on Ungael due to its lack of aggression, leaving it as a "distraction" for any humans that would stumble onto the island.

name: Vulture
examine: Vultures are small flying monsters found north-west of the Agility Pyramid located in the Kharidian Desert. When they are found flying, Ranged or Magic is required to attack them. They are briefly featured in Rag and Bone Man II where the player must kill one to obtain a vulture wing.

name: Vyrewatch
examine:
The Vyrewatch are the vampyric vanguard that receive blood tithes from the population of Morytania and suppress any resistance to the Drakan overlords.
They patrol the skies as both soldiers and lords of Meiyerditch and ask any human, including the player, that catches their attention for a blood tithe.
